title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chili powder, thoroughly.
Roll in ball; sprinkle with chili powder.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with Ritz.

title: old english cheese soup(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Melt 1/4 cup butter in a skillet; add vegetables and saute until crisp-tender.
Set aside.
Melt 1/2 cup butter in a Dutch oven over low heat.
Gradually stir in flour; cook, stirring constantly, until bubbly.
Gradually stir in milk; cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is smooth and thickened.
Add sauteed vegetables, salt, cheese and broth; cook, stirring frequently, until cheese is melted and mixture is well heated.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Mix both soups together and pour over chopped chicken.
Spread bread crumbs on bottom of baking dish, then add chicken mixture and top with bread crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: honey nut granola
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine all ingredients except raisins; mix well.
Bake in lightly greased pan (13 x 9-inch) at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in raisins.
Spread mixture onto ungreased sheet; cool.
Store in a cool, dry place or in refrigerator.
Makes about 9 cups.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix eggs and onions into cornbread before cooking.
Crumble up bread.
Add margarine (melted), soup, water, and cooked squash (drained) to crumbled cornbread.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Bake for 30 minutes at 400°.

title: jello poke cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Cool. Prick cake with 2-prong fork at 1/2-inch intervals.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cold water; stir.
Spoon over cake. Chill 4 hours.
May top with Cool Whip.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: In a Dutch oven, combine the stock, carrots, celery, bay leaf, thyme and pepper.
Bring to a boil over high heat.
Add the chicken and return to a boil.
Cover; reduce the heat to low and simmer gently while you prepare the dumplings.

title: ruth's corned beef salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: "no-fail" dessert
directions: Blend
well
and serve with a smile.
For best results, make a fresh batch every day.

title: opal's finnish oatmeal cookies
directions: Grind raisins and peanuts through food grinder.
Set aside. Sift flour, baking powder, salt and spices into large bowl.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender.
Add raisin and peanut mixture, sugar and oats.
Mix well.

title: sticky buns
directions: Butter Bundt tin.
Lay rolls around tin.
Mix sugar, pudding and nuts.
Sprinkle on rolls.
Pour melted butter over all.
Let set in warm place overnight.
Bake next morning at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Measure and set aside in a bowl the oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Put in saucepan, sugar, butter, milk and cocoa.
Boil 3 minutes and pour over peanut butter mixture and then mix until all ingredients are moist.
Drop onto wax paper by teaspoon and let cool.

title: taco salad dip
directions: Layer as listed and serve.

title: apricot coconut balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Form into balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Refrigerate in covered container.

title: au gratin chicken bake
directions: Combine chicken, soup, water chestnuts, spaghetti, 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese, milk and pimento.
Mix lightly.
Spoon into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with remaining Cheddar cheese and additional Parmesan cheese.
Continue cooking until Cheddar cheese melts.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken breasts with dried beef
directions: Cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with slivered dried beef. Wrap each breast with a slice of bacon and arrange on layer of dried beef.
Mix the sour cream and soup and spread over chicken breasts.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Uncover and bake 1/2 hour longer.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add milk and continue beating.
Add whipping cream and half and half.
Add other ingredients together and put in container for ice cream freezer.
Must have ice cream salt and ice for the freezer.
Churn until frozen.

title: scallop casserole parmesan
directions: Lightly grease 4 large clam shells or small casserole dishes. Pack equally with scallops.
Add garlic salt and paprika to oil and brush tops of scallops.

title: avocado chicken dip
directions: Combine chicken, avocado, tomato, onion, jalapeno peppers and garlic.
Stir remaining ingredients until well blended.
Cover and chill until ready to serve.
Makes 2 3/4 cups dip.

title: john and marion's favorite play dough
directions: This is a great, non-toxic play dough that will inspire your children's imagination!

title: chocolate pecan dessert
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 10 minutes; cool.

title: ripple soup
directions: Heat milk to hot, but not boiling.
Mix egg and enough flour to make almost dry.
Stir into hot milk; cover and let set on stove for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chili-cheese balls
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients.
Shape into 3/4-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake until set, 15 to 18 minutes.

title: lemon pecan bread
directions: Cream the butter and sugar well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour.
Stir in pecans and lemon peel.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans and bake at 350° for approximately 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Drain all vegetables.
Toss all ingredients together in large bowl; marinate overnight.
(Keeps 2 to 3 weeks in refrigerator.)

title: raw spinach salad
directions: Wash spinach and drain on paper towels to absorb excess water. Tear or cut leaves into bite-size pieces and put in a salad bowl. Add green pepper, onion rings, lemon juice, oil, tarragon, salt and pepper.
Toss lightly.
Garnish with egg slices and anchovies. Serves 6 to 8.

title: sweet potato cookies
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs.
Blend in sweet potatoes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Thaw shrimp if frozen.
Combine flour, bread crumbs, salt, pepper and paprika.
Dredge shrimp in flour mixture.
Melt butter in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add shrimp and garlic. Cook, stirring frequently 1 to 3 minutes until shrimp turns pink. Stir in parsley.
Serve over rice.
Squeeze lemon juice over shrimp if desired.
This is also good served over fettuccine alfredo.

title: yum yum chicken
directions: Wash and pat dry chicken breasts.
In a large bowl combine next 5 ingredients and crush.

title: apple spoon up
directions: *Two cups apple pie filling can be used instead of the apples and 1/2 cup sugar.

title: prune cake
directions: Blend sugar, oil and eggs.
Sift flour, salt, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice together.
Add alternately with buttermilk to the egg mixture.
Add vanilla, nuts and prunes.
Mix well and pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish which has been greased with butter. Bake at 300° in preheated oven for 1 hour.

title: chicken tamale pie
directions: Prepare muffin mix as directed, adding 1/2 cup cheese to mixture.
Set aside.
Combine chicken, soup, chilies, corn, onion and chili powder in large saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until heated through.

title: trout in foil
directions: You will also need heavy foil.

title: chicken a l'orange
directions: Melt oleo in frypan.
Add chicken and brown.
Remove chicken and place in shallow pan and arrange orange slices.
In same frypan, make sauce by adding flour, salt and cinnamon.
Gradually add orange juice.
Cook over medium heat 5 minutes. Pour over chicken.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: he-man casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in oil, drain.
Add seasonings. Cook noodles according to package directions.
Pour meat mixture over cooked noodles. Stir in soup and milk.
Add beaten egg.
Put in deep dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese and egg breakfast
directions: Spread cubed bread in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with cheese, onions and bacon.
Pour mixture over all.
Let stand 6 hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 9 x 9-inch cake pan.
Cook and stir together the beef and onion until meat is brown.
Stir in seasoning mix, then spread in pan.
Sprinkle with chilies.
Beat milk, baking mix and eggs until smooth; pour over meat and chilies.
Bake for 25 minutes, then sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until knife comes clean.
Cool 5 minutes; cut into squares.

title: country butter
directions: Bring margarine to room temperature.
Mix corn oil and buttermilk in food processor.
Add margarine and process until thoroughly mixed and smooth.
Keep in covered plastic container. Makes 2 pounds.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Mix meal, flour, milk, butter and eggs.
Add celery and onions.
Pour into 8-inch square dish and bake about 25 minutes at 400° or until golden brown to make cornbread.
Break up cornbread and mix with crumbled bread and pour turkey broth over this. Allow to stand for a little while and then blend well.
Add salt and pepper to taste and sage, if desired.
Place in Pyrex dish and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not overcook.
It will be dry.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Mix ingredients together in bowl. Drop by spoonfuls on baking sheet. Bake at 375° until brown.

title: peanut brittle cookies
directions: Spread into 15 x 10 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° or 375° (depends on oven) for 25 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: chicken rotel casserole
directions: Cook and dice chicken. Cook and drain egg noodles. Melt margarine with onion and peppers. Add mushrooms, broth and Ro-Tel. Simmer 20 minutes. Add chicken and cheese. Stir until melted. Add noodles and peas. Pour in dish. Cook at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Saute onion in oleo; set aside.
Mix all other ingredients, then add onion mixture.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling tea.
When starting to thicken, add other ingredients.
Put in molds.
Serve on lettuce leaf with mayonnaise.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Mix sugar, vanilla, eggs and butter together.
Then mix in beans.
Put in a pie shell and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Pie should taste like a pecan pie.

title: homemade clay
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Knead for at least 5 minutes. Colored clay may be made by adding a small amount of food coloring to water before mixing.
If the mixture is too sticky, add more flour.
If it is too thick, add more water.
Colored clay can be mixed together to create a marbled effect.
After the clay is shaped, you can just let it harden or you can put it on a cookie sheet in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
When the sculpture cools, it can be painted.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Place uncooked rice in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Salt and pepper chops, then brown in skillet.
Arrange browned chops, overlapping, on top of rice.
Place a slice of onion, tomato and pepper ring on top of each chop.
Pour bouillon over this.
Cover securely with foil.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute green pepper, onion and celery in olive oil until tender.
Add tomatoes, salt, pepper, red pepper and water; cook for 10 minutes.
Combine flour and sugar; add enough water to make a smooth paste and stir into tomato mixture.
Cook and stir until slightly thickened.
Add shrimp and pea pods.
Cook until pea pods are tender and shrimp are cooked.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken and set aside. Cook spaghetti (don't overcook) in broth with onion flakes added. Drain spaghetti and add all other ingredients in a large pot or bowl. Pour mixture in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Place in oven at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted. Top with garnish of fresh parsley.

title: apple chicken salad
directions: In a small bowl, combine first 6 ingredients.
Chill until ready to serve.
Place lettuce leaf on a serving plate and top with chilled chicken salad.
Yields 1 or 2 servings.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Crumble rolls.
Place in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix seafood with juices and spices. Pour over crumbled rolls and pat down. Slice half stick of margarine into thin slices and place slices across top of casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Grease baking dish.
Place potatoes in bottom, then onions, next beef and cream of celery soup.
Sprinkle with pepper. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: seafood lasagne
directions: Cook
noodles
as
directed
on package.
Prepare white sauce and stir in tarragon.
Grease a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Layer 1/3
of the
noodles,
seafood,
1/3 white sauce and 1/3 cheese; repeat twice.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: banana split (without ice cream)
directions: Mix the graham cracker crumbs and the melted butter together and press to the bottom and sides of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat the powdered sugar, eggs and remaining butter until fluffy.
Spread over the crust.
Add a layer of drained, crushed pineapple, then a layer of sliced bananas followed by a layer of Cool Whip. Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Add cherries on top.
Refrigerate.

title: salmon party loaf
directions: Drain salmon.
Mix in ingredients, except pecans.
Roll in pecans and chill 2 hours.

title: cucumbers in sour cream dressing
directions: Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and garlic cheese dressing.
Add vegetables and toss.
Chill several hours before serving.
If preferred, large head cauliflower (broken into florets) may be substituted for the cucumbers.

title: watergate salad
directions: Sprinkle Jell-O (dry) over pineapple. Add Cool Whip and marshmallows. Add 1/2 cup nuts if desired. Mix well. Put in bowl and refrigerate.

title: egg strata
directions: Soak bread in milk.
Drain and reserve milk.
Combine with eggs.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put soaked bread in bottom of pan. Add egg mixture.
Top with cheese and the crumbled bacon.
Pour margarine over top.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until firm.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cherry cola salad
directions: Heat juices drained from pineapple and cherries.
Pour over Jell-O.
Cool.
Mix pineapple, cheese, cherries and nuts.
Add to Jell-O mixture.
Blend well.
Add Coke and blend again.
Chill until firm.
Serve.

title: what's missing? potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes, cut into small cubes and boil, covered with water, for 45 minutes.
Drain well and refrigerate until completely cold.
Add remaining ingredients and mix very well.

title: chicken and wine
directions: Dip chicken in egg, then bread crumbs.
Brown in oil.
Drain oil and saute onions and mushrooms until tender.
Add diced tomatoes, tomato sauce and white wine.
Add chicken to this mixture.
Cover and simmer 1/2 hour, until chicken is tender. Serve over rice.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Mix the first six ingredients together, then mix 1/2 cup flour with all the other ingredients and then mix all ingredients together.
Cook in tube pan at 250° for 3 hours.
Glaze.

title: barbecue grilled shrimp
directions: Mix everything together but shrimp.
Marinate shrimp in sauce for 24 hours.
Cook on grill until done, 3 to 5 minutes per side.

title: cheese and sausage dip
directions: Melt cheese in top of double boiler.
Add next 4 ingredients and heat.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate.
Best if made the day before serving.

title: mabel's cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients and let stand refrigerated overnight. Great with crackers and celery.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large bowl, beat eggs until foamy. Beat in flour, sugar and brown sugar.
Add cooled melted butter. Stir in chips and nuts.
Pour into pie shell and bake 1 hour. Serve with whipped cream or ice cream, if desired.

title: almond rice hot dish
directions: Brown sausage, celery, rice, onions and green pepper in frypan. Cook and stir over medium heat until meat and rice are brown.
Drain off any grease or the rice will not brown. Drain mushrooms;	reserve
liquid
to add to water used in soup mix. When
meat	mixture is brown, add drained mushrooms (chopped), half of the almonds and the soup mix.
Turn into buttered dish and sprinkle
remaining
almonds
on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Serves 6 to 8.

title: scripture cake
directions: Look up in the Bible and make a delicious cake.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients
and
bake at 350° for 30 minutes. (Instead of using soup, I cook noodles in tomato juice.) If not enough tomato, I add a little pizza sauce after all mixed together.

title: sauerkraut salad(a minute on the lips, a lifetime on the hips.)
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Mix the remaining ingredients.
You may heat second mixture to dissolve sugar, if you want.
Pour over kraut mixture.
Chill 24 hours.
Serves 4.

title: apple pie
directions: Sift together 1/2 cup sugar, 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon and 1 tablespoon flour and sprinkle in bottom of pie crust. Place the apples on top of this mixture. Sift together 1/2 cup sugar, 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon and 1 tablespoon flour and sprinkle over apples. Cut up the oleo over sugar mixture and apples. Cover with top crust. Fold bottom crust edge over top and flute. Slit top crust to allow steam to escape. Bake at 425° until brown and apples are bubbly.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook cauliflower tender-crisp; drain well and cool.
Melt cheese with 1/2 stick butter; drizzle over cauliflower.
Crumble Ritz crackers and combine with 1/2 stick butter.
Put crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.
Can be made ahead and refrigerated.
Bake before serving.

title: fruit cobbler delight
directions: Place pie filling in bottom of a 28 x 18 x 4 cm oven or microwave dish; sprinkle 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon into pie filling. Mix dough ingredients together and sprinkle over pie filling. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: new orleans chocolate cake with icing
directions: Sift sugar and flour into large bowl.
Set aside.
Put oleo, shortening, cocoa and water in pan and bring to boil.
Pour over flour mixture.
Stir well.
Add soda to buttermilk; add to mixture, then add eggs, cinnamon and vanilla.
Beat well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350°
for 25 minutes.
About 5 minutes before cake is done prepare icing.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Prepare cake mix using 4 eggs and no water.
Add cherry pie filling and
mix well.
Bake as directed on package in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Serve topped with whipped cream.

title: shoo-fly cupcakes
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar, margarine and Crisco; save 1 cup for top of cakes.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over crumbs; beat until smooth.
Fill each tin 3/4 full and sprinkle crumbs on top.
Place tins on top rack of oven.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 30 cupcakes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Tear day-old french bread into 1 inch cubes and put into 1 large or 2 medium greased casserole dishes.
In a separate bowl blend 4 eggs, cheddar cheese soup, 1 soup can of water, 2 cups cheese.
Pour over bread.
Bake uncovered 30 minutes at 350 degrees.
(Cooked sausage, bacon, onion, etc. can be added if desired.)

title: favorite banana bread
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add the flour and soda alternately with the buttermilk, ending with the flour.
Add vanilla.
Fold in mashed bananas and pecans.
Bake in a Bundt pan at 325°.
May also be baked in 2 loaf pans.

title: smelt dip
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add egg and water.
Dip smelt in mixture and deep fry.

title: jambalaya
directions: Saute onion and pepper.
Add sausage and rice, stirring constantly.
Combine Ro-Tel and water to make 3 cups liquid.
Add this liquid along with soup, gravy mix and seasonings to the sausage and rice mixture.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat.
Cover and cook for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: dutch apple cake
directions: Peel and core apples.
Cut each apple in 8 parts.
Sift flour, salt and sugar into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Add oil and milk; whip with a fork.
Pat out to cover bottom of pan and push dough up along sides about 1-inch.
Arrange apples over pastry and sprinkle streusel over top.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: garlic cheese bread
directions: Combine all ingredients; refrigerate for a couple of hours. Spread on French bread or bread of your choice.
Place under broiler to brown.

title: oven pot roast
directions: Sprinkle meat lightly with salt and pepper; coat lightly with flour.
Brown well in a skillet with olive oil.
Reduce heat; add onions, garlic and celery; cook until limp.
Transfer to a 3-quart pot.
Stir broth, water, steak sauce and mustard into skillet and bring to a boil, scraping meat particles from pan bottom.
Pour liquid and vegetables over meat; cover and bake at 325° for 2 3/4 hours or until almost tender.
Add carrots and wine; cover and cook 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove meat and carrots; keep warm.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: rrickaroni
directions: Brown hamburger meat in skillet with onion, salt, paprika and pepper.
Simmer until meat has browned.
Drain off grease.
Add tomatoes, mushrooms and macaroni.
Cook on medium heat for 20 minutes.

title: extra special spinach dip
directions: In medium bowl, blend the soup mix, sour cream and mayonnaise; add lemon juice.
Stir in spinach and water chestnuts.
Chill. Makes about 3 cups dip.

title: holiday punch
directions: Mix all ingredients (except ginger ale and sherbet); pour ginger ale slowly down the side of punch bowl.
Garnish with orange and lemon slices.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and press in pan.
In a small saucepan over low heat, melt chocolate chips, butter and vanilla. Spread over the peanut butter mixture.

title: grandma's apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour oil over sugar and let stand. Sift together 2 cups flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Cream eggs, sugar and oil and add to dry mixture, using mixer.
Mix together 1 cup flour, apples, nuts and vanilla and add to batter.
Bake in a Bundt pan for 1 1/2 hours or a 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour.
Cool before removing from Bundt pan.

title: chicken on cornbread
directions: Cook chicken.
Debone.
Cook carrots, onion, celery, salt and pepper in broth.
Cook until done.
Use strained broth for sauce.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.
This recipe makes 3 loaves.

title: vegetable spaghetti with tuna(with or without dairy)
directions: Drain tuna.
Lightly saute onion, garlic, broccoli, mushrooms and oregano in oil and margarine.
Add zucchini and tomatoes, cook until zucchini is tender-crisp.
Break tuna in chunks and add to vegetables.
Stir in sour cream for moist sauce.
Toss with spaghetti and Parmesan cheese.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and kidney beans.
Drain and let cool.
In large bowl, combine lettuce, onion and tomato.
Add ground beef mixture.
Just before serving, add remaining ingredients and stir.

title: chicken mediterraneo
directions: Brown chicken in large skillet in margarine.
Transfer chicken to large casserole.
Add vegetables (onions, garlic and carrots) to skillet and cook 5 minutes.
Add broth and sauce; bring to boil and ladle over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, covered.
Set chicken aside.
Divide twists between 2 casseroles. Mix half of sauce into each.
Arrange chicken on top of each casserole.
Serve one.
Cool, wrap and freeze the other.
Reheat, covered, in preheated 400° oven for 2 hours, uncovering the last 15 minutes.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: frozen daiquiris
directions: Combine all ingredients and keep frozen.
Makes 3 1/2 quarts.

title: caramel corn & candy crunch
directions: Place popcorn in greased roasting pan and keep warm in 300 degree oven.
Grease saucepan and cook on medium heat the brown sugar, butter and corn syrup to boiling, stirring constantly, until thermometer reads 255 degrees (hardball stage-about 4 minutes).
Remove from heat, add baking soda and vanilla, then pour over popcorn.
Stir to coat and bake at 300 degrees for 10 minutes.
Stir and bake another 5 minutes.
Let cool, break into smaller pieces and add M&M's, peanuts and raisins.
Store in sealed container.
Makes 9 cups.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Mash berries in large pan.
Add sugar and lemon juice.
Heat to boiling over high heat, stirring constantly.
Boil, stirring, until translucent and jam is thick, about 30 minutes.
It will boil and pop; skim off foam quickly.
Immediately pour into hot, sterilized jars, leaving headspace.
Wipe off rims and seal. Makes 5 jars.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Boil chicken and debone; break up into strips.
Put tomatoes, soup, bell pepper and onion together and heat (good to simmer about 5 minutes).
Put about half a bag of chips on the bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add chicken and pour mixture on top. Add grated cheese.
Cook for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Put chicken breasts in shallow pan.
Mix undiluted soups together and pour over chicken.
Spread sour cream over top. Sprinkle almonds over sour cream.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Serve sauce over rice.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Beat together and put in oblong pan and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until done.

title: tomato relish
directions: Cook together until somewhat thick.
Makes approximately 7 pints.

title: star-spangled brownies(an award-winning boy scout recipe)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare brownie mix as directed on package, except bake 20 minutes.
While brownies are baking, beat vanilla, egg, milk and cream cheese in a large bowl until smooth. Pour over baked brownie layer.
Bake until topping is set, 25 minutes.
Cool 2 hours.
Arrange cherries in stripes like flag and blueberries are star field.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli, stems and florets; add raisins or almonds and bacon and stir.
Add Miracle Whip, sugar and vinegar.
Chill well.

title: paradise salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate at
least
hour
before serving.
Slice and serve on lettuce.
May
be frozen for future use.
May be used for dessert.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: egg nog from camille lane may
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 4 tablespoons cold water.
Let set 10 minutes.
Add hot milk.
Let thicken.
Beat egg yolks and sugar gradually, then add whiskey.
Combine with gelatin mixture and let thicken.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and then whipped cream.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar, vanilla and salt.
Add chocolate chips.
Drop by spoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Place in preheated 400° oven and turn off.
Do not open until cooled.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender, then pull apart.
Fix dressing as instructed, but use chicken broth instead of water to mix.
Mix chicken broth with soup and set aside.
Then layer dressing, then chicken and top with soup mixture in a casserole dish; repeat. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cornmeal chicken nuggets
directions: Combine cornmeal, chili powder and cumin in small bowl.
Add chicken and toss to coat well with mixture.

title: bahamas dove
directions: Marinate dove at least 2 hours in wine.
Roll marinated dove in flour; brown in oil.
Mix soy sauce, ginger, vinegar and brown sugar; heat.
Add garlic, pineapple and pepper to dove.
Heat to boiling; add sugar mixture to dove.
Simmer about 45 minutes. Serve with steamed rice.

title: pumpkin pudding
directions: Put milk in bowl; add 2 packages of pudding mix.
Blend with whisk until well blended.
Will be very thick.
Add pumpkin, nutmeg, cinnamon and ginger.
Blend all together.
Refrigerate about 3 hours to blend the flavors.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry for 9-inch pie pan. Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion in pastry-lined pie pan.
Blend remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie pan.
Bake 15 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 300°.
Bake 30 minutes longer or until knife inserted 1-inch from edge comes out clean.
Let pie stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Makes 6 servings.

title: scalloped onions
directions: Slice and boil onions until tender.
Alternate layers of onions, bread crumbs, butter, pepper and salt in a casserole dish. Add enough milk to cover.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: del monte potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: holiday a-b-c salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cold water.
When slightly jelled add pineapple. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let jell.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Mix
ingredients
with	an
electric
mixer.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread crumbs. Spread in a lightly greased casserole (9 x 13-inch or longer) dish. Top with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Saute mushrooms, onion and garlic in butter and set aside. Saute chicken cutlets on both sides in frying pan to seal in juices.
Arrange in baking dish; put mushroom mixture over chicken.
Mix other ingredients together and pour over chicken. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Stir sauce to mix juices and sprinkle with shredded Swiss cheese; bake 5 minutes longer to melt cheese.

title: nancy's crab quiche
directions: Bake pie shell in 350 degree oven for 7 minutes.
Spread filling in pie shell and bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Baked pie can be frozen when wrapped well in foil.
Thaw and warm in 350° oven.

title: ham loaf
directions: Pat sugar evenly over bottom of loaf pan.
Arrange cloves over sugar.
Beat milk and eggs together and add to meat with corn flakes and green pepper.
Press meat in pan over sugar and cloves. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Invert on platter; discard cloves.
Serve with plum sauce.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Line an 8-inch plate with a pastry. Combine sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon and salt. Add to beaten eggs and vanilla; stir until smooth. Pour into pastry lined pie plate, then pour in rhubarb. Dot crust with butter. Place top of crust over filling; seal and flute edges. Cut 2 small slits in center. Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes. Remove from oven and brush with butter. After brushing with butter, wipe off with a napkin as to remove excess butter.

title: colonial poppy seed cake
directions: Combine seed and milk in a large bowl and let stand at room temperature for 3 to 4 hours.
Take out butter to soften or use a microwave to soften, not melt.
Add other ingredients to milk and seed.
Beat at medium speed for 1 minute or so.
Pour into a greased and floured loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Top will be browned and the center will spring back when touched to check doneness.
Cool 10 minutes and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Makes one loaf.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Make brownies according to directions.
On top of brownies, after baking, pour 4 tablespoons strong coffee, mixed with 1 teaspoon of sugar.

title: chicken dumplings
directions: Open cream of chicken soup; add 1 can sweet milk and margarine.
Cook on low heat.
When starts cooking good, add meat (separate with a fork) and add a teaspoon of salt to chicken. When this is cooking good, add your dumplings.

title: garlic herb cheese ball
directions: In a bowl, with mixer at medium speed, beat softened cream cheese, butter, garlic, parsley, vinegar, herbs and Worcestershire sauce until fluffy and well mixed.

title: apple cake
directions: Grease pan (9 x 13-inch or 9 x 9-inch) and fill halfway with apples that have been sliced.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Mix other ingredients and spoon over apples. Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Good warm or cold.
Cool Whip or ice cream on top, if desired.

title: chicken and vegetables
directions: Slice and shred all vegetables. You can use whole, boneless, or chopped chicken breasts. Mix vegetables and chicken with seasonings you prefer. Have a little oil in your cast iron skillet. Put vegetables and chicken in the skillet and stir well. Turn down and simmer until your desired doneness.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients into a batter. Melt 3/4 butter in 10 x 14 pan. Pour over melted butter, then add large can of peaches with syrup over batter. Sprinkle 3/4 cup sugar over top and sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: remoulade sauce
directions: Combine lemon juice, vinegar (tarragon, if you have it) and seasonings.
Gradually add oil.
Stir with fork or rotary beater to blend well.
Add celery and onion.
Makes 2 cups.

title: stir-fried veggies
directions: Melt a tiny bit of butter in a pan (electric skillet or wok works best).
Stir until onion begins to be transparent. Stir constantly.
Season with lemon pepper or seasoning salt or with favorite seasonings.

title: easy fruit cake
directions: Put
candied
fruit,
dates
and pecans in large mixing bowl and
set aside.
Beat eggs, vanilla and salt.
Pour over the fruit
mixture
and
mix together.
Sift sugar and flour. Mix with other ingredients.
Preheat oven to 250°.
Line your bread pan
with foil.
Press cake batter into the pan.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Cool before storing.

title: guacamole tarts
directions: In a bowl, combine tomato, garlic, lime juice, salt, pepper and hot pepper sauce.
Dice avocado and add to mixture, mashing until spreadable.

title: caesar salad
directions: In large bowl, mix first 6 ingredients and add the next 3 ingredients.
Add 1 package greens (spinach) and croutons.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Stir in soup.
Pour into casserole dish.
Cover with sour cream and layer of Cheddar cheese.
Top with Tater Tots and bake for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: kentucky corn cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into cupcake liners in large muffin tins.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Yield: 2 dozen.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers, onion and green pepper in a bowl.
Add sugar, vinegar, salt and celery seed.
Mix well.
Cover and store in refrigerator.
Wait 24 hours before enjoying.
Pickles will last about 3 months.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix salmon, seasonings and eggs.
Add milk and flour sifted with soda; mix well.
Drop batter from spoon into hot vegetable or olive oil.
Fry until brown, turning once.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Cut rounds out of bread with whiskey glass.
Butter one side and toast in oven on a cookie sheet.
Remove from oven; turn over to cool.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix dry and add wet ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Refrigerate and take out as needed.

title: frozen chocolate bananas
directions: Put chopped peanuts into shallow bowl.
Put a piece of waxed paper on a plate.
Put chocolate into skillet.
Put skillet on burner.
With adult help, turn burner to low heat.
Stir with wooden spoon until chocolate melts.
Turn off burner.
Remove skillet from burner.
Peel banana.
On cutting board, cut banana in half with table knife.
Push a wooden spoon into cut end of banana half.
Use table knife to spread chocolate on all sides of banana halves.
Then roll in peanuts.
Put bananas on waxed paper-lined plate.
Freeze until hard.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter, sugar, egg yolks, bananas, nuts, flour and salt. Add soda to milk; fold in beaten egg whites and pour into pan. Bake one hour slowly.

title: barley salad(low-fat recipe)
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Stir in barley and 1/4 teaspoon salt. Reduce heat and cover.
Simmer 50 to 60 minutes or until tender. Drain and cool.
Transfer to large bowl.
Add tomatoes, green onions, parsley, cheese and mint.
Combine lemon juice, oil, garlic, remaining 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Pour over barley mixture; toss.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.
Great served with tortilla chips as an appetizer.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni by directions on package.
Blend flour, mustard, salt and pepper together.
Melt margarine in 1-quart saucepan. Add flour mixture.
Cook until blended; add milk and cook for about 10 minutes.
Add cheese and heat until cheese melts.
Drain and rinse macaroni.
Layer in greased casserole with sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: aloha pineapple punch
directions: Cut off tops from pineapple; reserve tops.
Cut out fruit from shell, leaving 3/4-inch wall.
Punch a hole in each reserved top large enough for a straw; replace top.
Wrap each pineapple in aluminum foil; refrigerate until serving time.

title: salmon with biscuit topping
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over medium heat.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add salmon liquid and milk and cook until thickened, stirring frequently.
When mixture has thickened, remove from heat and add to it the salmon from which the skin and bones have been removed, and cheese.
Pour into greased casserole. Place small biscuits on top.
Bake.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Lightly brown onions and peppers in bacon drippings.
Combine all ingredients in a casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° until bubbly and brown on top.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Layer cooked macaroni, cheese and tomatoes.
Dot each layer with salt, pepper and margarine.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Beat
oil,
sugar, eggs and vanilla until well blended. Combine
dry
ingredients and add to sugar mixture; beat well. Stir
in
apples
and
nuts.
Pour	into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan or Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.

title: corn casserole with jalapeno peppers and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine corn, creamed cheese and peppers in a 1 1/2-quart covered casserole.
Bake, covered, about 30 minutes until heated through.
Stir once or twice.

title: peanut butter coffee cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, stir together 1/2 c brown sugar, 1/2 c flour, 1/4 c peanut butter and melted butter or margarine till crumbly; set aside. Cream 1/2 c peanut butter and shortening. Gradually beat in 1 c brown sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating till light and fluffy after each addition.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour in baking dish. Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: bill's salad
directions: Slice and quarter oranges.
Mix oranges, lettuce and onions together.
Add French dressing to your taste.
Garnish with almonds.

title: broiled crab meltaways
directions: Slice English muffins in half, then cut each half into fourths and arrange on two cookie sheets.
Mix remaining ingredients well in a small bowl. Spread on the English muffin quarters.
Freeze them at least 30 minutes, even if you plan to use them that night. (It is easiest to make them ahead.)
Remove from cookie sheets and place in freezer bags.
They may be kept frozen for weeks. When ready to serve, broil them until they are bubbly and slightly golden brown, just a few minutes.
Serve hot.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Boil chicken broth, then add soy sauce.
Pour eggs into center of
contents
while still boiling.
Add parsley.
This soup is delightful served with Oriental meals.

title: granola
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients. Sprinkle on pan. Microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes until brown (you may toast this in a regular oven). Add raisins. Mix well and spread on paper towels to cool. Store at room temperature in a tightly closed container.

title: rolled flank steak kabobs
directions: Salt and tenderize steak letting it sit 1 hour.
Mix remaining ingredients well and spread over meat.
Roll up steak lengthwise and cut into 1 inch thick slices.
Put onto skewers. Broil 6 inches above coals for 5 - 6 minutes on each side.

title: orange whole wheat pancakes
directions: Beat eggs with vanilla and almond extract.
Mix in orange juice and oil; set aside.
In a separate bowl, mix whole wheat flour, baking soda and salt.
Add liquid to dry ingredients, stirring just enough to mix.
Cook on grill or griddle over medium heat.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: janet's broccoli casserole
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, melt margarine over low heat.
Add broccoli and onion; saute, covered, over medium heat.
Stir well and remove from heat.
Cook rice, drain and add to broccoli mixture.
Add soup and cheese.
Pour into buttered 2 1/2-qt. casserole and bake, covered, for 30 minutes at 350 degrees.
If dry, add 1/2 cup milk.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain fat.	Add taco seasoning; simmer according to package directions.
Layer 13 x 9-inch pan with refried beans, meat mixture, salsa, green chilies and grated cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Top with black olives.

title: parsley buttered potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Drain thoroughly and replace over heat for a minute to evaporate excess moisture.
Pour melted margarine over potatoes.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley and serve immediately.

title: chicken swiss casserole
directions: Put chicken in greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Combine soup and milk in small bowl; stir well.
Spoon over chicken.
Sprinkle with Stuff and Such.
Drizzle oleo over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding mix and pineapple.
Add other ingredients and put in a large glass dish.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.
Serves 12.

title: cream cheese pie(makes two)
directions: Blend together softened cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and whipped topping with mixer.
When well blended, put in pie shells and refrigerate 1 hour before serving.
Add topping before serving.

title: caramel nut cake
directions: Cream margarine, shortening, brown sugar and sugar in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder in bowl. Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beating well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Fold in peanuts.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan for several minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.
Frost with favorite caramel icing.
Yield: 16 servings.

title: plain apple cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Mix with butter or oleo. Add eggs, apples and vanilla.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: fruit salad
directions: Take large bowl, mix all ingredients together.
Sweeten to taste.
Serve cold.
Use more or less fruit if you wish.
Use large apples.

title: no fat chocolate sauce
directions: In a small saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa and cornstarch.
Add skim milk.
Cook and stir constantly over medium heat until thickened.
Continue cooking for 2 more minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Serve warm or cool.
Can keep in refrigerator covered for one week.
Use on ice cream, cake, etc.
Only 47 calories per tablespoon.

title: italian sausage and broccoli pasta
directions: Serve with rice (mixed with turmeric to give it a rich yellow color), shredded coconut, sliced banana and chutney.
These are usually placed in separate dishes and passed around to be sprinkled on top of the bobotie.

title: orange slice bars
directions: Mix sugar with margarine. Stir in eggs; mix well, then add vanilla, 1 1/2 cups flour, baking powder and salt. Toss candy and nuts in the remaining 1/2 cup flour and add the mixture. Thoroughly grease a jelly roll pan or cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cool 15 minutes in pan. Cut in 2-inch squares. Cool. Cut in half again.
Can sprinkle with powdered sugar on top.

title: hawaiian tea
directions: Heat 1/2 cup water and sugar together until sugar dissolves. Brew tea; add sugar-water mixture and the remaining ingredients.

title: monkey milk
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender or jar. Cover and blend or shake until mixed well.
Makes 2 servings.

title: goulash casserole
directions: Cover bottom of 1 1/2-quart casserole with meat.
Spread rice over meat.
Cover rice with onion; sprinkle salt and pepper.
Top with tomatoes and water.
Cover; bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: lemon chiffon cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients into bowl.
Make well in center of dry ingredients.

title: grandma normandeau's hamburger soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large stock pot (except rice or macaroni).
Boil over low heat 45 to 60 minutes.
Serve over rice or macaroni.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Melt margarine in glass bowl on High in microwave.
Add both sugars, vanilla and egg.
Stir to smooth consistency.
Gradually add flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir until mixed.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
This makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Fill cups 1/3 to 1/2 with mix; finish with boiling water. Makes approximately 115 cups.

title: old fashioned raisin bars
directions: Boil water and raisins.
Remove from heat and add margarine. Let cool.
Stir in egg and sugar.

title: party bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread in hollowed out bread. Replace bread lid and wrap all in foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Use bread pieces and corn chips, etc., as dippers.

title: italian style roasted peppers
directions: Wash and dry whole peppers.
Line broiler pan with foil.
Broil peppers 10 minutes, turn, boil additional 10 minutes or until peppers turn almost black.
Set peppers aside to cool.
Under cold running water, peel off skins, remove stems and seeds and slice in half.
In large bowl combine all ingredients and marinate for 4 hours.
Take peppers out of refrigerator and allow to reach room temperature.
Prepare platter with a bed of bite-size lettuce and serve peppers with slices of fresh Mozzarella cheese and olives. Serves 6.

title: calico bean bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. In large skillet, cook bacon 1 minute, tear into small pieces. Add ground beef and onion, cook until browned. Stir with fork to break up meat, drain. Add ketchup, sugar, brown sugar, mustard, salt & vinegar, stirring to blend. Spoon mixture into a casserole dish and add remaining ingredients, stirring lightly to blend. Bake 1 hour.
Recipe can be doubled or tripled.

title: aunt evelyn's taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning.
Spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan (double if you like it thicker).
Chop the vegetables thin and small.
Add in layers in pan in the following order:
lettuce, green pepper, onion, tomato and Cheddar cheese.
Use Tostitos for dipping.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk as directed.
Add sour cream.
Mix well and blend in Cool Whip.
Put in dish layers of vanilla pudding, wafers and bananas.

title: lemon-lime jello salad
directions: Mix packages of Jell-O with boiling water until dissolved. Add mayonnaise and blend with electric mixer until smooth. Refrigerate until partially set.
Fold in remaining items, adding milk and cold water mixture last.
Pour into Pyrex dish and let set until firm.

title: potato soup
directions: In a large kettle, cook potatoes, carrots and celery in water until tender.
Drain, reserving liquid.
Set vegetables aside.
In same kettle, saute onions and butter until soft.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually add milk; stir until thickened.
Stir in vegetables.
Add 1 cup or more of reserved liquid until soup is desired consistency.
Add shredded cheese.
Simmer.
Serve hot. Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: chocolate lime swirl
directions: Butter a 10-inch spring-form pan or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line sides with 12 or more cookies; mix with butter and place on bottom of pan.
Save some for topping.
Dissolve gelatin in hot water. Add lemon juice and sugar and let stand to cool.
Whip milk in large bowl until stiff peak is formed.
Mix in gelatin mixture and add lemon rind and green food coloring.
Pour over crumbs and top with remaining crumbs.
Chill about 4 hours or until firm.

title: 9-grain bread
directions: Combine in 4-cup measuring cup the 2 cups water, molasses and margarine.
Heat in microwave until margarine is melted; stir. Combine in large bowl the yeast, dry milk powder, flours and cereal.
Stir to blend.
Combine wet and dry ingredients.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in lightly oiled large bowl and cover with towel or plastic wrap.
Let rise until double in bulk. Punch down and knead.
Shape into loaves and place in lightly oiled (or spray with Pam) bread pans.
Let rise again until doubled in bulk.
Place loaves in oven.
Turn on oven to 350°.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes depending on your oven and "doneness" taste.

title: peanut butter balls(no bake confection)
directions: Melt peanut butter chips and condensed milk in heavy saucepan. Stir constantly and do not scorch.
Blend in cream cheese.
Mix in the ground nuts, raisins or dried fruit.
Chill at least 2 hours.

title: chicken fried in coke
directions: Place chicken in skillet.
Spread ketchup over all the pieces. Add the cola.
Cover and cook on medium for 30 minutes.
Uncover skillet and continue cooking until done and until some of the liquid is evaporated.
Turn chicken a couple of times to prevent sticking.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil the chicken breasts.
Cut cooked chicken into small pieces.
Mix together the cheese, sour cream, chicken soup and poppy seed.
Add cut up chicken pieces and mix well.
Put in casserole dish.
Melt the margarine.
Mash up the crackers and mix with the melted margarine.
Spread over chicken mixture.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple tidbits and fruit cocktail.
Set aside.
Stir lime Jell-O into sour cream.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Carefully fold in drained fruit.
Keep refrigerated.
You can use different flavors of Jell-O.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Mix!
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Serve with bagel crisps or pita chips.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Cut up pork or chicken.
Heat 1 inch oil in wok.
Mix flour, cornstarch, water, 1/2 teaspoon salt and egg.
Mix together to make batter.
Stir meat in batter until coated, then fry.
I use my fingers to coat the meat, I find it easier.
Fry for 5 minutes. Drain on plate with paper towel.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream butter flavor Crisco, cream cheese and milk in medium bowl at medium speed until well blended.
Beat in sugar and vanilla.
Mix in flour.
Stir in nuts.
Drop level measuring tablespoonfuls of dough 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Remove to cooling rack.
Makes 3 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: bacon and eggs
directions: Place 3 pretzels side by side after dipping them in the melted chocolate or bark.
The pretzels should be on waxed paper with space between each group of 3.
Drizzle white chocolate in the center of the "bacon and top with an M&M for the yolk.

title: baked stuffed tomatoes
directions: Remove the stem ends of tomatoes and cut out the centers. Fill with filling made from the rest of the ingredients.
Place in a baking dish and bake in a moderately hot oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Place zucchini in a small amount of boiling water, simmer until tender.
Drain and cool.
Add remaining ingredients. Place in an unbaked pie shell.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add 2 whole eggs.
Separate the other two and add the yolks.
Save the 2 whites for the icing. Beat in well. Sift flour, salt and baking powder.

Add alternately with milk. Beat with electric mixer until smooth. Bake in four 8-inch greased and floured layer pans at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched with fingers. Frost with icing or may use whipped cream and coconut.

title: taco salad
directions: Grate cheese; add beans, chopped onion and pimento.
Mix into large bowl.
Break chips; add also chopped lettuce.
Just before serving, add dressing and fold in all ingredients.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk according to directions on box.
Then mix in sour cream and Cool Whip.
Layer this mix in a large bowl along with vanilla wafers and bananas.
This mix keeps well in the refrigerator and then layer with cookies and bananas when ready to serve.

title: harvest potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar into mixing bowl and blend well.
Bring to a rapid boil in saucepan the margarine, shortening, water and cocoa.
Pour over flour/sugar mixture and mix well.
Combine remaining ingredients and add all at once to batter, mixing well. Pour into lightly greased and floured sheet cake pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Let cool 10 to 15 minutes while preparing frosting.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown beef with onion and green pepper in a large skillet over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally to separate meat; drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce.

title: stephen's lasagna
directions: Noodles:
Fill large pan with 3 to 4 quarts water, 1/2 tablespoon salt and 1 tablespoon oil.
Bring to a boil; put lasagna noodles in and cook for time stated on the box.
Drain noodles.
(Begin remaining steps while waiting for water to boil and noodles to cook.)

title: shrimper's delight
directions: Split fresh shrimp in half from the head to the top of the tail.

Place shrimp on a cookie sheet with peeling side down. Sprinkle garlic salt, Season-All and salt on fresh shrimp. Sprinkle self-rising flour lightly over the top of the seasoning. Pour melted butter over the top.
Bake at 500° for 10 minutes. Serve hot in shells.

title: zucchini raisin cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add egg, beat well.
Add zucchini and set aside.
Combine all dry ingredients and add to zucchini mixture.
Stir thoroughly, then add raisins.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yield:
3 dozen.

title: gingerbread(diabetic dessert)
directions: In large bowl, cream together margarine, fruit sweetener and yogurt.
When well blended, beat in egg whites.
Combine dry ingredients separately and add to batter.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch pan which has been sprayed with nonstick coating.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 16 pieces.
One piece = 1 bread and 1 1/2 fat exchanges and contains 140 calories, 6 grams fat, 19 grams carb, 3 grams protein, 140 mg sodium and trace of cholesterol.

title: oyster sauce chicken
directions: Coat chicken with flour and deep fry.
Put the rest of the ingredients in a pot and bring to a boil.
Add chicken and simmer about 5 to 10 minutes, turning chicken to coat with sauce.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In large mixing bowl, cream the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla. Gradually blend in flour mixture.
Stir in M&M's.
Roll into balls; place onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Melt the cheeses in a double boiler. Mix with sausage and serve warm.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix and blend first 8 ingredients. Add carrots. Bake in 3 layer pans for 30 minutes at 350° or one 9 x 13 pan for 45 minutes.

title: chicken dressing bake
directions: Toss stuffing mix with half can of soup.
Add chicken broth and beaten eggs.
Spread mixture in baking pan, 9 x 9-inch.
Top with cooked chicken.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: In a large saucepan, stir the yeast into the warm water.
Add sugar, salt, oil and half the flour.
Beat the mixture until consistent.
Add 3 more cups flour and mix with hands.
Turn out onto counter top and knead for 10 minutes.
Add flour only as needed to make dough dry enough to handle.
Let rise in saucepan until double.
You might cover with a towel to hold in warmth. Punch down.
Reshape into long, skinny loaves (1 1/2-inch diameter before rising).
Let rise again until double or triple in bulk on cookie sheets.
Bake at 425° until the bread is dark and crispy. Cut into bite-size pieces, ensuring a crust on each piece.
Stab with fondue forks and dip into the Cheese Fondue mixture.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add grated carrots and oil. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 3 layers.

title: microwave caramel corn pops
directions: Melt butter, syrup, salt and brown sugar together.
Cook 2 minutes on high.
Add vanilla and soda; should foam up.
Pour pops in large grocery bag and syrup mixture over pops while it's still hot.
Shake bag really well.
Cook for 4 more minutes, shaking well after each minute.
Pour out on wax paper and separate.

title: salmon souffle
directions: Remove bones and skins and separate into flakes and add seasonings.
Cook bread crumbs in milk 5 minutes.
Add salmon and egg yolks, beaten until thick and lemon colored.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Turn into buttered loaf pan or other shape desired.
Set in pan of hot water and bake at 350° until firm.
Serve with cream sauce and peas and a little pimento.

title: egg roll
directions: Mix all ingredients except dough.
Cut dough in squares, put ingredients in middle, wrap and tuck in ends.
Heat oil to 350°. Deep fry egg rolls, turning both sides until golden brown color. Drain excess oil before serving.

title: butterscotch noodles
directions: Melt morsels in a double boiler.
Mix in noodles and nuts. Drop one spoonful on a cookie sheet and let cool.

title: filling for cherry pie
directions: Drain cherries into separate bowl.
Put cherries and all ingredients, except butter, into saucepan.
Cook slowly until thickened.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Add pieces of butter.
Top with lattice top.
Bake as usual.

title: oreo cake
directions: Crush 3/4 of Oreos and press in bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan. Pour enough melted butter over this to hold it together.
Mix pudding and milk together; add cream cheese.
Pour over Oreo crust.
Spread Cool Whip over all.
Top with crushed Oreo cookies. Refrigerate until cold.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces.
Brown it well and drain.
Cut potatoes into cubes and add to bacon.
Add water to just cover potatoes and bacon.
Boil until potatoes are soft.
Add creamed corn.
Simmer about 15 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Enjoy!

title: crown jewel cake
directions: Prepare first
3 packages Jell-O separately using 1 cup hot water and 1/2 cup cold water for each.
Pour into separate 8 x 8 x 2-inch pans and chill overnight.

title: okra pickles
directions: Pack okra tightly in jars; place one clove garlic and hot pepper in each jar.
Combine water and remaining ingredients in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Pour boiling vinegar mixture over okra.
Seal jars.
Process in water bath 5 to 7 minutes.

title: cream cheese roll-ups
directions: Spread cream cheese, covering the top side of each slice of meat.
Place a thin strip of green onion at the edge of meat and roll up, keeping as firm as possible.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. In mixing bowl, combine 3/4 cup sugar, flour 3 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt. Blend in milk, melted butter and vanilla; beat until smooth. Pour batter into square 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. In small bowl, combine remaining sugar, brown sugar and remaining cocoa.
Pour in hot water; mix well. Pour mixture over batter in pan. Do not stir. Bake 40 minutes or until center is almost set. Let stand 15 minutes. Spoon into dessert dishes. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: frosted lemons
directions: Grate rind from 2 lemons.
Slice them in half and juice them. Combine rind, juice and sugar and stir until sugar dissolves. Pour mixture into a chilled ice tray or shallow pan and slowly add half and half.
Stir constantly until well blended.
Freeze 2 hours.
Cut remaining lemons in half lengthwise, removing juice and pulp.
(Save for another purpose.)
Fill each half with lemon cream.
Serve at once with mint garnish.
Serves 4.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Fry all ingredients except Mozzarella cheese.
Place in pan; top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: sawmill gravy
directions: Put bacon grease in deep skillet and heat, adding flour, salt and pepper; stir constantly, until brown.
Add water while stirring, keep adding until you reach desired thickness.
Makes approximately 6 servings.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: In a bowl, dissolve yeast and warm water.
Add sugar, salt and half of flour.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Add egg and shortening. Gradually beat in remaining flour until smooth.
Roll out dough to a circle, 1/4-inch thickness.
Spread with softened butter; sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Roll up and pinch finished edges together to seal.
Cut into 3/4-inch slices and place on greased baking sheet, allowing space between each for rising. Allow to rise until double in size.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until browned.
While warm, drizzle powdered sugar over rolls.

title: spinach
directions: Wash and take out big stems.
In skillet add 1 to 2 tablespoons of margarine.
Add handful of spinach, stir until wilted, add another handful of spinach, stir until wilted.
Do the same until all has been wilted.
Takes about 5 minutes.
Serve while hot.
I always use vinegar before eating.
It's really good. You must try it.

title: tropical orange cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease and lightly flour (on bottom only) a 9x13x2 inch pan. Cream together the butter and sugar.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.

Combine the baking soda with the buttermilk. This will foam so be sure your bowl is large enough. Add the 1 1/2 of flour to the batter alternately with the buttermilk mixture. Coat the dates, orange slices, and walnuts with the 1/4 cup flour.
Stir into batter.
Pour into pan and bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched in center.
Cool and frost.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Combine all of the ingredients and beat 2 minutes.
Pour into 2 large well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Drizzle glaze over warm loaves of bread.

title: orange cookies
directions: Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
I ice while warm.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add vanilla, eggs and milk. Mix in dry ingredients.
Roll out and bake on a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: norwegian meat balls
directions: Mix everything thoroughly together and let stand for 3 hours before making into balls.
Fry in hot vegetable oil.
After the meatballs are well browned, cover with water and simmer for 30 minutes.
Thicken liquid for gravy.

title: 5 spice beef-n-rice
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Cook until tender.
Stir in seasonings, rice, soup and tomatoes.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Put cheese on top and cover for a few minutes for cheese to melt.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Combine ingredients; add whites last.
Bake in a pie shell.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix altogether, except berries.
Do not overbeat.
Fold in berries.
Bake in muffin tin at 350° for 45 minutes, or until done.

title: grandma cunningham's cornbread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with buttermilk to egg mixture.
Add the butter and bake in 8 to 10-inch cast-iron skillet.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: coating for chicken
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and coat the chicken.
Roll in corn flakes and put in a greased pan.
Then pour 3 teaspoons melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix and set aside.

title: penuche nuts
directions: Bring sour cream and sugars to soft boil.
(When dropped in water, starts to form balls.)
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour on aluminum foil on cookie sheet.
Cool and break up. Store in airtight containers.

title: amaretto lace cookies
directions: In a saucepan, combine Amaretto, butter and dark brown sugar. Bring mixture to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in pecans and flour.
Beat until well blended.
Drop mixture by level tablespoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake only 6 cookies at a time.
Bake in a preheated hot oven (375°) for 6 to 8 minutes or until deep brown and bubbly.
Cool cookies on cookie sheet for 1 minute.
While cookies are still warm, roll up cookie like jelly roll.
Cool. Store in an airtight container in a cool, dry place.
Makes 40 cookies.

title: willie's corn salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: snack sandwiches
directions: Cook hamburger, sausage and soup mix, then drain.
Add Velveeta until melted.
Spread on party bread and bake until warm.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Combine first three ingredients and melt.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Spread into buttered loaf pan and refrigerate.

title: almond punch
directions: Add water to make a gallon.
Garnish with orange or lemon slices.

title: stuffed chicken
directions: Combine salt and pepper, reserving 1 teaspoon for the stuffing.
Season fryers well, rubbing inside and out, then rub the outside with oleo.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients and drop in miniature muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Do not grease tins and do not serve with butter as these biscuits are rich and short.

title: deep dish biscuit pizza
directions: Brown beef and onion. Drain off fat.
Stir in tomato paste, mushrooms and seasonings. Simmer 10 minutes. Press biscuit dough into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan to form crust. Spread meat over top.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: cowboy special
directions: Cook hamburg (with onion, if desired)

title: oriental appetizer
directions: Combine cornstarch and sugar in pan; add vinegar, soy sauce and pineapple juice.
Mix well.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 to 2 minutes or until thick.
Put remaining ingredients in chafing dish and pour sauce over.
Keep warm and serve with toothpicks.

title: christmas wreaths
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Spoon onto wax paper.
Place cinnamon bits on wreaths while mix in hot.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and cut up potatoes and cover with water.
Salt them and boil until a little tender.
While potatoes are cooking, melt margarine in a heavy saucepan.
Stir in the flour, chopped celery and chopped onion, stirring constantly, until the paste cooks and bubbles a bit, but don't let it brown, about 2 minutes.
Add hot water, continuing to stir as the sauce thickens.
Bring to a boil; add salt and pepper to taste.
Lower the heat and cook, stirring for 2 to 3 minutes more.
Remove from heat.
Pour this sauce into the undrained potatoes when done and add enough water to make a soupy consistency, as thick or thin as you like.
Simmer for an hour or as long as you need over a low heat or in your slow cooker. This soup is very good served with biscuits or onion rolls.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve in a pretty punch bowl.

title: cranberry-orange relish
directions: Drain crushed pineapple and reserve the syrup.
If necessary, add enough water to this syrup to make 1/2 cup of liquid; set aside.
Mix together the crushed pineapple, celery and nuts and also set aside.

Place jello gelatin into desired serving bowl. Pour 1 cup boiling water over the jello and mix until dissolved. Add the reserved pineapple liquid, along with the cranberry-orange relish to the gelatin; stir to combine.
Place in refrigerator. When the gelatin is partially set, stir in the pineapple, celery and nut mixture.
Chill until firm.
Delicious with turkey. Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: hot ham rods
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Fills 8 hot dog buns.
Wrap in foil and chill until ready to use.
Heat in oven or on grill.

title: quick buttermilk rolls
directions: Mix together all ingredients except oil and flour, then add vegetable oil.
Add just until easy to handle the 2 to 2 1/2 cups flour.
Mix and knead.
Shape as desired, as bread or sweet rolls. Let rise 45 to 60 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: bleu cheese dip
directions: Reserve 1/3 cup Bleu cheese.
Combine Bleu cheese and cream cheese until mixed (low speed).
Add mayo and half and half, mix until blended (medium speed).
Stir in remaining Bleu cheese (this makes the dip chunky).
Chill at least 3 hours.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: microwave apples
directions: Peel, slice and wash apples.
Shake water off and put in glass dish.
Cover and cook on High for 5 minutes.
Mix sugars, cornstarch and allspice together.
Sprinkle on apples, stirring gently.
Cook on High 5 more minutes.
Dot with butter and add vanilla.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except fried onions. Place in casserole dish. Bake at 300° for 40 minutes. Top with fried onions and bake 5 minutes more.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Place peas in bottom of casserole dish.
Layer asparagus spears over peas.
Pour mushrooms over; then heat soup in a saucepan.
Pour over the other ingredients.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Mix cabbage as you would for slaw; stuff small peppers and cold pack for 15 minutes.

title: cherry or blueberry cheesecake
directions: Put your cream cheese and condensed milk into a medium sized bowl and mix together well.
Squeeze lemons and add juice or about 1/2 cup of bottled lemon juice.
Beat well.
Melt the butter and pour into a pie plate. Then put your graham cracker crumbs in after the butter.
Mix that together to form your crust.
Pour cream cheese mixture in next.
Let that chill for about 15 to 20 minutes until firm.
Then put your blueberry or cherry pie filling on top and chill until time to serve.

title: sausage and cheese breakfast casserole
directions: Butter or spray with Pam a 2-quart casserole dish.
Butter 8 slices of bread and place in dish; cover with 8 slices of cheese. Brown sausage and crumble on top of the bread and cheese.
Butter the other 8 slices of bread and put on top.
Beat eggs with milk; pour over casserole.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: black bean salad with cumin vinaigrette
directions: Place beans in large mixing bowl.
Add peppers, red onion and scallions.
In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients, except cilantro garnish.
Mix well to combine.
Pour over bean mixture. Toss well to combine.
Serve at room temperature.
Garnish with cilantro.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate chip pan cookies
directions: Melt
margarine in baking pan.
Mix sugar, eggs, margarine and vanilla in mixer bowl;
mix well, then add flour and soda. Mix well.
Fold in chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into the baking
pan
that the butter was melted in (8 x 13-inch). Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: cathedral cookies
directions: Melt chocolate chips with oleo.
Cool.
Add eggs and vanilla. Blend well.
Mix marshmallows and nuts.
Pour chocolate mixture over marshmallows mixture.
Sprinkle 3 pieces of wax paper with powdered sugar.
Roll in rolls.
Chill.
Cut in slices.

title: marinated salad
directions: Cook vegetables about 5 minutes until crisp-tender.
Drain. In bowl, mix vegetables, onion and salad dressing; toss to coat. Cover and chill 2 to 24 hours, stirring once or twice.

title: crunchy south carolina peach crisp
directions: Sprinkle peaches with sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg mixture. Place in 2-quart glass baking dish.
Combine flour, oats, brown sugar and cinnamon in medium mixing bowl.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over peaches.
Microwave on High 4 minutes. Rotate dish one-half turn.
Cook additional 3 to 4 minutes.
Serve warm or cold with ice cream or whipped cream.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheesy chicken wings
directions: Wash chicken wings; pat dry.
In a bowl, combine the crumbled crackers or bread crumbs, herbs and Parmesan cheese.
Add seasonings and mix well to blend.

title: bulgogi korean b~b~q beef
directions: Mix all ingredients, marinade for awhile. I grilled it on my outdoor gas grill, but I am sure it would work fine on the stove as well. I like to eat this dish with white rice.

title: tom heyde's presbyterian award-winning chile
directions: Brown meat in skillet with onion and garlic.
Add Worcestershire sauce and seasoned salt. Stir in tomato sauce, picante sauce and kidney beans. Cook, uncovered, 20 minutes.

title: pop in oven stew
directions: Set oven to 325°.
Bake for 2 to 3 hours.

title: dried fruit pies
directions: Choose kind of dried fruit. Soak fruit overnight. Wash and cook until soft-cooked.
Drain off water. Add sugar and your favorite spice. Chill well in refrigerator.
Roll out Butter-Me-Not biscuits.
Fry in Mazola oil in electric skillet for slow even cooking.
One package of dried fruit makes about 20 pies.

title: caramel-oatmeal bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line 9-inch square baking pan with foil, letting ends extend above 2 sides of pan.
Lightly grease foil.

title: chow chow
directions: Wash and chop cabbage, peppers, cucumbers and onions together. Add salt; let stand for 3 hours.
Drain.
Boil the sugar, vinegar and celery seed; add to chopped ingredients.
Can while hot.

title: busy day casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add salt, pepper and chili powder. Cook well and add soup and tomato sauce; simmer 5 minutes.
Pour over cooked macaroni.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs and grated cheese.
Bake at 450° for about 10 minutes.

title: honey whole wheat bread
directions: Combine in a large mixing bowl the wheat bread flour, dry milk, salt and yeast. Heat in saucepan over low heat until warm the water, honey and oil. Pour warm liquid over flour mixture. Blend at low speed 1 minute, then medium speed for 2 minutes. By hand, stir in 1 cup wheat flour and 4 to 4 1/2 cups additional all-purpose flour. Knead on a floured surface about 5 minutes. Place dough in greased bowl; cover and let rise 45 to 60 minutes until light and doubled in bulk. Punch down dough; divide in half. Shape each half into loaves. Place into greased 8 x 4-inch pans. Cover loaves. Let rise 30 to 45 minutes until light and doubled. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes until loaves sound hollow when lightly tapped from pan.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Combine and heat.
Serve in chafing dish, using round Fritos to dip.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla, then add flour, soda, salt and sour milk.
Stir in rhubarb.
Mix the last 3 ingredients; sprinkle on top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: tomato-pepper saute
directions: Saute
green peppers and onions in oil over medium heat for 10	minutes.
Add
remaining
ingredients, stirring well. Cover, reduce
heat
and
simmer 15 minutes.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: shrimp with oil and lemon(antipasto)
directions: Put celery, carrot, vinegar and salt in saucepan with 2 to 3 quarts of water.
Bring to rapid boil.
Add the unpeeled shrimp. If small shrimp are used (not over 1/2-inch diameter) they will be cooked shortly after the water returns to a boil.
Medium shrimp cook in 2 to 3 minutes.
When cooked, drain shrimp.
Peel and devein.

Put them in a shallow bowl and add the oil, lemon juice, salt to taste and pepper (optional) while shrimp are still warm. Mix well and steep in the seasonings at room temperature for 1 to 1 1/2 hours before serving.
Serve with crusty French bread or Italian bread.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cauliflower salad(cavolfiore insalata)
directions: Rinse and core
cauliflower.
Cut
into
flowerets; set aside. Bring a medium saucepan
of
water to boil, adding 1/4 teaspoon of the salt.
Boil
cauliflower for 5 minutes; drain. Let cauliflower cool completely
in
colander.
In shaker jar, mix rest of ingredients.
Pour
onto
cooled
cauliflower
and toss gently.
Let marinate 30 minutes.
Serve at room temperature or chilled.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: apple and onion beef pot roast
directions: In a large nonstick skillet coated with nonstick cooking spray, brown roast on all sides. Transfer to a 5-qt. slow cooker. Add water to the skillet, stirring to loosen any browned bits; pour over roast. Sprinkle with seasoned salt, soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce and garlic powder. Top with apple and onion. Cover and cook on low for 5 - 6 hours or until the meat is tender. Remove roast and onion; let stand for 15 minutes before slicing. Strain cooking liquid into a saucepan, discarding apple. Bring liquid to a boil; cook until reduced to 2 cups, about 15 minutes. Combine cornstarch and cold water until smooth; stir in browning sauce. Stir into cooking liquid. Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened. Serve over beef and onion.

title: double chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix cake mix, eggs and oil in bowl. Mix well. Fold in chips and nuts. With teaspoon, measure out 1 teaspoon of cookie dough onto ungreased cookie sheet. Cook 8 to 10 minutes. Yields 24 to 36 cookies.

title: flowerpot soil
directions: Grind cookies in blender or food processor.
Mix cream cheese, oleo and sugar.
Mix pudding with milk and beat.
Add Cool Whip. Add cheese mixture to pudding.
Put one layer of cookies on bottom of pot, then a layer of cheese/pudding.
Alternate layers until all ingredients are used, ending with cookies.
Add artificial flowers and use as centerpiece during dinner, then surprise your guests when it is time for dessert.

title: old fashioned apple pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Add beaten egg, vanilla and sour cream.
Beat until smooth.
Add apples.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with mixture of brown sugar, flour and butter from above.
Bake an additional 20 minutes.

title: spinach salad with black pepper dressing
directions: Whisk ingredients together; set aside.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and salad dressing until well blended.
Add other ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with vegetable dippers.

title: coconut pies
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into pie crust.
Bake at 325° until golden brown.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Combine jello and boiling water.
Mix well.
Stir in pineapple, juice and pie filling.
Pour into a 7 1/2 x 12-inch dish.
Refrigerate until set.
Mix together cream cheese, sugar, sour cream and vanilla.
Spread over strawberry gelatin. Sprinkle with nuts.

title: crab melt-a-ways
directions: Slice muffins in half, then into quarters.
Mix remaining ingredients in bowl with mixer.
Spread on muffin quarters. Arrange on baking sheet and flash freeze.
Store in plastic bags.

title: chili con queso(mexican cheese dip)
directions: Melt margarine in large frying pan.
