Saute onion until soft. Add chili peppers, tomatoes, garlic and coriander.
Serve for 1 hour.
Keep on very low heat and then add cheese cubes and heat until melted.
Serve warm with taco chips.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Crumble crackers and mix with melted margarine, then add poppy seed and mix again.
Put half of crackers in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix soup, sour cream and chicken.
Pour over crackers. Top with remaining crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until top is browned.

title: raisin bars
directions: Boil raisins and water until 3/4 cup liquid remains.
Cream together sugar, eggs and butter.
Add flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and liquid.
Mix together. Stir in raisins.
Pour in jelly roll pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Immediately spread with powdered sugar icing made of:

title: pineapple and coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 2 pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: oriental ham
directions: This is an excellent recipe for left over ham.

title: fudgy chip bars
directions: In medium bowl, combine cookies, flour, coconut and chocolate chips.
Stir in spread, condensed milk and vanilla extract. Spread into 8 or 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned around edge.
Cool; sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Cut into bars.
Yield: 2 dozen.

title: black olive spread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together. Spread on slices of party loaf. Top with bacon.
(May be frozen at this point.
Place on cookie sheet until frozen, then store in plastic bag.)
When ready to serve, place under broiler until cheese melts.

title: goodie balls
directions: Mix all together.
Shape into small balls.
May be rolled in coconut.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil hen until tender; add water to make 2 quarts.
Set aside. Cut onions, celery, pepper and garlic.
Cover and simmer until tender.
Put paste, tomatoes, veggies and 2 cups broth in heavy pan.
Cook slowly for 2 to 3 hours.
Add peas and all other ingredients.
Salt to taste.
Add water to make 2 quarts.
Bring to a boil.
Add spaghetti and cut up chicken.
Mix well.
Bake in covered roaster in medium oven until hot.
Serve with grated cheese.

title: tuna patties
directions: Drain tuna, crumble crackers fine and dice onion.
Mix all ingredients together.
Add small amount of Crisco oil or margarine to pan.
Make patties thin.
Fry slow and until brown, then turn.

title: pumpkin refrigerator dessert
directions: Mix graham crackers with melted butter and sugar.
Press mixture firmly into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: crumb cake
directions: Sift first 5 dry ingredients.
Work in shortening as if making biscuits.
Reserve 2/3 cup of this mixture.
To remaining mixture, add egg, lightly beaten, and combine with milk.
Beat until smooth. Put into shallow pan, greased and dusted with flour.
Add brown sugar and cinnamon to 2/3 cup of dry mixture and spread over cake. Bake in oven at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix jello, sugar and water; heat until it boils. Cool. Beat together cheese and yogurt. Fold in baby food, pineapple and jello. Add pecans. Put in 1-quart mold or 6 x 10 pan. Serves 12 to 14.

title: corn bread
directions: Combine
flour,
salt,	cream
of
tartar, baking soda, sugar and
corn
meal.
Cut
in 3/4 cup shortening.
Add milk slowly; mix
well,	then add well beaten egg.
Bake in an 8 x 8-inch pan at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: corned beef-noodle casserole
directions: Combine ingredients; top with crushed potato chips.
Dot with butter.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 425° oven or until bubbly on top.

title: meat pie
directions: Put 2 tablespoons butter in saucepan with flour; add onions, stirring until light brown.
Add milk and stir until thick.
Add meat, salt and vegetable seasoning.
Cut meat into small chunks; add to white sauce and cook for 10 minutes, stirring constantly. Pour into pie crust and top with small biscuits.
Makes one 10-inch pie.
Makes 8 servings.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together and let set overnight. Next day, drain.
Cook vinegar, mustard, turmeric, celery seed and black pepper.
Add zucchini and cook 15 minutes; jar.

title: country-style ribs
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Cut ribs into serving pieces.
Arrange, with meaty sides up, in ungreased, rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Cover.
Bake about 2 hours or until done.
Drain.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine soups and milk.
Stir.
Tear up cheese; add.
Stir until melted.

title: microwave mexican chicken legs
directions: In this recipe, all cooking is done in the microwave.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients and set aside.
Beat milk and eggs together.
Add dry ingredients and butter to milk and egg mixture and cook slowly until thickened, stirring constantly.
(If not thickened by boiling stage, add more flour.
Mixture should not boil.)
Add vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Cool before refrigerating.
Top with whipped cream.

title: shrimp or crab dip
directions: Saute vegetables in oleo until onion is transparent.
Add crabmeat or shrimp, parsley, onion tops and soup.
Add 1 tablespoon of flour to thicken.

title: blackberry or strawberry pizza
directions: Mix flour, oleo and sugar well and press into pizza pan or 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes; let cool. Mix together Eagle Brand milk, cream cheese and lemon juice and spread on cool crust.
Cook together 1 quart berries with the cornstarch; cook until thick.
Spread on top of cream filling. Frost with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts, if desired.

title: salmon party log
directions: Drain and flake salmon.
Remove skin and bones.
Combine all ingredients except nuts and parsley.
Chill well, rolled in wax paper.
When thoroughly chilled, serve with crackers.

title: macho nacho dip
directions: Melt and blend all ingredients in crock-pot or large pot. Enjoy with tortilla chips, sour cream and peppers.

title: spicy cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Crumble sausage into large skillet.
Add onions.
Cook and drain.
Place sausage in large bowl.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Spread mixture into 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Bake 20 minutes.
Cool 20 minutes on rack before cutting.
Serve warm or cold.
It's also good to serve sour cream with it.
Yummie stuff.

title: apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Add eggs to apples.
Add oil, cinnamon, salt, sugar and raisins and nuts.
Sift together flour and baking soda.
Mix into apple egg mix.
Put into well greased bundt pan.
Bake 45 - 65 minutes depending on your oven.
Carefully turn onto serving plate.

title: maxine's cheese cake
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Mix ingredients and pour into crust. Bake
for
10 minutes and reduce heat to 225° to 250°. Bake
for 20
to 25 minutes longer.
Cheese cake is better if left in refrigerator for a day before cutting.

title: bread pudding
directions: *Substitute a can of Goya coconut milk (16 ounce) plus 16 ounces milk for 4 cups milk.
You can also cut down on sugar, if you use this product.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix soda, salt and flour.
Add to creamed mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Yields 1 large or 3 small loaves.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Heat the milk and add the marshmallows, then stir.
Add the pineapple with juice, nuts and Cool Whip.
Put crushed graham crackers into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Pour mixture over and chill 4 hours.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil margarine, sugar, cocoa and milk for 1 1/2 minutes.
Turn off heat and add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Stir until well blended.
Drop by teaspoons onto wax paper.

title: layered bean dip
directions: Layer bean dip in oblong casserole.
Combine avocado and lemon juice.
Layer on bean dip.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise, salt, pepper and taco seasoning together.
Layer on avocados.
Layer chopped onions on sour cream mixture.
Layer tomatoes on onions. Layer cheese on tomatoes.
Layer black olives on cheese.
Serve with chips.

title: forgey's salsa
directions: Mix all vegetables together in bowl; lightly salt.
Put in garlic powder to taste and vinegar.
Add hot peppers to taste, depending on heat of peppers.
Add cilantro (optional).

title: chicken fajitas with colored peppers
directions: For marinade, in a large mixing bowl, combine cooking oil, vinegar, garlic, jalapeno pepper, oregano, seasoned salt and cumin.
Pour half of the marinade into another bowl.
Add chicken strips to 1 bowl of marinade.
Add pepper strips and onion to the other bowl.
Cover and marinate both bowls at room temperature for up to 30 minutes or in the refrigerator for 2 to 24 hours.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Bake one hour at 325°.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients; pour into a lightly greased casserole.

title: ragu casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Pour off excess fat.
Pour in Ragu sauce and simmer for 5 minutes.
Mix noodles, ground beef and sauce in casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: mary grace's corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in a greased Pyrex dish and bake at 400° for 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.
Pudding will be firm when done.

title: cracked wheat bread
directions: Night before, pour boiling water over cracked wheat.
Soak overnight in large crockery bowl.

title: mushroom scalloped potatoes
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Mix in a 2-quart bowl, all ingredients except potatoes.
After well mixed, stir in potatoes.
Put in a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Top with 1/4 cup grated American cheese.
Bake 1 hour until potatoes are tender.

title: liver dumplings
directions: Mix well; form into balls the size of walnuts.
Drop into a good beef broth.
Boil for 30 minutes.

title: great banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding according to directions (cooked pudding is best).
Use ovensafe bowl or baking dish.
Spread a layer of pudding, then a layer of vanilla wafers and a layer of sliced bananas.
Last layer should be pudding.
Separate egg whites from yolks (use about 3 eggs).
Beat egg whites on high speed of mixer. Add sugar until fluffy.
Spread meringue over pudding.
Bake in oven until meringue is golden brown.
Cool before serving.

title: crab mold
directions: Heat soup, remove from burner.
Add 3 tablespoons cold water to gelatin.
Stir gelatin into soup.
Cool.
Add celery, onion and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Add 1 can crab meat.
Pour into lightly buttered mold.
Chill until serving time.

title: pineapple ambrosia
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 2 tablespoons juice.*
Blend reserved juice with sour cream.
Combine with remaining ingredients; mix well.
Chill.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: date pecan cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar, then sift over dates and pecans.
Melt butter and add with vanilla.
Mix. Beat egg yolks until smooth.
Add to butter and vanilla; mix well. Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in very gently.
Pour into greased and lined tube pan.
Bake at 275° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: rolls
directions: Heat milk, sugar and butter to boiling point.
Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in water.
Add yeast and 2 cups flour to mixture.
Mix well and let rise for 2 hours.
Sift remaining flour with salt, soda and baking powder and add to mixture.
Make into rolls and let rise before baking.
Brush rolls with melted butter before rising.
Bake at 425°.
Makes 3 dozen rolls.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, cream of tartar, soda, nutmeg and salt.

With an electric mixer set at medium-low speed, cream the butter and 3/4 cup sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in the egg and vanilla. Reduce speed to low and beat flour mixture into butter and sugar until well blended. Combine cinnamon and remaining 1/3 cup sugar.
Roll into 1-inch balls, then roll in cinnamon-sugar.
Place on ungreased baking sheet about 2-inches apart.
Bake until lightly brown, about 10 minutes.

title: carrots
directions: Boil carrots in salted water until tender.
Drain.
Combine other ingredients and heat but do not boil.
Pour over carrots in a covered casserole.
Store in refrigerator overnight before serving.
Will keep for several days.

title: chicken or veal parmesan
directions: Pound meat until it is very thin.
Beat eggs.
Mix breadcrumbs with Parmesan cheese.
Dip meat into egg, then into breadcrumb mixture.
Heat oil; brown meat in frypan.
Put some sauce in a casserole dish; arrange meat on it.
Arrange sliced Mozzarella on meat and cover with sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake chicken/veal 3/4 hour at 350°, covered; uncover last 15 minutes.

title: foolproof fudge
directions: Butter sides of heavy 3-quart saucepan.
Add sugar, evaporated milk and butter.
Cook over medium heat to soft ball stage (236°), stirring frequently.
Remove from heat; add chocolate pieces, Marshmallow Creme, vanilla and broken walnuts.
Beat until chocolate melts.
Pour into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Score while warm; cut when cool and firm.

title: pear amber marmalade
directions: Wash and remove peel from oranges.
Add 1 quart of water to peel and boil 5 minutes.
Drain; discard water.
Add another quart of water to peel and boil again for 5 minutes.
Drain and grind peel and peeled oranges together.

title: butterscotch nut fudge
directions: In saucepan,
cook brown sugar, sugar, marshmallow, oleo and evaporated milk to a full, all over boil (5 minutes).
Take off heat.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Stir until candy is thick and creamy.
Pour in buttered 8-inch square pan.
Makes 1 3/4 pounds of fudge.

title: aunt mona's buttermilk pie
directions: Cream together sugar, butter and flour. Add eggs, buttermilk, vanilla and coconut. Pour half of mixture into each unbaked pie crust. Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: strawberry sour cream salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Add strawberries, stirring until separated and thawed.
Pour 1/2 mixture into mold; chill until set.
Mix sour cream and pecans; spread over strawberry layer.
Add remaining strawberry mixture; chill until firm.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cedric's casserole
directions: Saute onion in 3 tablespoons butter or margarine.
Add beef, salt and pepper to onion and brown lightly.
Spread 3 cups of cabbage in a casserole dish.
Spread the beef mixture over the cabbage, then add remaining 3 cups of cabbage.
Pour over the mixture the can of tomato soup.
Do not dilute soup.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hot apple juice
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium saucepan.
Simmer over low heat for about 5 minutes, then strain and serve hot.
Makes 4 servings.

title: coconut pie
directions: Cream the sugar and margarine.
Stir in buttermilk and eggs. Add coconut and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 300° for 50 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Melt margarine over low heat.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Brush over meat as it broils or grills.

title: old fashioned strawberry cake
directions: Use any good 2-cup flour biscuit recipe, adding to it 1 tablespoon	sugar
and
an	extra tablespoon shortening.
Roll dough thin.
Cut
large
biscuits
and
bake
in a quick oven. When brown	and still very hot, put a square of butter in each and add sweetened strawberries and whipped cream.

title: shrimp chips
directions: Bring water to a boil and dissolve salt and pepper powder. Pour boiling water onto the tapioca flour in a large mixing bowl and stir quickly with a cooking spoon.
Add in the shrimp and knead as a dough.
As the water content of the shrimp is unpredictable, you may adjust it by adding more boiling water.
The dough should be on the hard side.
Now shape into a cylinder about 1-inch in diameter.
If you do not have the proper steamer for this process, a bamboo rack or cake cooling rack will do.
Lay a cheesecloth underneath and on top of the dough and place it on the rack.
Make sure the cylinders of dough are far enough apart (at least 1 1/2-inches if space permits) to prevent them from sticking together.
Steam at a high temperature for 45 minutes.
Make sure there is plenty of water in the steamer to avoid having to open it to add more water.

title: pink delight
directions: Drain pineapple. Mix dry Jello into cottage cheese, add fruit and then topping.
Chill until serving.

title: whirligig cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars and peanut butter; add egg.
Beat until fluffy.
Mix dry ingredients into mixture well.
Roll dough into oblong shape 1/4-inch thick.
Melt chocolate bits over hot water.
Cool chocolate slightly.
Spread on dough with a spatula. Roll up like jelly roll and chill.
Slice 1/4-inch thick.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for 12 minutes. Yield:
3 dozen cookies.

title: bread pudding
directions: In a large mixing bowl, break bread into small pieces.
Add raisins, sugar, milk and cinnamon.
Mix well until texture becomes a batter.
(Can add more milk if necessary.)
Add vanilla flavoring.
Melt 1 stick margarine in a large square pan.
Pour margarine into mixture.
Mix well.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake at 375° for about 1 1/2 hours or until bread pudding is a golden brown.
Serve.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cranberry apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine apples and cranberry sauce in a medium mixing bowl.
Combine brown sugar, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg in a separate mixing bowl.
Add to apple mixture, mixing well.

title: smoked oyster dip (double)
directions: Combine sour cream and mayonnaise. Blend in olives and oysters. Chill and serve with crackers.

title: chili pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in a large skillet.
Turn burner on high. When pork chops start to fry, turn heat down on low and saute until brown on both sides.

title: london broil
directions: Score meat by making shallow cuts across the meat in a diamond pattern on both sides.
Marinate meat in oil, vinegar, garlic, 1/4 tsp. salt, and 1/4 tsp. pepper for 1 hour.

title: brownies
directions: Sift flour; melt shortening and chocolate.
Add sugar to eggs, then to the chocolate mixture and blend.
Add flour and mix, then mix nuts and vanilla and spread into greased pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry conserve
directions: Place cranberries in large pan with water. Bring to a boil and simmer 5 minutes until berries pop. Add remaining ingredients, except nuts. Cook about 30 minutes or until thick. Stir occasionally. Remove from heat. Add nuts.
Pour into hot sterilized jars. Makes 3 pints.

title: penne with artichokes
directions: Cut off stems, tough outer leaves and pointed tops of artichokes and snip off the tips of the outside leaves.
Cut artichokes into quarters; remove chokes and place in bowl with lemon juice.
Cover with water and leave to soak for 10 minutes. Peel and crush garlic.
Heat the oil in saucepan.
Drain artichokes and add to pan with garlic.
Cook gently over low heat for about 10 minutes, until tender, turning them several times. Add parsley and cook for a further 4 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: jello cake
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: banana split pie
directions: Put pie filling into crust.
Top with bananas, then pudding. Top with Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: scottish shortbread
directions: Using your hands, cream butter and sugar until soft.
Add remaining ingredients; continue using your hands.
This is the secret to good shortbread.
Pour mixture onto a jelly roll pan that has been lined with foil paper.
Stick holes into batter with a fork.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.
Remove from oven and cut in squares while hot.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10-inch pie plate.
Brown beef and onions.
Drain and stir in seasoning mix.
Spread in pie plate and sprinkle with chiles.
Beat milk, baking mix and eggs until smooth (1 minute with hand mixer).
Pour on top of other mixture.
Bake 25 minutes and top with chopped tomatoes and cheese.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes longer.
Remove and let cool for 10 minutes.
Top with extra cheese, tomatoes and lettuce, either in layers or in a circle.
Serve with sour cream.

title: peach preserve cake
directions: Place oil in mixer bowl.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy. Add eggs one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add alternately with buttermilk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Fold in peach preserves and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: plum wine chicken
directions: Heat oil in 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chicken breasts and saute about 2 minutes each side.
Remove from skillet and set aside on warm plate.
Reduce heat to medium.
Add ginger root and garlic to skillet and cook, stirring constantly, for 1 minute or until garlic is just tender.
Add the green onion and continue cooking and stirring about 30 seconds.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook the tops of broccoli well.
Chop up fine.
Add together all other ingredients.
Heat in saucepan.
Add broccoli.
Serve in soup bowl with crackers.
Serves four.

title: sauerkraut salad(servings:  4)
directions: Cut sauerkraut into short strands; mix in remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: irish bread
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening. Add dry ingredients and raisins.
Add milk. Have milk at room temperature.
Spoon into a long loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: country crowder peas
directions: Add crowder peas, sugar, onions, bacon, and Tony's seasoning to pot.
Boil in water until done.

title: mesa dip
directions: Brown your ground beef and season with taco seasoning.
Drain off the excess grease.
Pour your ground beef into a crock-pot. Add your refried beans, Pace picante sauce and Velveeta cheese and let it simmer for at least 1 hour.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: dutch apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brush bottom and side of crust evenly with egg yolk.
Bake on baking sheet until light brown, about 5 minutes.
Remove crust from oven.
Reduce oven heat to 350°.

title: venison sausage balls
directions: Combine first 11 ingredients, mixing well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Brown well in oleo, stirring occasionally.
Cover and cook over low heat 15 minutes.
Arrange on serving platter, garnish with fruit and parsley if desired.
Yields about 5 dozen.

title: calla lilly crunch cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in order.
Roll in walnut size balls.
Roll balls in sugar.
Smash with sugared fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until browned.

title: salsa dip
directions: Cook together the hamburger and sausage; drain and set aside. In crock-pot, melt cheeses, stirring to keep from sticking.
Add hamburger, sausage, salsa and picante sauce.
Let simmer until ready to serve.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: eggplant parmesan snack
directions: Cut eggplant
into cubes and steam until tender.
Slice onion and saute
in
oil	until
tender, but not brown.
Place eggplant, onion
and	rest
of
ingredients in blender;
pulse briefly to partially
puree mixture (should be consistency of peanut butter). Spread
on
crackers,
rice cakes, pita, etc. Store in a tightly covered container in refrigerator for up to 10 days.
Makes 2 cups.

title: blueberry surprise
directions: Spread pineapple in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Add 1/2 cup sugar.
Spread blueberries on top of this.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup of sugar on top of berries.
Add cake mix on top of this.
Chip margarine on top of cake mix.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown and crumbly.

title: hot sausage ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into small balls.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° until lightly browned.
These may be frozen before baking or afterward, then reheated.

title: diane's banana nut bread
directions: Blend first five ingredients.
Add rest, stirring only enough to moisten dry ingredients.
Put in greased, bottom only, loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: zucchini marmalade
directions: Combine zucchini, lemon rind, pineapple and lemon juice in a large pan.
Cook to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer uncovered 25 minutes or until tender and holds shape.
Add Sure-Jell and cook over high heat to boiling.
Stir in sugar and ginger and continue cooking according to directions on Sure-Jell package.
Remove from stove and stir for 5 minutes, removing foam.
Fill sterilized containers and seal.
Makes enough for 6 half-pint containers.

title: rhubarb strawberry jam
directions: Mix rhubarb, pineapple and sugar together and let stand for 10 minutes. Mix and start cooking, bringing to a boil. Boil 10 minutes, stirring all the time. Remove from heat; add the Jell-O, mixing well. Seal in glass jars. Makes 3 1/2 pints.

title: southwestern oven-fried chicken
directions: Place bread, cilantro, cornmeal, pine nuts, cayenne, garlic, cumin, oregano, 1/4 teaspoon salt and cloves in food processor. Process to fine crumbs.
Add egg white; mix until moist.
Place mixture in large shallow plate; set aside.
In small bowl, mix together mustard, water and honey; brush evenly over chicken. Sprinkle chicken with pepper and remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Dip chicken, one piece at a time, in bread crumbs and press gently to adhere to a thin coating.
Place chicken on rack in greased jellyroll pan.
Bake in 400° oven for about 50 minutes or until chicken is crisp and brown and a fork can be inserted with ease.

title: caramel coconut frosting
directions: Cook sugar and milk together until soft ball forms. Add butter and vanilla.
Cool.
Beat until spreading consistency.

title: pineapple nut salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; blend in cream cheese and then add the other ingredients and congeal.

title: unbaked cookies
directions: Heat slowly to boiling point the margarine, sugar, salt, cocoa and milk.
Boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add the oats, nuts, coconut and chocolate chips.
Mix.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper and let set up and cool.

title: peach cooler
directions: Put all ingredients except ice cream, into blender.
Cover and process at liquify (Ice crush)
until smooth.
Add ice cream, cover and blend for 1 cycle.
Makes 2 servings.

title: penuche frosting
directions: Place over low heat, bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Boil hard 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Beat until lukewarm.
Add vanilla.
Beat until can spread.
(Add cream if needed.)

title: apple fritters
directions: Sift
together
flour,
sugar,
baking powder and salt. Beat eggs until light.
Add milk and apples with dry ingredients.
Fry in hot fat.

title: lemony cucumbers
directions: Score cucumbers with a fork and thinly slice.
Combine vinegar and remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Pour over cucumbers. Cover and chill 4 hours.
Yields 6 servings.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Place butter and oil in frying pan until melted. Add garlic. Saut for 5 to 8 minutes, being careful not to burn garlic. Add fresh spinach and wilt down. Add cheese. Cut chops to bone, making a pocket. Put spinach mixture in each chop. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: clara's cheese balls
directions: Have all at room temperature.
Cream in mixer.
Cover and chill for 3 hours until firm enough to shape.
Divide into 2 balls.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Wrap in plastic and foil.
Place in plastic bag.
Freezes well.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix well. Pour
in
3 (9-inch) cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Ice with Coconut Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve the Jell-O in water.
Add immediately the frozen strawberries, pineapple and bananas.
Stir well and pour half of the mixture into the Jel-N-Serve.
Place into refrigerator to congeal.
Leave other half on countertop.
When mold is congealed, put a layer of sour cream over the salad and spread gently.
Then very gently dip the rest of the Jell-O mixture over the sour cream and return to the refrigerator.
May be made a day ahead.
Keeps well, if sealed.
Serves 12.

title: *sweetheart salad
directions: Put crushed pineapple and sugar in pan.
Heat until the sugar melts.
Add dissolved gelatine and cherry juice.
Cook over low heat until blended.
Add lemon juice.
Mix cream cheese and cherries; mix thoroughly with pineapple mixture.
When mixture begins to set, fold in whipped cream.

title: partridges smothered in cabbage
directions: In casserole, fry bacon until some fat is accumulated; then add the ham and cook until both begin to brown.
Add diced onion and carrots; cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Then add the herbs, salt and pepper.

title: hot beef dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Heat in microwave until melted and mixed well.
Serve with party crackers.

title: cheese cake pie
directions: Blend softened cream cheese until smooth.
Add other ingredients and blend until smooth.
Pour into crust and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, milk, and salt in heavy 3 quart saucepan.
Bring to a full rolling boil over high heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, stir in peanut butter until melted. Add marshmallow creme and vanilla.
Beat until smooth and well blended.
Fold in candies, immediately spread into greased 13 x 9 inch baking pan.
Cool at room temperature.
Cut into squares. Yield: 3 lb.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Butter the bottom of a 9 x 12-inch casserole dish; sprinkle chopped chicken in dish.
Add Veg-All.
In separate bowl, mix until smooth the cream of chicken, mushroom and celery soups and the cup of milk.
Pour mixture over the chicken and Veg-All.
Crush the Ritz crackers; sprinkle over the other ingredients.
Dot with pats of butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: portuguese bean soup
directions: Combine all ingredients, in a large covered kettle, except macaroni, cabbage and beans.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to hard simmer.
When meat is tender and done, add cabbage, macaroni and beans (undrained).
A bay leaf can be added, but is optional. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: tomato cheese ball
directions: Form into a ball and roll in nuts.
Wrap in plastic and refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: fig preserves with strawberries
directions: Cook 3 to 5 minutes.

title: creole okra
directions: Prepare okra and tomatoes.
Saute onion and green pepper in oil until browned.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook covered over medium heat for 30 minutes uncovered for 5 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
May be served over 6 cups of cooked rice.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add sauce and cook 15 minutes. Place in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Cover with cheese.

title: spicy potato soup(easy and delicious)
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add onion, tomato sauce, water, salt, pepper and hot sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and let simmer 30 minutes.
Add potatoes and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and let simmer an additional 30 minutes.
Serve with a loaf of fresh bread.

title: wilted "killed" lettuce and onions
directions: Wash lettuce and pat dry with paper towels.
Combine lettuce and onions in a large bowl.
Set aside.
In a saucepan over high heat, combine oil, vinegar, water and sugar.
Bring vinegar mixture to a boil (do not boil in microwave) and pour over the lettuce and onions, stirring and turning the lettuce so most of the lettuce comes in contact with the hot mixture.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add bacon, if desired.

title: cracker candy
directions: Place foil on cookie sheet.
Lay graham crackers on foil.
Cook butter and sugar on top of stove for 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers.
Bake in oven at 300° for 15 minutes.
Pour morsels and nuts on crackers and spread.
Put in refrigerator until cold, then break.

title: banana pudding
directions: Bring 1 1/2 cups milk to boil in saucepan.
While milk warms, mix remaining ingredients, except egg whites, in 1/2 cup milk, using 2 tablespoons to 3/4 cup sugar, depending on desired sweetness.
Add well mixed ingredients into saucepan when milk boils.
Stir until thickened.
Layer vanilla wafers in bottom of ovenproof dish.
Place one layer of sliced bananas on top of wafers.
Continue to layer until dish is about 3/4 full, ending with wafers on top.
Pour pudding over layers.
Beat egg whites with 2 tablespoons sugar until very stiff.
Top pudding mixture with egg whites.
Bake at 350° until brown on top (5 to 10 minutes).

title: crockpot dressing
directions: Melt butter in skillet and saute onion, celery, parsley and mushrooms. Pour over bread cubes in a large bowl. Add all seasonings and toss. Pour in enough broth to moisten. Add eggs and mix. Pack into a crockpot. Cover and set on high for 45 minutes. Turn to low and cook 4 to 8 hours.

title: cheesecake cupcakes
directions: Line 24 muffin tins with paper liners.
Place one wafer in the bottom of each.
Blend sugar, cream cheese, lemon juice, eggs and vanilla in bowl.
Spoon enough mixture in each tin to fill half full.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Top with pie filling.

title: stroganoff beef burgers
directions: Cook the bacon until crisp; drain on a paper towel.
Cook onion in bacon grease; drain in a colander.
Cook the ground beef until done; add the bacon and onion.
Blend the flour and seasonings into the mixture; stir in the soup.
Cook slowly, uncovered, for 20 minutes, stirring frequently.
Stir in the sour cream and heat through.
Serve, open-faced, on the toasted buns. Feeds four teenage boys or a family of six.

title: country apple pie
directions: Arrange apples in pie shell.
Mix next 5 ingredients together and pour over apples.
Mix together remaining ingredients and sprinkle all over the pie.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.

title: sally lunn bread
directions: Combine yeast and 1/2 c. warm water in 1-cup measuring cup; let stand 5 minutes.

Heat milk, sugar, butter, salt in a saucepan over medium heat, stirring until butter melts. Cool to 100-110°. Beat yeast mixture, milk mixture, and eggs at medium speed with a electric mixer until blended.
Gradually add flour, beating a lowest speed until blended.
(Mixture will be a very sticky, soft dough.)
Cover and let rise in a warm place (85°), free of drafts, 1 hour or until dough is doubled in bulk.
Stir dough down; cover and let rise in a warm place (85°), free from drafts, 30 minutes or until dough is doubled in bulk.
Stir dough down, spoon into well-greased, 10-inch Bundt pan or tube pan.
Cover and let rise in a warm place (85°), free from drafts, 20-30 minutes or until dough is doubled in bulk.
Bake at 350° for 35-40 minutes or until golden brown and a wooden pick inserted into center of bread comes out clean.
Remove from pan immediately.
Serve bread with Blackberry butter, honey, molasses, or jelly, if desired.

title: baked corn
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add soup and mix until smooth.
Stir in milk.
Add remaining ingredients except oleo.
Pour into a well-buttered baking dish.
Dot with remaining oleo.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: helen's spanish rice
directions: Wash rice, drain and allow to dry thoroughly.

title: rich chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven 350 degrees. Mix sugar into oleo and chocolate, add vanilla and eggs, mix well. Add dry ingredients mix well. add nuts and bake about 25 minutes. Cool 5 minutes before cutting. Do not over bake.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Combine egg and buttermilk, set aside.
Combine 1/4 c flour, cornmeal, 1 tsp salt and 1/2 tsp black pepper in a shallow bowl or pan.
Dredge tomato slices in remaining 1/4 c flour, dip in egg mixture, then dredge in corn meal mixture.

title: cool whip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and drop by teaspoon onto a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 13 minutes.
Sift powdered sugar on baked cookies if desired.

title: sunshine cake
directions: Beat 4 egg yolks and 3 tablespoons cold water together.
Add the sugar gradually; beat well.
Add 1/2 cup boiling water; beat until foamy.
Sift 3 times the cake flour, baking powder and salt; add this to egg yolks.
Beat well.
Add the almond extract and vanilla.
Beat egg whites with the cream of tartar until stiff; fold into mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Add your desired frosting.

title: sweet and sour shrimp
directions: In a large skillet, combine pineapple juice, water, ReaLemon, sugar, cornstarch, soy sauce and ginger.
Cook over medium-low heat until thickened.
Add shrimp and cook until pink.
Add remaining ingredients except rice.
Heat through.
Serve on rice. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: twinkie dessert
directions: Lay Twinkies cut side up in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat softened cream cheese with milk and instant pudding.
Pour over Twinkies. Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: date and nut cake
directions: Add dates to flour mixture; blend.
Bake in loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Freezes well.

title: no fat banana cake
directions: Combine bananas, applesauce and egg whites.
Mix well with mixer until blended.
Add remaining ingredients except 2 teaspoons sugar and cinnamon.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan coated with no fat cooking spray.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon and sugar mixed. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease big 10 or 12-inch ovenproof skillet.
Sprinkle lightly with cornmeal and brown slightly. Combine in bowl the cornmeal, soda, salt, milk, eggs, corn and bacon drippings.
Pour half of batter in skillet; spread evenly. Add rest of ingredients as listed, one at a time.
Add remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: country corn bread
directions: Mix ingredients together in bowl.
Pour in Pam greased 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until browned to your liking.

title: tomato cheese crusts(appetizer)
directions: Saute onion in butter until soft and pale gold.
Add tomatoes that have been peeled, seeded and diced with a little salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat until tomatoes are thick and no liquid remains.
Cool the mixture completely and stir in egg yolk, Parmesan cheese and Worcestershire sauce.
Spread the mixture on slices of toast (Italian bread) and place them in a hot oven (400°) until the topping is lightly browned.
Serve the "Crestini" very hot.
Very easy to make and delicious!

title: green jacket house salad
directions: Layer 1/3 of lettuce on bottom of salad bowl.
Put onion slices and then dot 3 tablespoons of mayonnaise.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon sugar over that plus salt and pepper.
Then add any additional salad fixing you may want such as celery, green pepper, carrots, peas and Swiss cheese.
Repeat layers 3 times.
Top with bacon bits and refrigerate 1 to 3 hours.
When ready to serve, add croutons and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Toss and enjoy!

title: rum-glazed pineapple angel food cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Combine cake mix and pineapple in a large bowl; beat with a mixer at medium speed until blended. Pour batter into an ungreased 13x9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Combine powdered sugar, milk, and rum flavoring in a small bowl; stir well.
Spread glaze over warm cake.
Let cake cool completely.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook chicken; remove skin and bones.
Cook spaghetti in broth.
Brown bacon; add onion, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook until tender.
Combine all, plus cheese and pimientos.
Season to taste and add broth to moisten well.
Top with more grated cheese.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
(Makes a 3-quart casserole.)

title: ambrosia
directions: Pour out juice from pineapple and oranges.
Mix fruit, coconut, marshmallows and sour cream.
Put into a dish; refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: caramel sauce
directions: Combine sugar and water in medium heavy saucepan.
Place over medium-low heat and cook 13 minutes or until sugar dissolves.
(Do not stir.)
Cover, increase heat to medium and boil 1 minute. (This will dissolve any sugar crystals clinging to sides of pan.) Uncover and boil an additional 10 minutes or until amber or golden. (Do not stir.)
Remove from heat; let stand 1 minute.
Carefully add margarine, stirring until margarine melts.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly.
(Caramel will harden and stick to spoon.) Place pan over medium heat and cook 3 minutes or until caramel melts and mixture is smooth, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla and salt.
Pour caramel into a bowl, cover and chill.
Yields 1 1/4 cups (serving size 1 tablespoon).

title: tiny tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and blend in flour and salt; add vanilla and stir well.
Drop 1/2 teaspoon into greased tin. Bake at 375° until done (light brown around edge).
Decorate with nuts, cherries or colored sugar.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Then sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake for 10 minutes longer.

title: easy microwave peanut butter fudge
directions: Microwave frosting and peanut butter on High for 4 minutes. Mixture will be very runny.
Mix together ingredients. Pour into greased pan and let cool.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat strips about 1-inch long.
Melt butter.
Add mushrooms and onion; cook until tender.
Remove, then cook meat until light brown.
Reserving 1/3 cup of the broth, stir into remaining broth, catsup, garlic and salt.
Cover; simmer for 15 minutes.
Blend reserved broth and flour; stir into meat mixture. Add mushrooms and onion; boil and stir about 1 minute.
Reduce heat.
Stir in sour cream; heat.
Serve over noodles.

title: walleye parmesan
directions: Mix Parmesan cheese, garlic powder and paprika.
Place butter in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Lay fillets in the pan and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake at 425° for about 6 minutes, then carefully turn fillets.
Dribble lemon juice over fillets, then sprinkle Parmesan mixture on top.
Return to oven and bake until thickest part of the fish flakes easily with fork.

title: mom's best-ever macaroni and cheese
directions: Bring 3 quarts water to a boil in a large kettle; add 1 tablespoon salt and the macaroni.
Boil until tender.
Drain macaroni and rinse with hot water.
Put in a buttered casserole (about 2-quart size).
Start at 400°.

title: dad's dish
directions: Boil macaroni until done and set aside with margarine, tossed in drained macaroni.
Cook hamburger until crumbly, along with onion, bell pepper and garlic.
Drain grease.
Pour in tomatoes and macaroni.
Optional:
You may add chili powder.
Serves 7.

title: oatmeal brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter and set aside.
Combine dry ingredients.
Stir in eggs, vanilla and chocolate mixture.
Add nuts and oatmeal.
Bake in 8 x 8 x 2-inch greased pan at 375° about 20 minutes.

title: fruit salad supreme
directions: Drain off
juices
from
fruit	and mix all ingredients well with a spoon. Chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Mix together apples, sugar and cinnamon (set aside).
Combine other ingredients and mix well.
Pour 1/2 of batter into 10-inch tube or Bundt pan, greased and floured.
Put apple mixture on top of batter.
Cover with remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: apple-angel food cake
directions: Prepare cake according to package directions.
Bake in jelly roll pan for 30 to 35 minutes. Invert to cool.
When cake is cooled, preheat oven to 400°.
Cut each apple in half and slice thinly. Bake slices 10 minutes; cool 5 minutes.
Place apples on cooled cake.
Heat jelly and cinnamon in saucepan and spread over apples on cake.
Serves 20. Contains 105 calories.

title: fresh apple cake and glaze
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Bake in oblong pan at 300° for 1 hour.
Cool and then glaze.

title: cherry sparkler
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Add ginger ale or cola slowly.
Pour into parfait glasses. Chill until firm.
If desired, garnish with whipped cream and mint sprigs.

title: baked mixed vegetables
directions: Cook enough yellow squash and onion to yield about 3 cups cooked (5-6 smallish squash and 1 large onion).

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Beat eggs, bananas and 1/2 cup flour, then add the remaining flour, soda and nuts.
Put in 2 small loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix all but last ingredient together.
Pour salad dressing over mixture.
Toss and refrigerate overnight.
Stir before serving.
Makes about 20 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: b. l. t. dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with bread sticks or crackers.

title: curry shrimp creole
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Cook the onion, pepper, celery and garlic.
Add undrained tomatoes, almonds, raisins, chili sauce, lemon juice, salt, hot pepper sauce, curry powder and thyme. Bring to a boil, reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes. Add shrimp, cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Serve over rice. Serves 4.

title: sausage and rice bake
directions: Fry sausage until well browned and drain off excess fat. Break up sausage with a wooden spoon as it fries so that it is crisp to pick up savory drippings.
Stir in chicken noodle soup. Bring to a boil again and remove from heat.
Add celery, pimento, onion, chopped green pepper and rice.
Turn into a 9 x 13-inch greased baking pan; sprinkle with cheese over top.
Bake, uncovered, in a slow oven (300°) for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: shrimp with fresh tomato basil over pasta
directions: Heat olive oil and garlic; add chopped tomatoes and juice, salt and pepper to taste.
Add fresh basil.
Peel and devein shrimp.
Add to tomato sauce.
Cook until done, about 3 minutes. Pour over pasta.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cheese spread for rolls
directions: Mix together all the ingredients.
Spread on bun; place under broiler.
Makes about 3 to 4 dozen whole buns, cut in half. Sourdough rolls or hot dog buns can be used.
Mix. Will keep in refrigerator for several weeks.

title: good luck black-eyed peas
directions: Fry bacon until slightly brown; add onions.
Saute for about 15 minutes or until glazed; add bell pepper.
Cook for 10 minutes. Pour in peas.
Simmer for about 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in 2-quart buttered dish. Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: easy garlic shrimp
directions: Shell and devein shrimp, leaving tails intact.
Combine rest of ingredients and marinate shrimp in mixture for at least 1/2 hour.
Bake at 450° for 5 to 7 minutes or until shrimps are pink. Serve as main dish or as appetizer with wooden picks.
Serves about 35.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Cook noodles; drain and set aside.
Brown ground beef and drain off grease.
Saute onion, garlic and mushrooms.
Add beef and cook for a few minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in flour, tomato sauce, bouillon and a dash of salt and pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes; remove from heat.
Stir in sour cream.
Add noodles; pour into greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake, uncovered, at 375° for 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: fruit cookies
directions: Cream butter or oleo and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add nuts and fruit.
Sift remaining ingredients and flour together and add to first mixture. Mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoons 1-inch apart on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for about 12 to 15 minutes. Makes about 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: hot wings
directions: Fry chicken wings until done.
In a saucepan, melt butter. Pour in hot sauce and other ingredients and simmer for about 7 minutes.
Mix wings and hot sauce.
Allow wings to soak in hot sauce as long as desired.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Put butter in shallow baking pan and melt.
Crush stuffing mix with rolling pin.
Add salt to crumbs. Beat eggs with water in pie plate.
Dip chicken in egg mixture, then shake a few pieces at a time in stuffing mix until coated. Place skin side down in melted butter in single layer.
Bake uncovered in a 425° oven for 30 minutes.
Turn and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: greek bread
directions: Heat all ingredients (except bread) in a pot until melted. Cut French bread in half lengthwise and spread mixture on each half.
Bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: zucchini puff
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in greased 9 x 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Mix crumbs in milk and add to butter and sugar mixture.
Beat well until smooth. Fold in coconut, pineapple and nuts.
Bake at 350° until done.
May frost if desired with cream cheese frosting or eat plain.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt margarine and milk.
Pour over bread crumbs.
Mix with squash, stir in eggs.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Cover with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bake crust and cool.
Mix 1 cup sugar and cornstarch.
Add water; cook until clear.
Remove from stove.
Add Jell-O.
Put fresh strawberries in crust.
Pour filling over berries.
Chill and top with Cool Whip.

title: snack oyster crackers
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over the package of oyster crackers. Put in Tupperware and seal.
Put in refrigerator.
Turn often for 1 week.
Keep refrigerated.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add 1 cup of water and brown gravy mix. Place mixed vegetables in a large baking dish and add beef mixture.
Place biscuits on top of mixture and bake at 325° until biscuits are done.

title: butterhorns
directions: Cream butter and margarine with cottage cheese.
Add flour and salt and mix well.
Refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.
Divide dough into 3 parts.
Roll each part into a circle on a floured board. Cut each circle into 12 triangles.
Roll dough by starting with wide end and rolling to a point.
Bake at 350 degrees on a greased cookie sheet for 25-30 minutes.
(Keep other dough refrigerated until ready to roll out.)

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: In an oblong pan, place all ingredients except chocolate chips.
Mix together and then add chips.
Stir in chips.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes or until top springs back.
Cool and serve topped with ice cream or whipped cream.
Store in fridge, covered.

title: pheasant salad
directions: To serve warm, heat the pheasant, rice and soup.
Can be served cold, also.
Mix all ingredients and enjoy!

title: apple cranberry casserole
directions: Mix apples, cranberries and white sugar.
Put in casserole dish.
Cut up margarine and brown sugar.
Add oats and nuts. Place on top of apple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shortbread cookies
directions: Resift flour and baking powder; cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Slowly add flour.
Stir in nuts.
Cover and chill.
Roll out on floured board to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut in any shape you want.
Place on ungreased sheet.
Bake 20 minutes at 300° or until edges are very lightly browned.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: seven-up salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin with hot water and 7-Up.
Drain pineapple, reserving 1 cup juice.
Add marshmallows, pineapple and bananas to gelatin; chill.

title: stewed tomatoes
directions: Peel the tomatoes. Cut in small pieces and mash. Add onion, celery and green pepper. Simmer 10 minutes, covered.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Cover and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.

title: date nut bars
directions: Mix and sift together first 4 ingredients.
Make a well and add in order, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Beat with wooden spoon or mixer. Last, chop nuts and dates, then add to mixture.
Pour into a greased pan (9 x 9-inch) and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar; cut into squares.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cream together vanilla, sugar, butter and milk.
Bring to boil, then add peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Let stand at room temperature.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Refrigerate at least one hour before serving.
Garnish with additional parsley.

title: fixed ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes and when done drain them, mash the potatoes add 2 tbs. of butter and the next 5 ingredients. Pour in a baking dish. Brush top with melted butter. Bake 20 minutes.

title: 1-2-3-4 icebox cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients, except dates, to make a dough.
Cut dates in small pieces and cook in 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup water until thick; cool.
Roll out dough and spread with date filling; roll jelly roll style and freeze.
When frozen, cut in 1/8-inch slices and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Watch closely, they burn easily.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, combine Crisco and sugars.
Mix until creamy. Blend in egg, soda, vanilla and salt.
Add flour gradually, stirring well.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes at 375°.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add a little milk if too thick.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: meringue cookies
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Beat egg whites until frothy.
Gradually add sugar and vanilla.
Beat for 5 minutes or until stiff peaks form.
Fold in nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Put in oven immediately and turn off heat.
Leave for 2 hours. Enjoy.

title: penne with peppers and bacon
directions: Slice peppers into thin squares.
Saute onion, vegetable oil and 3 tablespoons butter in a skillet.
When the onion is translucent, add the bacon.
Brown the bacon, but not until it is crispy.
Add the peppers and cook, stirring frequently for 6 to 8 minutes, until the peppers are tender but not mushy.
Add salt and liberal pepper; turn off the heat.
Drop the pasta into a pot of boiling salted water.
Drain and toss with the sauce.
Add the grated cheese and toss with the remaining tablespoon of butter. Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve promptly.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: jello popsicles
directions: In a deep bowl, mix together Jell-O, Kool-Aid and sugar.
Add hot water and stir well until dissolved.
Add cold water and stir. Pour into popsicle tubs and freeze.

title: apple walnut supreme cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Combine apples and sugar- set aside.
In a large mixing bowl combine eggs and vanilla - beat 1 minute.
At medium speed, add combined dry ingredients.
Fold in apple mixture.
Bake in a greased 13 x 9 x 2 pan at 350 degrees for 45-50 minutes, until cake tests done with a toothpick.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix
yeast with 2 tablespoons warm water.
Add sugar to flour and cut in shortening. Stir in buttermilk. Add yeast and blend. Store in refrigerator until ready to use.
(Does better if chilled at least 30 minutes.)

title: hot water gingerbread
directions: Cream
shortening and sugar.
Add beaten egg, molasses, then dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Add hot water last and beat until smooth.
Bake in greased shallow pan for
35 minutes in moderate oven (325° to 350°).
Serve warm. Gingerbread will be very light and fluffy.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all of the ingredients in a medium-size bowl and toss with your favorite salad dressing. Serves 4 to 6.

title: creamy cool salad
directions: Drain pineapple; save the syrup.
Take syrup, marshmallows and crumbled cheese; put in a saucepan.
Cook over low heat until smooth, then add drained fruit and nuts.
Mix and chill.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Coarsely chop vegetables (run through meat grinder or blender).
Drain.
Beat eggs. Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased 8 x 11-inch pan. Bake 1 hour.
Can top with grated cheese the last 10 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together except the first 3.
Mix the first 3 ingredients together to form dough and pour over other ingredients.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: cocoa, raisin and walnut muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine butter and sugar in a mixing bowl.
Beat with an electric mixer until mixture is light and fluffy.
Add egg and mix thoroughly.
Combine next 6 ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Remove 3/4 teaspoon flour mixture and toss with raisins and walnuts in another bowl.
Add 1/3 flour mixture to egg mixture and mix thoroughly.
Stir in half the milk.
Add another 1/3 of flour mixture and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Spoon batter into prepared muffin tins.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: oinker in a trough
directions: Brown pork with onion in skillet, stirring until pork is crumbly; drain.
Add soup, milk, Colby cheese, butter and parsley; mix well.
Cut top off bread.
Remove center of bread carefully, leaving shell intact, reserving center of bread.
Fill bread shell with pork mixture.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls - halupki
directions: Core cabbage and either blanch in boiling water or place in freezer to get leaves flexible.
Separate leaves.
Mix meat with other ingredients.
Place 2 Tbsp. of mixture into each cabbage leaf.
Roll one side, then roll to end of leaf and tuck inside. Shred remaining cabbage.
Place each filled cabbage roll into pot with shredded cabbage and tomato sauce on top. Bring to boil. Simmer 50 minutes.
Variation:
Add sauerkraut (large or small can) on top of cabbage rolls before cooking.

title: gooey cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and eggs.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and eggs and pour over mixture already pressed into pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes, after coming to a boil.
Make sauce: Mix together the soup, eggs, cheese, mayonnaise, onion, salt and pepper.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar together and spread in pie shell.
Cover top with strawberries and then strawberry glaze. Refrigerate.

title: gourmet gore's chicken a la broccoli
directions: You will need aluminum foil, large pan and oven.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, tomatoes, sauce mix and V-8 juice.
Add garlic powder.
Bring to a boil and cook 10 minutes.

title: sweet and sour short ribs
directions: Brown ribs on all sides in small amount of shortening.
Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Add enough water to reserved juice to make 2 cups.
Add soy sauce, brown sugar and ginger to juice; pour over browned ribs.
Cover; simmer for 2 hours.
Add the pineapple and onion; cook 30 minutes longer.
Serve over rice.

title: ozark pudding
directions: Beat egg and sugar together until very smooth.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir this into egg mixture.
Add nuts, apples and vanilla.
Bake in a greased pie pan in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: linguine with white crab sauce
directions: Saute garlic, onion, parsley and red pepper until soft.
Add dissolved fish bouillon.
(If you like a "clean" broth, you can strain through cheesecloth to remove bits of garlic and onion, but tie up and add to pot to simmer.)
Season to taste.
If too fishy, add more water.
For a thick sauce, thicken with a little cornstarch.
Add cleaned crabmeat and simmer on low to heat through.
Serve over fresh linguine with lots of grated cheese and fresh ground pepper.

title: party punch
directions: Process water, sugar and bananas.
Pour into large container. Add juices and mix.
Freeze in freezer bags until ready to serve. When ready to serve, place frozen mixture in punch bowl.
Pour ginger ale over top.
Will become slushy punch.

title: frances' sweet potato delight
directions: Mix together and pour into greased baking dish.

title: chile
directions: Brown, drain and rinse hamburg.
Place in electric roaster. Add chili powder and mix well with hamburg.
Add salt and pepper. Brown onions until soft.
Add to roaster.
Add beans, sauce and juice.
Stir in 2 to 3 quarts of water.
Add more if needed. Bring to boil and turn to simmer.
Cook for 2 hours or more.
Add more water if needed.
Serves 80 to 85.

title: peanut butter cereal candy
directions: Pour cereal in medium size mixing bowl.
In saucepan, combine sugar and syrup.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a full boil.
Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Immediately pour over cereal, stirring gently, until mixed up.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: fried apples
directions: Melt butter in heavy pan.
Place apples, skin side down, in pan.
Sprinkle generously with sugar.
Add a little water.
Cover and cook very slowly until tender and candied.
Eat them hot. Makes 6 servings.

title: texas pie
directions: Spray a cobbler pan (9 x 13-inch) with Pam.
Add the cherry pie filling and crushed pineapple and juice.
Sprinkle sugar over fruit. Sprinkle the cake mix.
Sprinkle sugar over the cake mix. Sprinkle with coconut and pecans.
Pour the melted margarine over the pie. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together the cream cheese and sour cream. Add taco mix. Stir until creamy. Spread in pie plate. Top with lettuce, olives, tomatoes and shredded cheese.
Serve with chips.
Keep refrigerated.

title: pineapple pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. In small bowl, combine brown sugar and flour. Mix well.

In large bowl, combine eggs, pineapple ice cream topping, vanilla extract and butter. Beat with fork until well mixed. Add brown sugar mixture and mix well. Stir in the pecans. Pour into the unbaked pie crust. Bake for 1 hour, until filling is set and pecans are golden brown.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix onion, celery, cheese, mayonnaise and cooked vegetables. Put in a baking dish.
Add cracker crumbs and drizzle oleo over them.
Bake for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: skinny soup
directions: Combine in soup pot and simmer until veggies are soft.

title: banana nut loaf
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat well. Sift together dry ingredients, add to creamed mixture alternating with bananas.
Beat well after each addition.
Stir in walnuts. Pour into a well-greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix oil, chocolate and sugar.
Blend in one egg at a time until well mixed.
Add vanilla.
Measure flour and sift.
Stir in flour,
baking powder and salt.
Chill several hours or overnight. Heat oven to 350°.
Drop teaspoonfuls of dough into confectioners sugar and coat well.
Place 2 inches apart on a greased baking sheet.
Do not mash flat.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Be careful not to overbake because they will get quite hard.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cheeses; cream well.
Stir in caraway seed.
Form into ball; roll in crushed walnuts.
Wrap and refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Add cocoa and sugar.
Then add milk, butter and vanilla.
Boil until it forms a soft ball when dropped into cold water.
Beat until this thickens and cools.
Drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper and allow to cool.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well and bake at 325° for 1 hour 20 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: onion-roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. In 13 x 9 baking pan, combine all ingredients. Bake, uncovered, stirring occasionally, 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.

title: walnut butterballs
directions: Mix and chill.
Form into small balls.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: manhattan clam chowder
directions: Scrub clams and place in large pot; fill with water to cover and boil until clams open.
Save juice!
Fry bacon; remove and crumble.
Saute in bacon fat the onion, garlic and green pepper. Pour in clam juice.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: cajun seasoning
directions: Mix and blend well.
Store in tightly sealed container.

title: peanut butter icing
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients until it boils. Add the vanilla and powdered sugar.

title: hamburger swiss steak
directions: Shape ground beef into serving size patties.
Flour each patty real good. In oil, fry patties until done.
Remove from pan.
Pour off excess grease, leaving some to make gravy.
Add onions, cook until brown.
Add enough flour to make gravy.
Then add juice from 1 can of tomatoes, plus enough water to make gravy the right consistency.
Place patties back in pan and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cherry congealed salad
directions: Heat cherry pie filling. Stir in dry cherry jello, mixing well. Add drained pineapple to cherry mixture, stir in chopped nuts. Allow to cool. Place in bowl or jello mold and put in refrigerator to chill. Serve as a salad or dessert.

title: coconut caramel pie
directions: Melt margarine; add coconut and chopped pecans.
Brown lightly.
Set aside.

title: turkey manicotti
directions: Stir together cream cheese, sour cream, onion, mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Add turkey.
Spoon into shells.
Arrange in single layer and pour cheese sauce over shells.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cheesy squash
directions: Cook squash in boiling salted water 6 to 8 minutes or until tender, but firm. Drain and cool slightly. Cook bacon in large skillet until crisp. Drain well, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings in skillet. Crumble bacon and set aside. Saute onion in bacon drippings until tender; stir in bacon, bread crumbs and squash. Spoon mixture into casserole dish and top with cheese. Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly and cheese melts. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: hot cranberry punch
directions: Combine juices, sugar, 4 cloves, and cinnamon in two-quart microproof casserole. Cover and place in microwave oven. Cook on high, (100%), for 11 minutes. Stir until sugar is dissolved. Strain into warmed punch bowl. Stick cloves into orange slices and float slices on punch as garnish. Makes 8 servings.

title: sherried shrimp
directions: Saute shrimp in hot butter for 2 minutes. Reduce heat and stir in parsley. Add the sherry and stir for another minute. Serve with rice. Makes 4 servings.

title: blueberry jello salad
directions: In large bowl, dissolve jello in hot water.
Pour in crushed pineapple with juice and blueberry pie filling.
Chill until set. Mix cream cheese, sour cream and sugar until smooth.
Add nuts. Spread on top of jello mixture.
Chill.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cheeses and mix well.
Add onion, dry mustard, Worcestershire sauce and Accent.
Form into ball.
Roll in finely chopped pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: cocoroons
directions: Fold sugar and salt into egg whites, then corn flakes, coconut and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven 12 minutes.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: In small saucepan, bring margarine, Coke and cocoa to a boil. Mix flour and sugar.
Pour boiled mixture over flour-sugar.
Stir. Add eggs and buttermilk with soda.
Add rest of ingredients. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: california casserole
directions: Cook vegetables until just tender, following package directions.
Drain well.
Heat soup, milk and cheese in saucepan until cheese melts.
Pour over vegetables in 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: 7-up cake
directions: *Please make sure you use cake flour, not all-purpose flour. Examples:
Softasilk, Swan's Down.

title: potato salad(one serving)
directions: In medium bowl, combine beans, potatoes and egg; set aside.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Put all ingredients together in a mixing bowl; beat about 3 minutes.
Pour into a prepared 9 x 13-inch pan; bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cake is very moist and good with or without a topping.

title: breakfast cookie bars
directions: Cream butter or margarine until fluffy.
Add molasses and sugar; stir in eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spread mixture in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes. Cool in pan and then cut into squares.
Makes approximately 2 dozen.

title: charczynski chicken
directions: Mix stuffing mix and margarine together. Grease 13 x 9 pan, then place chicken in it. Put cheese over chicken. Cover with soup, then layer stuffing mixture over top. Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: instant hot chocolate
directions: Mix and store in a large covered container.
Use 1/3 cup mix to 1 cup boiling water.
Makes 50 cups of hot chocolate.

title: microwave wilted lettuce salad
directions: With scissors, snip bacon into 1-inch pieces into 3-quart casserole.
Microwave at High 3 minutes, until crisp.
With slotted spoon, remove bacon to paper towels to drain.
To drippings in casserole, add vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper and tarragon.
Microwave at High 2 to 3 minutes to boil.
Stir in celery and onion.
Gradually add lettuce to hot dressing, tossing to coat each piece, just until slightly wilted.
Add orange segments and crisp bacon pieces and toss again lightly.
Serve immediately.

title: janie's beans
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake 3 hours at 300°.

title: fruit cake candy rolls
directions: Shape in rolls and roll in xxxx sugar.
Wrap in foil and keep in refrigerator at least 24 hours before slicing.
Store in refrigerator.

title: chicken and rice soup
directions: Cut up chicken and remove skin.
Boil chicken in water with ginger.
Mince garlic and onion.
Remove chicken from water and add rice.
Simmer.
Stir often.
Add water as needed.
Remove chicken from bone and cut into small pieces.
Mix garlic, onions and chicken.
Add rice.
Simmer, stirring often.
Soup will thicken as rice cooks.
Add salt or soy sauce to taste.
Soup should be thick.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in a bowl.
In another bowl, blend remaining ingredients 1 minute at low speed; 4 minutes high speed. Blend apple mixture into batter by hand or with mixer.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Let stand for 1/2 hour out of draft (angel food pan preferable).

title: seven-layer salad
directions: Slice, crumble, chop or shred first 8 ingredients in separate bowls.
Layer ingredients, beginning with lettuce or spinach. Lettuce or spinach will be layered in between other ingredients. Mix mayonnaise and sour cream together.
Amount will depend on size of bowl, since the mayonnaise mixture is spread across the top of the salad, sealing edges.
Let sit in refrigerator overnight.
Mix together just before serving.
Add cherry tomatoes, if desired.

title: peach bread
directions: Stir 6 to 8 peaches in blender until pureed.
In mixer bowl, cream together sugar and shortening.
Add dry ingredients and peach puree; mix thoroughly.
Add vanilla and nuts; stir until well blended.
Have oven preheated to 325° and 2 loaf pans well-greased and floured.
Divide batter equally between 2 pans. Bake at 325° for about 50 minutes to 1 hour.
Let bread cool in pans for a bit before removing.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Lightly oil an 2-quart casserole and put peaches in.
Sprinkle with sugar, nutmeg and cinnamon.
In a small bowl, mix margarine and sugar until well blended.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and juice or milk.
Mixture may be a little thin.
Pour over the peaches.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° to 375° oven.

title: pimiento cheese sandwiches
directions: Combine cheeses, mixing well. Add next 3 ingredients, mixing well. Cover and chill at least 1 hour.
Cut pocket bread rounds in half. Line each half with lettuce and fill with 1/4 cup cheese mixture. Yields 8 servings (about 211 calories per serving).

title: italian vegetable soup
directions: Mix all ingredients except green beans, zucchini and cheese in Dutch oven.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in green beans and zucchini.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes or until macaroni and vegetables are tender.
Remove bay leaf.
Sprinkle each serving with cheese.
Makes 5 servings.

title: pineapple low fat pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients plus a small amount of cool whip until thoroughly mixed.
Pour into a graham cracker crust and top with remaining cool whip.
Set in refrigerator for about 1/2 hour before serving.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Stir soup (do not add water) over medium heat, until smooth; add milk and pepper.
In buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole, alternate layers of potatoes, onion, sauce and cheese.
Dot top with butter; sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and bake at 375° for one hour. Uncover and bake 20 minutes more.
Makes 4 generous servings.

title: polish apple pancakes
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, sugar and salt.
In another bowl beat eggs; add milk and oil.
Add to dry ingredients and stir until smooth.
Fold in apples.

title: main course chicken salad
directions: Day Before:
Bake or steam chicken until moist and tender. Cool and cut into chunks.
Wash and slice the celery; cut the grapes in half longwise.
Pour all of the ingredients in separate containers in the coldest part of your refrigerator.

title: v.i.p. pizza
directions: Place rolls on pizza pan; press together, then bake in 350° oven until light golden brown. Cool. Spread onion dip over crust and spread veggies on crust; sprinkle with shredded cheese and chopped egg.

title: rainbow prism cake
directions: Prepare first 3 packages of Jell-O separately using 1 cup hot water and 1/2 cup cold water for each. Chill until firm in separate 8 x 8 x 2-inch pans.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and syrup slowly.
When well mixed, add eggs, beaten with salt.
Mix well.
Stir in pecans and vanilla. Turn into unbaked pie shell and bake in moderate 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: green salad
directions: Dissolve jello in the usual manner.
Set in refrigerator until it begins to congeal.
Whip cream; add mayonnaise and whip again. Add pineapple, nuts, whipped cream and mayonnaise to jello.
Stir until well mixed.
Chill until jelled.

title: peanut patties(microwave)
directions: Combine sugar, water, salt and light corn syrup in a 2-quart glass measuring cup.
Bring to a boil in microwave (approximately) 3 minutes.
Stir and add peanuts.
Cook 7 to 9 minutes more or until soft ball stage (234°).
Remove from oven; add butter, vanilla and red food coloring.
Cool and beat until creamy.
Drop by tablespoons onto greased cookie sheet or make into two large patties.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix broccoli, soup and cheese. Microwave until cheese is melted.
Stir and mix well. Serve with Triscuits or any snack cracker.

title: fruit pizza (serves 8)
directions: Mix together well and pat into a jelly roll or pizza pan. Bake at 350° until edges begin to brown, approximately 15 minutes. Cool completely.

title: minestrone
directions: Rinse
beans
and drain well.
Remove stems of spinach. Wash cabbage and spinach.
Cut spinach and cabbage leaves into thin strips and steam, with only the water left on the leaves after washing,
until
tender
but
not soggy.
Drain and set aside. Cut
carrots,
potato,
onion, celery and string beans into small pieces.
Chop together parsley, garlic and bacon or pancetta.

title: layered pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Rinse in cold water; drain.
Combine macaroni and oil; toss lightly.
Layer eggs, lettuce, macaroni, ham, peas and cheese in salad bowl.
Combine mayonnaise and remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spread mixture evenly over the salad, sealing to edge of bowl.
Cover tightly and chill 12 hours or more.
Toss gently before serving.

title: mexican corn bread casserole
directions: Mix
eggs,
corn,
baking powder, buttermilk, vegetable oil and
corn
meal
together.
Pour 1/2 of batter into well-greased skillet
or casserole dish.
Sprinkle peppers, cheese and
1 full cup of scrambled hamburger meat over the 1st half. Pour
on remainder of batter and sprinkle the top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Bring sugar and Karo to boil, stirring.
Mix peanut butter and Cocoa Krispies together.
Add mixtures together.
Roll into balls. Dip in melted almond bark chocolate (this is optional).

title: el grande
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Simmer.
Serve over yellow rice.

title: picante sauce
directions: Chop onion and peppers in food processor.
Add tomatoes and process a few seconds.
Warm oil, vinegar, salt and Accent in saucepan until salt dissolves.
Mix together and add cilantro.

title: sweet potato casserole(makes 8 servings)
directions: Cook sweet potatoes in boiling water with skins on for 45 minutes or until tender.
When cool to touch, peel and mash. Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, eggs, vanilla, milk and butter. Beat with electric mixer on medium speed until smooth.
Spoon mixture into a greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine 1/3 cup brown sugar, pecans, flour and 2 tablespoons butter; sprinkle mixture over casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix cheese and sausage.
Add Bisquick mix and mix well.
Form into balls and bake in oven at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: peach cooler
directions: Put all ingredients, except the ice cream, into the blender and process until smooth. Add the ice cream. Cover and stir. Yields 2 servings.

title: trucker's beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake, uncovered, at 350° until bubbly (about 45 minutes).

title: turkey apple burgers
directions: In a bowl combine dried onion and apple juice.
Stir in egg, bread crumbs and apple.
Add sausage; mix well.
Shape into four 4-inch patties.
Place in a greased, shallow baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Serve burgers on lettuce leaves with slices of onion and tomato.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: lemonade pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix milk and lemonade together.
Add Cool Whip.
Place into pie shells.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: grit eggs
directions: In a skillet, melt butter.
Saute onion.
Add toast, torn into pieces.
Stir to soak up butter.
Pour in eggs, salt and pepper. Cook until firm.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix well with wire beaters.
Grease a deep baking dish and bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until firm.

title: onion rings
directions: Early in the morning, slice onions.
Mix milk with eggs.
Dip rings into egg milk mixture then into any popular pancake cornmeal mix, lay them on brown paper to dry until dinner time.
Heat deep fryer to 360 degrees.
Dump in rings as you would French fries.

title: grilled lemon dilled salmon steaks
directions: Pour marinade over 1 1/2 pounds salmon (thawed); marinate in refrigerator for 2 hours or more, turning once.
Brush remaining marinade on salmon while grilling.
Serves 6.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix the flour, sugar, nuts and stick of margarine together with pastry blender or fork.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add Crisco and cream well.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Sift flour and soda together.
Add to mixture, alternating with buttermilk.
Stir in other ingredients except egg whites.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in mixture.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) pans at 350° for about 30 minutes or until center springs back when lightly touched.

title: fruit salad
directions: Peel apples, oranges and bananas.
Cut into bite size pieces. Mix sugar with mayonnaise.
Pour over fruit and stir together. Chill before serving.

title: cornbread
directions: Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Combine puddings and milk.
Beat until thick.
