Add Cool Whip and blend.
Put layer of graham crackers in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Alternate layers of pudding and crackers.
End with crackers on top.
Combine sugar, cocoa and Pet milk.
Bring to a boil and cook for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and butter; let cool.
Beat until thick.
Spread over top of crackers.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: icebox cake
directions: Combine and cook the first 3 ingredients over low heat until it comes to a boil.
Add Jell-O (let cool).
Have cream cold; beat until stiff.
Add sugar and lemon juice.
After first mixture cools, fold into whipped cream; pour in dish lined with vanilla wafers.
(Alternate same as for banana pudding.)

title: terlingua texas chili
directions: Saute onions in small amount of oil in heavy pan until transparent.
Add meat and cook until brown, approximately 5 minutes).
Reduce heat to low and add remaining ingredients. Simmer for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: prune cake
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients, sift the flour and spices, add the prunes, buttermilk and soda.
Pour into a bundt pan and bake at 350° until done, when knife comes out clean.

title: play dough
directions: Cook over low heat.
Stir constantly until mixture leaves sides of pan.
Cool.
Knead.
Add food coloring (15 to 20 drops). Provides fun for kids of all ages.

title: okra creole
directions: Heat oil in pan.
Add onions and pepper.
Cook until tender. Add okra; cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add corn and tomatoes.
Cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: date ball
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add dates.
Cook for 5 minutes or until dates are tender and mash.
Remove from heat.
Cool a few minutes.
Add hot mixture, a spoonful at a time, to egg mixture, stirring rapidly. Boil for 2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat.
Pour over Rice Krispies.
Cool and shape into balls.
Roll in coconut and chill.

title: christmas fruit tea
directions: Pour cranberry juice, pineapple juice, lemonade, apple juice and orange juice into 30-cup electric percolator.
Place spices in basket.
Perk through complete cycle.
Let stand 1 hour.
Serve.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender; drain well.
Stir in margarine.
Add mayonnaise and 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Crush crackers; add 1/2 cup to mixture.
Add beaten egg, cayenne pepper, salt and black pepper; mix well.
Top with 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 cup crushed crackers.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes, or until brown.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a greased 10-inch pie pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Peel and mash avocado; blend in lemon juice, onion juice and seasonings.
Stir in sour cream.
Taste and adjust seasonings. Peel tomato, cut into small pieces and remove seeds.
Add tomato as a garnish.
Great with all kinds of chips.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar slowly.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover 2 cookie sheets with waxed paper. Drop by teaspoonfuls close together on waxed paper.

title: golombki(cabbage rolls)
directions: Cook bacon until crisp and remove from grease.
Add onion to grease and cook until tender.
Add bacon (crumbled) back to grease and onion mixture.
Bring to high heat and pour over raw ground beef; mix together.
Cook rice, drain and add to ground beef mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Beat egg.
Add sugar and Crisco in hot water, grated orange and orange juice.
Mix well.
Sift flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Add to liquid mixture.
Mix well.
Add cranberries and nuts.
Put in greased bread pan and let rise 3/4 hour.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325°.
Remove from pan after 10 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In a bowl, beat Egg Beaters until frothy.
Beat in the sugar, vegetable oil and the vanilla extract.
Beat until thick and lemon colored.
Stir in zucchini, carrot and flour which has been sifted with cinnamon, soda, salt and baking powder.

title: beet pickles
directions: Cook beets until almost tender.
Peel and slice.
Combine rest of ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Place in jars and seal.

title: tenderloin with marinade
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Spear meat in several places and place in Ziploc bag.
Pour marinade over meat; refrigerate for 8 hours.
Turn occasionally.
Drain and reserve marinade.
Place on rack in baking pan.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Baste occasionally.
Serve with remaining marinade.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: banana walnut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine cake mix, 1/2 the amount of water on package directions, eggs, oil and baking soda in mixer bowl.
Beat until mixed well.
Add 1 1/2 cups walnuts and bananas; mix until stiff.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking pan, sprayed with nonstick cooking spray and floured.
Frost with any cream cheese icing; sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup walnuts.

title: spanish pork chops
directions: Brown chops on both sides and place around sides of baking dish. Add rice to center of dish.
Place remaining ingredients in pan.
Stir to combine well. Pour over chops and rice.
Cover and bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, and eggs.
Combine soda, buttermilk, and all flavorings.
After sugar, eggs, and margarine are blended, add buttermilk mixture (1/3 of it at a time) with 1 cup flour at a time, blending well.
Start in a cold oven with a pan of water underneath.
Bake at 350° in a buttered and floured Bundt cake pan, for about 1 hour and 20 minutes, or until done.
Using toothpick for testing.
Remove from pan as soon as you remove from oven.

title: crispy drumsticks(low-fat)
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a small dish, stir well. Combine egg white and milk in a small bowl.
Dip each drumstick in milk mixture; dredge in breadcrumb mixture.
Place drumsticks in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish coated with cooking spray.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.
Yield:
4 servings (196 calories per serving).
Fat:
5.8 grams per serving.

title: oriental casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
In a mixing bowl, blend soups, soy sauce and water.
Place celery, onion, bean sprouts and chestnuts in bottom of buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Pour the blended soup mixture over vegetables.
Spread browned meat over top.
Sprinkle rice over meat.
Bake 2 hours and 15 minutes in 325° oven with lid on casserole or pan.
Stir with fork once or twice last 15 minutes of baking.

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: Beat lemonade into Cool Whip.
Spread in pie shell.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.

title: cream doughnuts
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine eggs, sugar, cream and half and half.
Stir in baking powder, nutmeg and salt.
Stir in enough flour to make a soft dough.
Roll out, cut and fry in 365° fat.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt the butter in a double boiler.

Stir in flour, pepper, salt and cheese, then stir until thoroughly blended and smooth. Add the milk gradually while stirring and cook over boiling water until smooth and thickened, stirring constantly.
Makes one cup sauce.

title: brown sauce
directions: Melt butter, add flour and slowly brown.
Mix in onion.
Add water little by little and stir constantly. Season.
Bring to a boil.
Strain before serving.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onions until done. Mix together 1/2 can Ro-Tel, mushroom soup and Ranch beans. Crush Doritos. Spread some in the bottom of pan. Top with ground beef and add soup mixture. Top with cheese. Continue layering. Top with chips. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: "fudgy" apple snacks
directions: In medium saucepan, combine brown sugar, cocoa and salt; blend in evaporated milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture comes to a boil.
Cook gently 3 to 4 minutes, until mixture thickens, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat; stir in butter and vanilla.

title: fettuccine alfredo roma
directions: Cook noodles until tender in salted boiling water with oil added to prevent sticking.
Drain.
Melt butter over medium heat. Add cheese, sour cream, cream and beaten egg gradually and blend until slightly thickened.
Add pasta noodles, salt and pepper to taste and toss lightly.
Garnish with additional cheese.
You may add steamed broccoli and shrimp for a lovely variation.
Buon appetito!

title: pea and bacon salad
directions: Thaw peas.
Drain fried bacon on paper towel.
Combine all ingredients.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: woodford pudding
directions: Cream the sugar and butter until light.
Add eggs and mix well. Dissolve the soda in the buttermilk. Add the flour (which has been sifted with the cinnamon) to the sugar and egg mixture. Add buttermilk mixture.
Blend in the jam.
Bake in a greased shallow baking dish about 40 minutes in a 325° oven.
Cut in squares and top with sauce.

title: joy gears barley and mushrooms
directions: Saute onion and barley until lightly browned.
Add 2 cups chicken broth.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Add mushrooms and 2 cups more broth.
Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes more at 350°.
Add more broth if needed, cover with slivered almonds and bake another 45 minutes.
Total baking time:
2 hours.
Serves 8.

title: balloon buns(traditional roll dough)
directions: Divide dough in half about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into 3 1/2 circles.
Mix cinnamon and sugar.
Dip each marshmallow into butter, then into cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Wrap each dough circle around marshmallow, pinching together tightly at the bottom.
Dip roll in butter, then in cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Place in greased muffin cups (2 3/4-inch diameter).
Let rise until double.

title: apple raisin snack cake
directions: Blend salad dressing, cake mix and eggs at low speed with electric mixer until moistened.
Beat on medium speed 2 minutes. Add apples and raisins.
Spread into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until wooden pick comes out clean.

title: homemade spicy tomato juice
directions: Place all ingredients through parsley in large soup pot. Bring to a boil and simmer until soft. Strain juice in a colander, pressing to extract all liquid or put through a juice machine. Flavor to taste with the seasonings. Can according to current instructions.
Makes 12 quarts.

title: cynthia's yum yum chicken
directions: Cook chicken. Cool. Cut into bite-size pieces. Mix with soups, sour cream, and 1 cup broth. Put in large pan. Pour herb mix

on top. Melt butter and 1 cup broth together. Pour evenly over top of dressing. Cook 1 hour at 350 or until hot and bubbly. For extra kick add 1 can rotel tomatoes to chicken, soup and sour cream and broth.

title: the barnes' family baked chocolate pudding and hard sauce(a family tradition; the taste makes up for the calories!)
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients over moderate heat in medium saucepan, stirring until thick.
Remove from heat; cool.
In large mixing bowl combine remaining ingredients.
Add chocolate mixture and blend gently but thoroughly.
Pour into well-greased and floured Bundt-tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve warm, topped with Hard Sauce.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream butter, oil and sugar well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well. Add seasoning and flour, blending well. Add 7-Up. Grease and flour tube pan. Bake at 350° for about an hour.

title: meat loaf(always good)
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Press mixture into an ungreased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Cover with a good layer of catsup.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Drain off excess fat. Invert loaf onto serving dish.
Let stand several minutes before slicing.

title: mean miss judy cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
While cake is still warm, poke holes in it with handle of wooden spoon (about 4 holes wide).
Then pour your condensed milk and caramel topping over the holes.
For a more moist cake you can let it set overnight.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: homemade blackberry preserves
directions: Gently sort, rinse and drain fresh berries. Place them in a large pot with the sugar and lemon juice. Bring to a boil over medium-high heat. Reduce heat to medium-low and stir occasionally. This juicy mixture will thicken while it simmers. Skim off foam. Be careful not to overcook or it will become tarry. Fills 8 wide-mouth, one-pint jars.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: mini meat loaves hawaiian
directions: In a large bowl, combine beef with bread crumbs, onion, tomato sauce, egg, 3 teaspoons Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Shape into 6 individual meat loaves.
Place in a shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Increase oven temperature to hot 425°.
Mix pineapple with remaining teaspoon Worcestershire sauce.
Spoon on top of each loaf.
Return to oven.
Bake 15 minutes more.

title: zucchini and tomato
directions: Melt butter and saute green peppers and onions.
Add zucchini, bread crumbs, Romano cheese, salt and pepper.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart covered casserole.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Add tomatoes and bake 10 minutes more.
Melt Cheddar cheese on top and serve.

title: golden cream soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine all vegetables and seasonings and water; cook until tender.
Combine mix and flour; pour in vegetables.
Stir until soup thickens.
Dice cheese and add to soup mixture until smooth.
Recipe will double.
Easy to freeze.

title: party potatoes
directions: Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread hash browns in bottom of pan.
Drizzle 1/2 of melted butter over.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup onion over.
Mix soup, cheese and sour cream together; put over.
Mix cornflakes with rest of butter.
Sprinkle that over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: texas hash
directions: If you buy whole peeled tomatoes, you'll need to cut them into small pieces.

title: terrific tuna casserole
directions: Break tuna into chunks.
Combine butter, milk, salt and sauce mix; heat.
Add noodles and tuna and mix lightly.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes or until heated through.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Combine sugar and egg in a double boiler; stir well.
Add butter and remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Bring water to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; cook, stirring constantly, until smooth and thickened.
Serve warm over pound cake.
Yields 1 1/3 cups.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix instant pudding according to directions on box and set aside.
Take angel food cake and break into small pieces in bottom of dish.
Next slice the strawberries on top of cake, then add the instant pudding and top with the Cool Whip.
Let this sit in the refrigerator for a few hours or even overnight before serving.

title: red dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat 1/2 hour.
Very good on lettuce.

title: cheese cake
directions: Measure Rice
Krispies	and
crush.
Melt
margarine in small saucepan over
low	heat. Remove from heat.
Stir in the 1/4 cup sugar
and	the
cinnamon.	Add
crushed
cereal.
Mix well.
With back
of
spoon,
press
mixture evenly and firmly around sides and in
bottom
of 9-inch pan to form crust.
Set aside.
In small mixing bowl, mix together sour cream and the 2 tablespoons off sugar.
Set
aside.
In
large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add eggs, vanilla and 1/3 cup sugar and 1
teaspoon of
the
lemon
juice.
Beat until well combined.	Pour mixture into crust.
Bake in oven at 375° for about 20 minutes
or until set.
Remove from oven, spread sour cream mix over top and return to oven.
Bake 5 minutes longer. Remove and let
cool.
In small bowl, mix pie filling with the remaining 1	teaspoon
lemon juice. Spread over top of cooled pie.
Refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions.
Drain.
Squeeze to remove moisture.
Combine spinach with remaining ingredients. Form into 3/4-inch balls.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet and bake in 325° oven for 20 to 25 minutes. Yields 10 dozen balls.

title: orange candy cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs, 1 at a time.
Add flour and milk.
Roll dates, nuts and candy (chopped) in flour.
Add coconut.
Pour in large tube pan or 4 large coffee cans and bake at 250° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Mix thoroughly, 1 cup orange juice (4 to 5 fresh oranges) and 2 cups confectioners sugar.
Pour over hot cake and let sit overnight.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix
together
flour,
sugar,
butter and shortening to form crumbs,
then
take
out
cup
for
top of cake.
Pour mixture of	eggs,
milk and baking powder into crumb mixture. Mix well and pour into cake pan.
Sprinkle the crumbs you have saved on the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: black-eyed peas
directions: Clean and wash
peas.
Add
to
gallon of the water. Bring to a boil;
boil
for 10 minutes.
Drain off water.
The purpose of draining the
first
water is to keep the peas from being dark. Add the
other
gallon of water to peas and bring to a boil.
Add salt,
pepper, sugar, chopped onion and bacon drippings.
Cook over a
slow
fire until peas are tender, not mushy.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Measure rice and cook separately.
Peel and devein shrimp. Boil and save water.
Saute onion, celery, bell pepper and garlic in oleo until tender.
Add soups and 1 cup water where shrimp were boiled.
Stir in chopped parsley, onion tops, cooked shrimp and pimento.
Add cooked rice and half the bread crumbs.
Season with salt and both peppers.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple, fruit cocktail and mandarin oranges. Combine with strawberries and pie filling; chill. Fold and blend mixture with the sliced bananas and chill.

title: german apple cake
directions: Mix flour, soda, salt and cinnamon in large bowl. Combine eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla in a separate bowl. On low speed of mixer, gradually add the flour mixture to egg mixture until well blended.
Fold in apples and walnuts. Spoon into greased and floured 13 x 9 pan. Mixture will be thick. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: feather and fin casserole
directions: In a medium size saucepan melt 2 tablespoons butter over moderate heat.
Add onion and garlic and cook until softened.
Stir in flour.
Slowly whisk in broth, bring to a boil and cook stirring until sauce thickens.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes. Meanwhile, in a small frying pan melt 2 tablespoons butter, add mushrooms and cook until lightly browned.
In a small bowl, beat egg yolks and cream.
Whisk in about 1/2 cup hot sauce.
Whisk the egg cream mixture into remaining sauce.
Add mushrooms.
Sprinkle with pepper.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Let butter cool.
Mix and put small teaspoon into smallest muffin pans.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.
Can freeze.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
When cake is cool, add the icing.

title: bean casserole
directions: Mix beans (drained), soup and 1/2 of onions together in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with rest of onions for last 5 minutes of baking.

title: sausage-hash brown casserole
directions: Pour potatoes into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°, while preparing meat.
(They will not be brown.)
Brown meat and onion; drain.

title: modeling dough ornaments
directions: Mix salt and cornstarch together.
Bring water to boil; remove from heat.
Add salt and cornstarch slowly while stirring. Continue to cook over low heat until dough is hard to stir. Remove from pan; let cool and knead.
Store in airtight container. Model and paint.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown beef strips in butter.
Remove from skillet. Drain mushrooms (reserving liquid) and saute in drippings in skillet. Remove.
Stir 3 tablespoons flour into drippings in skillet and add soup mix.
Gradually add water and mushroom liquid, blending well.
Stir until thickened.
Return meat and mushrooms to pan. Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Blend in sour cream and serve over cooked egg noodles.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Mix cream cheese and butter in mixing bowl, cream until light and fluffy; add in sugar, mix well; add in eggs, 2 at a time, beat well after each addition.
Pour in flavors and mix in cake flour; beat until creamy.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour in greased and floured Bundt pan.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
In a large skillet, cook ground beef and onion in butter until onions are tender.
Drain.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sour cream and cream of chicken soup.
Heat through and serve over noodles.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: fried corn
directions: Fry bacon.
Drain and put aside.
Pour cans of corn in bacon grease.
Simmer for about 20 to 30 minutes.
Crumble bacon on top before serving.

title: cheese log
directions: Add grated Cheddar cheese, cream cheese, grated onion and garlic salt.
Mix together well. Roll into a ball or log.
Chill 10 minutes.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Cook onion, celery and butter in frying pan. Add bread crumbs, salt and sugar. Spray 8 x 8 casserole dish with Pam. Place a layer of	tomatoes, then a layer of bread crumb mixture. Repeat and end with a layer of bread crumb mixture on top. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cobbler dough
directions: Melt butter in a pan.
Mix together the flour, sugar, baking powder and milk.
Pour dough mixture in on butter.
Pour hot fruit in on dough.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes, until golden brown.

title: five cup salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill before serving.
Even better if prepared the night before.

title: christmas morning pie
directions: Fry sausage and drain.
Set aside.
Grate cheese and set aside.
Mix your eggs, grits, sausage and cheese.
Reserve some cheese for top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serve Christmas morning with biscuits.

title: party bread dip
directions: Mix last 5 ingredients.
Chill 1 hour.
Cut out center of loaf.
Fill loaf with dip.
Use center and/or cocktail rye bread to dip.

title: quick key lime pie
directions: In medium bowl, stir together condensed milk, ReaLime and food coloring.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into crust.
Chill 3 hours.

title: quesadillas
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Add fajita meat, bell peppers and onion.
Cook until meat is browned and cooked throughout, about 15 minutes.
Drain fat from meat and set cooked fajita meat aside. Spray a large griddle with Pam cooking spray.
Heat on medium-high heat until griddle is hot.
Place 3 to 4 tortillas in a single layer on hot griddle.
Add a layer of fajita meat and a layer of cheese.
Place a flour tortilla on top of cheese.
Cook for 5 minutes and turn.
Cook an additional 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Serve while hot with pico de gallo, guacamole and sour cream if desired.

title: orange salad
directions: Section oranges.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Serve with a maraschino cherry on top.

title: pretzel and pineapple salad
directions: Crust:
Mix pretzels, butter and sugar all together and press crust into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pat down with hands.
Bake at 325° for 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: tuna tilla's
directions: Place 1 tablespoon tuna mixture inside flour tortilla.
Wrap and broil for 1 minute.
Fast and good.

title: tex-mex spice mix
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly and store mixture in a sealed container in a cool, dark, dry place up to 3 months.

title: veg-all casserole(makes 4 to 6 servings)
directions: Combine 1/4 cup butter with the Cheez Whiz in medium saucepan.
Heat and stir until blended.
Add vegetables and mix. Melt remaining 1/4 cup butter.
Combine with cracker crumbs.
Put on top of casserole mixture.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: good pizza crust
directions: Add yeast to warm water.
Let stand a few minutes.
Stir to dissolve.
Add remaining ingredients and stir vigorously.
Knead until smooth.
Cover and let set for 20 minutes.
Divide dough into 2 equal portions or just one for a thick crust, if you prefer.
Roll out; brush with cooking oil.
Top with your favorite topping.
Bake at 425° until finished.

title: grandma's cookies
directions: Boil raisins in water to cover for 5 minutes.
Save water.
Let raisins cool.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla, nuts and raisins.
Dissolve soda in 1/2 cup raisin water.
Add along with the dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes in 350° oven.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Spread pecans and coconut evenly in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Pour cake mixture over nuts and coconut.
Mix margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar together.
(This works best if margarine is melted and cream cheese is softened.)
Pour mixture evenly over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes, depending upon individual oven temperatures.

title: chicken florentine
directions: Wipe chicken breasts with damp paper towel.
With sharp knife, carefully remove skin and bones keeping meat in tack. Lightly coat chicken with flour on both sides.
In 1/4 cup hot butter, in medium sized skillet over medium heat, saute chicken about 1 minute on both sides.
Add chicken broth; simmer, covered, 10 minutes or until tender.
Remove chicken and add 1/4 cup unsifted flour, salt, pepper and nutmeg; stir until smooth.
Add milk and cream a little at a time, stirring after each addition. Return to heat.
Over medium heat, return to boil, stirring constantly; reduce heat and simmer for three minutes, stirring. In small bowl, beat egg yolk with fork.
Stir in about 3/4 cup hot sauce; mix well.
Return egg yolk mixture along with 1/2 cup grated Parmesan and rest of sauce in saucepan, stirring constantly.
Cook, stirring over low heat, just until thickened and cheese is melted; do not boil.
To keep sauce hot, cover. Cook spinach as directed.
Turn into sieve; drain well.
Return to saucepan with one cup of cheese sauce; cover and keep hot.
Layer spinach in bottom of 2-quart shallow baking dish.
Arrange breasts in single layer on top of spinach.
Cover with rest of sauce and sprinkle with rest of grated Swiss cheese.
Broil 6-inches from heat or until lightly brown.

title: leona's green bean casserole
directions: Sauce:
Stir-fry bacon (chopped fine).
Drain.
Add garlic, onions and bell pepper (chopped fine).
Stir in soup and black pepper; cover.
Cook for 5 minutes on medium heat.
Add green beans; cover.
Boil 15 minutes in skillet with cover.
Put all into casserole dish; top with crushed garlic bread crisps (crushed). Makes 8 servings.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt butter over hot water in double boiler.
Drop in chocolate and allow to melt.
Add sugar gradually.
Be sure sugar is completely moistened after each addition; will be very thick and dry.
Add salt and milk.
Heat until sugar crystals have melted.
Serve hot.
Makes 1 quart.
Keeps in refrigerator for weeks. Can be thinned with evaporated milk.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Cook brownies and let cool.
Crumble brownies up and layer brownies, pudding, Cool Whip and candy until all have been used. Very good!

title: walnut cream cheese cake(this one is good for at work or for potluck.)
directions: Dust sides of buttered Bundt pan.

title: peach and pineapple jam
directions: Mix together in a large pan. Bring to a boil and boil for 45 minutes. Remove from heat. Add 1 family size box of orange or peach jello.
Stir well until dissolved.
Put in jam jar and seal.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix above sugar and cinnamon together.
Add biscuits and shake together in a bowl with lid or bag.
Put this in a greased bundt pan.

title: raisin cake
directions: Mix raisins, sugar, brown sugar, butter and hot water; set aside to cool.
Mix dry ingredients together; add liquid ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: rigatoni with spinach and beans
directions: Cook the pasta following the package directions until al dente.
Drain well.
Meanwhile, heat the olive oil in a medium size nonstick skillet over very low heat.
Add the garlic and saute until golden for about 2 to 3 minutes, being careful not to let garlic overbrown.
Add the spinach, then saute, stirring frequently, for about 4 minutes or until spinach is wilted.
Add cannellini beans, pink beans, grated Parmesan cheese, salt and red pepper flakes.
Cook for 5 minutes.

title: parfait pie
directions: Use same flavor Jell-O and yogurt.

title: potatoes o'brien
directions: In a large bowl mix hash browns, 1/2 cup melted margarine, salt, pepper, soup, cheese, sour cream and onion.
Turn into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: mother's heavenly delight
directions: Melt marshmallows in scalded milk.
Let cool.
Fold pineapple and whipped cream in the marshmallow mixture.
Put most of the graham cracker crumbs on bottom of 8-inch square pan.
Pour in marshmallow mixture.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Chill. This is a light fluffy dessert.

title: sugar coated peanuts
directions: Mix water and sugar; bring to a boil. Add peanuts. Boil on medium heat, stirring every 5 minutes until water is absorbed and peanuts coated. Spread on long, flat pan. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: mini cinnamon rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Separate crescent rolls into one large rectangle per package.
Flatten with rolling pin. Spread with butter.
Combine sugar, cinnamon and raisins or pecans.
Sprinkle over butter.
Roll each rectangle from short end.
Cut each roll into slices and place in a round pan.
Bake 20-25 minutes. Drizzle top of rolls while warm with glaze.

title: kanai banana bread
directions: Mix sugar, butter and shortening together.
Add bananas and eggs.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix
ingredients.
Pour
in graham cracker crust.
Beat egg whites; add 4 tablespoons sugar.
Beat well.
Put over pie and bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: great grape juice
directions: In a large punch bowl, combine grape juice and water.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Garnish with lemon slices.

title: easy pierogies
directions: Place cooked springs in a casserole dish.
Peel and cut potatoes in very small cubes.
Boil until soft.
Drain water off and add to springs.
Melt cheese and 1 stick of oleo together; pour over springs and potatoes.
Mix.
Saute onions.
Cut up and pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: dash cake
directions: Mix cake according to package directions. Bake cake in a long pan.
Make jello using 1 cup hot water. After cake is cool, punch holes in cake with fork.
Pour jello over cake.
Make pudding according to package directions and set aside until set.
Spread over cake.
Spread pie filling over pudding. Cover with Cool Whip.

title: laurine's divinity
directions: Add sugar and corn syrup to boiling water.
Cook until hard ball stage is reached (250°).
Slowly add sugar mixture to stiffly beaten egg whites.
Add nuts, vanilla and salt.
Beat until cool and thick.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Yields 3 to 4 dozen pieces.

title: easy punch bowl layer cake
directions: Divide all ingredients in 3 parts.
In large, clear punch bowl, spoon each part by layering ingredients in bowl.
Begin each part with cake.
Repeat layering until ingredients are gone and bowl is filled.
Top looks best with a layer of Cool Whip and nuts.

title: homemade waffle batter
directions: Sift together flour and baking powder.
Add salt, sugar, egg yolks, milk and shortening; blend until smooth.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into batter mix.
Spoon onto hot waffle iron and cook until brown.

title: baked apples
directions: Core apples and cut in 1/8-inch pieces.
Put in a buttered 1 3/4-quart baking dish with pineapple and sprinkle with a little cinnamon sugar and tapioca pudding.
Dot with butter, cover with plastic wrap and bake on High in microwave oven for 10 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese and drain pineapple. Mix all ingredients well, except nuts. Chill; form into
a ball and roll in nuts. Refrigerate up to 7 days or freeze until needed.

title: hona's turnip casserole
directions: Salt and cook enough turnips to make 6 cups of mashed turnips.
Drain and mash.
Add softened cream cheese, sugar and oleo.
Mix well.
Pour into casserole dish and top with bread crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven until bubbly hot and slightly brown. Serves 8 to 10.

title: pepper scallop stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in wok for 1 minute over medium-high heat.
Stir-fry peppers and onions until just cooked, about 5 minutes.
Remove and set aside.
Stir-fry scallops for 3 minutes.
Return vegetables to the wok and toss with scallops.
Add oil and soy sauce.
Toss, cover and cook 1 to 2 minutes.
Spoon over cooked noodles.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.
Per serving:
400 calories and 6 grams fat (14% of calories).

title: corned beef omelet
directions: Beat eggs together.
Add milk and salt.
Tear corned beef into small pieces.
Add to egg mixture.
Stir in cheese, green pepper and onion.
Pour into an 11 3/4 x 7 1/2 x 1 3/4-inch glass baking dish.
Set oven to 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Cover with wax paper.
Recipe yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except egg whites.
Beat 2 minutes.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in; don't beat.
Pour into 3 (8-inch) pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: hot chip dip
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Drain and mix all ingredients in baking dish.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour. Serve warm with large tortilla chips.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Place
in
glass or crock.
Do not use metal container. Blend ingredients in a small bowl.
Place in large wide-mouth jar, allowing room to expand double.
Cover with cheesecloth; let stand
4 to 5 days.
Starter will have a strong sour odor and should be bubbly.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Bake chicken breasts in 400° oven for 1 hour; when cool, shred into large pieces.
To the chicken broth, add mushroom soup, chicken soup and cream.
Stir in chiles.
Add tortilla pieces to sauce; mix well.
Add chicken pieces, stirring gently.
Place in casserole dish and top with 1/2 pound grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: black beans and rice
directions: Soak beans overnight; drain and rinse.
Cook bacon and set aside; brown pork roast cubes in bacon fat.
Combine beans, pork and bacon with water; cover and simmer for 2 hours.
Saute onion and garlic in fat; add to bean mixture.
Add remaining ingredients (except rice) and simmer for 30 minutes.
Allow to cool; refrigerate overnight to blend flavors.
The next day, reheat bean mixture and cook rice according to package instructions.
Serve beans over rice.

title: arizona ranch bean soup
directions: In large pan, combine beans, rice and tomatoes.
In skillet, brown bacon, onion and garlic until well cooked.
Add with bacon drippings to bean mixture.
Add seasonings and 2 cups water. Cover; simmer, stirring occasionally for 1 hour.
Add additional water, 1/2 cup at a time during cooking.
The amount depends on desired consistency.
Yields about 6 cups of soup.

title: crock-pot roast
directions: Rinse the roast in cold water and dry with paper towels.
Heat butter in a skillet over medium-high heat until it melts.
Brown the roast on all sides.
Place roast and any pan drippings in the crock-pot.
Cover with the water.
Add the bay leaves.
Cover the pot and cook on low for at least 8 hours.
You can use higher heat for a shorter cook time; however, the slower the meat cooks the better the flavor and tenderness will be.

title: pretzel jello mold
directions: Mix crushed pretzels with 3 tablespoons sugar and melted butter.
Put on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Press firmly. Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Let cool.
Beat cream cheese and 1 cup sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread on top of pretzel layer.
Let set in refrigerator for at least 15 minutes.
Dissolve strawberry Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Stir in frozen strawberries.
Let set for 10 minutes, then pour on top of cream cheese layer.
Chill until set.

title: raspberry cranberry sauce ring
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in the boiling water.
Stir until dissolved. Add your cranberry sauce. Stir until sauce is dissolved.
Add undrained pineapple.
Put sauce in refrigerator until jelly.
Put half of the mixture in the mold, leaving the other half at room temperature.
When the mold is thick, spread the sour cream on it and add the remaining jello in the mold.
Refrigerate until set.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix and make into small balls and mash with a fork.
Bake at 325° for 13 minutes.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: pepperoni triangles
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Lay down 1 phyllo sheet.
Brush with butter.
Repeat with second and third sheet, buttering each. Cut down short side.
Place 1 teaspoon filling at base.
Roll up as a flag; brush with butter.
Seal edges.
Bake at
375° for 10 minutes or until brown.

title: spring cake
directions: Mix each pkg. of cake mix by directions and add one box of dry jello mix to each cake mix.
Blend well.
Bake each cake in separate pan.
Let cool and place on top of each other.
Spread icing on cake and spray with icing spray for color.
Serve and enjoy.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil together the water, margarine, onions and broccoli for 3 minutes.
Add rice.
Take off burner and cover for 5 minutes.
Add soup and Cheez Whiz.
Pour in greased casserole.
Bake 30 minutes, covered, and 10 minutes, uncovered.

title: zucchini creole
directions: Cook zucchini until tender-crisp; drain and set aside.
In a large saucepan, melt butter and stir in flour.
Add tomatoes, pepper and onion.
Stir in salt, brown sugar, bay leaf and cloves; cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Place zucchini in a greased casserole dish.
Pour vegetable mixture over the top.
Cover with bread crumbs and dot lightly with butter or grated cheese.
Bake at 350° fo 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Use with fish or sandwiches.

title: wonderful vegetable dip
directions: Mix together.
Make day ahead to season.
Serve with vegetables cut into bite-sized pieces.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Mix ingredients together. Add about 2 cans of water.
Add 1 tablespoon chili powder.
Cook 2 hours over low heat.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese in a large bowl.
Fry sausage and onion; drain. Add sausage onion mixture and Ro-Tel to melted cheese.
Mix well. Can be used with nachos or regular chips.

title: salmon pate
directions: Mix all ingredients except parsley.
Line mold or bowl with Saran Wrap (to make unmolding easier).
Pack salmon mixture into mold.
Put in refrigerator overnight; unmold.
Cover outside with chopped parsley.
Serve with crackers.

title: pineapple cake pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg yolks, beat.
Add pineapple. Dissolve cornstarch in milk, add to mixture and mix.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake until brown and firm in the center.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and top with mild Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with your favorite crackers and serve as an hors d'oeuvre or snack.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: This makes enough for 2 pies.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or so.

title: red velvet cake and frosting
directions: Make a paste of cocoa and vinegar; set aside.
Cream sugar and buttermilk.
Add eggs and beat until very fluffy.
Add paste. Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Add buttermilk and sugar mixture, vanilla, food coloring and flour to batter.
Add flour, a little at a time, mixing well after each addition until all is used.
Bake at 350° in 9 x 12-inch pan or two 9-inch round pans for 30 minutes.

title: salmon special
directions: Mash salmon thoroughly.
Add onion.
Beat 3 eggs and add milk to eggs.
Mix. Combine bread crumbs, salmon, egg mixture and most of cheese.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour in casserole.
Dot with remainder of cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 300°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: austrian apple strudel
directions: Put large linen cloth or large new cheesecloth on table for rolling up strudel.

title: sunshine barbecue chicken
directions: You will need 1 Reynolds oven bag (large size, 14 x 20-inch).

title: icebox salad
directions: Mix well drained vegetables together. Mix sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil.
Cool slightly and pour over vegetables.
Serve cold with slotted spoon.
Refrigerate.
(This will keep up to a week.)

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix egg yolks and milk, slowly add lime juice while stirring briskly.
Poor into crust and bake at 350 degrees for 12-15 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: stir-fry seafood
directions: Heat seafood in oil in skillet or wok.
Add frozen vegetables. Cook 5 to 10 minutes until done.
Add seasoning; stir well.

title: crazy cake and frosting
directions: Sift together in cake pan the flour, cocoa, salt, sugar and vanilla.
Make 6 wells.
Put into wells the oil, vanilla and vinegar.
Pour over the cold water.
Mix with a fork.
Bake 40 minutes at 350° in 9 x 13 pan.

title: magic rainbow cookie bars
directions: Preheat the oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumbs. Top with remaining ingredients.
Press down firmly. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool. Chill, if desired.
Cut into bars.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.
Makes 24 to 36 bars.

title: savory spiced vegetables
directions: In a medium skillet, heat oil over low heat.
Add onion, garlic and curry powder.
Cook until tender, stirring frequently. Blend in tomatoes and raisins. Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Mix in potatoes and green beans; cover and heat through.
Season to taste with salt and pepper, if desired. Serves 4.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour and cocoa together.
Add to butter mixture.
Fold in coconut and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
While cake is still hot, spread on top the Marshmallow Creme.
Cool cake.
Frost.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour well.
Beat eggs and add to sugar mix.
Add milk and stir well.
Pour over fruit.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fruit casserole
directions: Preheat the casserole dish
with
stick of margarine in it. Mix in another bowl:
1 cup flour,	1 cup sugar and 1 cup milk. Stir these 3 ingredients well
and	then
pour into the casserole dish over the margarine.
Do
not
stir at any time. Put fruit in dish on top of
the
batter.
Bake	30 minutes at 325° to 350°.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Put lutefish in a glass oven dish with a little water.
Cover with wax paper.
Turn microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Then check with a fork it it's flaky.
If not, put in a few minutes and check again.
When done, drain off water.

title: spicy pumpkin cookies
directions: In an extra large mixing bowl, beat together the shortening and sugar with an electric mixer until fluffy.
Add pumpkin and egg; beat until combined.
In another bowl, combine flour, pumpkin pie spice, baking powder and baking soda; beat into the pumpkin mixture until combined.
Spoon by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake in a 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes, or until the tops seem firm.
Remove; cool on wire racks.
Prepare Cookie Glaze; spread over the cookies.
Sprinkle with the chopped nuts, if you like.
Makes 42 to 48 cookies.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream together eggs, sugar and oil.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Peel, remove seeds and grate zucchini.
Add dry ingredients, zucchini, chopped nuts and vanilla to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 7 3/8 x 3 5/8 x 2 1/4-inch loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: party mints
directions: Mix the 2 egg whites with a dash of salt.
Stir in powdered sugar with a fork until mixture is pretty stiff, then add 2 tablespoons cream and peppermint to taste.
Separate into 2 batches and make 2 different colors (2 drops for green or pink, 1 drop for yellow or leave mixture white).
Mix well.

title: microwave steamed fish
directions: Place water, salt and pounded ginger in dish.
Place fish on top of this after cutting 3 to 4 slices across top of fish.
Cover with waxed paper.
Microwave on High for 10 minutes.
Let fish stand 5 minutes.
Sprinkle green onion and slivered ginger on top of fish.
Heat oil with garlic until garlic browns lightly.
Pour over fish and serve.

title: ranch cheese ball
directions: Mix cream
cheese
(room temperature) and seasoning mix well. Roll mixture in chopped pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: cinnamon swirl cake
directions: Mix all ingredients for 10 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
On top of cake, sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Take knife and swirl around into cake.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: spicy pasta primavera
directions: Cook pasta with a splash of vegetable oil and salt.
Set aside.
In a large hot skillet, saute the vegetables, except the onions, garlic, and herbs in small portions using olive oil so that is is easy to turn them with a spatula.
Do not overcook the vegetables, they should be crunchy.
Set aside each batch of vegetables until the remainder is cooked.
Keep the skillet hot and turn the vegetables frequently so they cook evenly but do not burn.
Saute the onions, garlic, oregano, and basil.
Add the already sauteed vegetables; stirring and mixing them constantly. Add the bouillon, salt, and pepper.
Once the vegetables are ready, mix them with the pasta, stirring together and serve.

title: butternut squash pudding
directions: Peel, seed and slice the squash.
Steam in small amount of water until tender.
Drain and mash with fork until no lumps are left.
While squash is hot, add butter and let melt.
Add all ingredients and
mix well.
Pour into a greased baking dish and bake about 30 minutes at 350° or just until pudding is congealed. Serve warm.
Makes about 6 servings.
Pumpkin or sweet potatoes may be used.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Combine all ingredients except shrimp in crock-pot; stir to blend well.
Cover; cook on low 7 to 9 hours (high 3 to 4 hours). During last hour, turn crock-pot to high and add shrimp.
Cook 1 hour or until shrimp turn pink.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and strain.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix remainder of ingredients together; pour over sausage.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: funnel cake
directions: Fry in 1 in shortening until brown.
Cover with powdered sugar.

title: no fail divinity
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup, water and salt in 2 qt. casserole dish.
Cook in microwave oven for 19 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Roll into small balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes and then 375° for 10 minutes.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: Let cream cheese reach room temperature. Mix cream cheese in bowl until smooth; add sour cream, vanilla and sugar until smooth. Fold in Cool Whip with spoon until all ingredients are mixed well. Pour into 2 graham cracker crust pie pans and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: miniature pecan pies
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and margarine in large saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Beat eggs in gradually to syrup mixture.
Add salt and vanilla.

title: bacon bites
directions: Grease a baking sheet.
Layer bacon, cheese and optional onion.
In bowl, mix baking mix, milk, eggs and pepper until smooth.
Pour over bacon and cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° until golden brown (about 30 minutes).
Cut into bite-sized squares.
Serve warm.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together except oil.
Mix well and shape into balls. Fry meatballs in oil until browned. Drain and add to your favorite spaghetti sauce and serve over pasta.
Meatballs can be frozen raw or cooked for later use.

title: mounds cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions on box, making two 8-inch or 9-inch layers.
Let cool.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: In an 8 x 4-inch glass baking pan, combine the ground beef, milk, egg, soup mix and salt.
Mix well (mixture will be very moist).
Press evenly in pan.
Combine the brown sugar, mustard and catsup; spoon and spread over top of meat.
Cook, covered with wax paper, 8 minutes or until center is done.
Let stand, covered with the wax paper, for 5 minutes to finish cooking.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: pul-ku kee
directions: Place sirloin in the freezer until slightly frozen.
Slice diagonally across the grain, paper thin.
Mix the rest of the ingredients in a bowl and pour over the meat.
Marinate overnight. Put slices on a broiler pan.
Broil 1 to 2 minutes; do not turn.

title: cherry delight
directions: Combine all together except Cool Whip.
Fold in Cool Whip last.
Mix well.
Chill before serving.

title: "pilgrim pines" coconut cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift the flour, soda, baking powder and salt and add to the creamed mixture.
Add the vanilla, then stir in the oats and coconut.
Drop by teaspoonsful on greased cookie sheet. Bake until golden brown, about 12 minutes,
in a 350° oven.
Makes at least 6 dozen cookies.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Make jello with lemon juice.
Start jelling and then add other ingredients.
Put in square 8-inch Pyrex or glass dish.
A doubled recipe fits perfectly in a 9 x 13 dish.
Lasts well for several days in refrigerator.

title: sweet potato pie(makes one 9-inch pie)
directions: Take an overflowing measure of cheerfulness and add the milk of human kindness.
Leaven with constantly rising good spirits and fold in plenty of patience.
Season with common sense and a lot of laughter.
Do not let the mixture stand, but stir continuously in the cup of your life.
When ready, bake in the warmth of your heart over a high flame of faith.
Do not cover with icing of selfishness or indifference.
Instead, spread thickly with love and serve large and generous portions daily to your family and friends.

title: calico bean bake
directions: In a large skillet, cook bacon, beef and onion until meat is browned and onion is tender. Drain off fat. In a 3-quart casserole or bean pot, combine the 3 beans, brown sugar, water, ketchup, vinegar and mustard. Stir in meat mixture until well combined. Cover the casserole or bean pot. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes until heated through. Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: oven-fried chicken chimichangas
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; set aside.

Wrap tortillas in damp paper towels and microwave at High for 15 second or until hot. Brush both sides of tortillas, one at a time, with vegetable oil. Place 1/2 cup chicken mixture just below center of each tortilla. Fold in left and right sides of tortilla to partially enclose filling.
Fold up bottom edge of tortilla; fold into a rectangle and place, seam side down, on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes or until crisp.
Serve with shredded lettuce, sour cream, salsa and cheese.

title: chili stacks
directions: Brown ground beef in oil.
Add salt, chili powder, oregano, minced onion and tomato sauce.
Simmer together for 10 minutes. Layer a soft corn or flour tortilla with meat sauce, then cheese. Repeat 2 times, making a stack containing 3 tortillas with meat and cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven until hot and melty (10 to 15 minutes).
Cut into wedges.
Makes 2 stacks (4 servings).

title: chicken eden isle
directions: Cover bottom of 9 x 1-inch Pyrex dish with dried beef.
Wrap chicken with bacon strips.
Place chicken on top of beef.
Pepper (do not salt).
Combine soup, cream cheese and sour cream.
Mix and pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 325° for 2 hours. Uncover and bake until sauce browns.
Serve over rice.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Peel and dice apples.
Mix and let stand apples and sugar 1 hour.
Stir often.
Add dry ingredients to apples.
Add oil, vanilla and eggs.
Stir by hand.
Bake in greased and floured tube cake pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes in 350° oven.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix boiling water and oats; let stand for 20 minutes.
Cream together shortening and sugars.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add oat mixture.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 275° for 35 to 45 minutes.
While still warm, put topping on cake and return to oven to broil for about 5 minutes.

title: church supper special
directions: Mix crumbs, sugar and butter in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press onto bottom; chill.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water, chill until slightly thickened.
Melt marshmallows in milk over low heat, stirring constantly.
Cool thoroughly.
Arrange banana slices in a single layer on the crumb base.
Blend whipped topping into the cool melted marshmallows.
Swirl slightly into the thickened gelatin for marbled effect.
Pour over banana slices.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.
Makes 20 servings.

title: strawberry fig preserves
directions: Mash figs with potato masher and mix in pan with sugar and gelatin.
Bring to a boil and cook for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Seal in jars . Yield: 2 1/2 pints.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream margarine until soft and smooth.
Slowly add brown sugar and white sugar.
Add peanut butter and continue creaming until fluffy.
Add egg and stir until smooth.
Add dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Shape into balls the size of a walnut and place on a greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Stir sugar, cocoa, salt, milk and vanilla together in 1 1/2-quart casserole or Pyrex dish until partially blended.
Put butter over top in center of dish.
Place in microwave and cook about 2 minutes.
Stir until smooth.
Pour into buttered pan. Chill 1 hour in refrigerator.
Cut into squares.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken, reserve stock.
Debone and skin and cut into bite-size pieces.
Mix chicken, onion, celery, bell pepper, garlic and set aside.
Mix soups, tomatoes, chili powder, cumin and salt. Soak corn tortillas and line bottom of casserole dish.
Layer chicken mixture and soup mixture with corn tortillas.
Top with flour tortillas.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with cheese. Serve with side of jalapeno peppers.

title: frosted brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat shortening and chocolate in 2-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly until melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Stir in remaining ingredients except frosting.
Spread in a greased square pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
Bake until brownies begin to pull away from sides of pan (30 to 35 minutes).
Cool slightly.
Frost with Easy Chocolate Frosting.
Cut into about 2-inch squares.
Yields 16 brownies.

title: peppermint patties
directions: In a bowl, combine first four ingredients.
Add milk and mix well.
Roll into 1-inch balls and place on a waxed paper-lined cookie sheet.
Chill 20 minutes.
Flatten with a glass to 1/4-inch; chill for 30 minutes.
In a double boiler or microwave safe bowl, melt chocolate chips and shortening.
Yield:
about 5 dozen.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix shortening, eggs, water and milk.
Sift dry ingredients. Mix all ingredients well.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: baked chicken wings
directions: Soak wings in salted water for 1 hour. Rinse and pat dry. Place wings in large bowl and add mixture of brown sugar, soy sauce, and garlic. Cover and refrigerate over night.
Put wings in baking dish and bake uncovered 1 hour at 350°.

title: cauliflower, broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar and pour over the first 5 ingredients; mix and add cashews before serving.

title: 7-layer salad
directions: Layer each item, starting with the first one to the last. Don't mix.
Cover with Saran Wrap.
Refrigerate overnight.
Then ready to eat the next day.
Very good.

title: glazed carrots with five spices
directions: In a heavy 10-inch skillet, bring the water to a boil and add the carrots, cinnamon stick, cumin, ginger, coriander and cayenne pepper.
Adjust the heat so that the liquid bubbles gently, cover and simmer for 12 minutes.
Uncover, add the honey and lemon juice, raise the heat to high and boil until all the liquid has evaporated and the carrots are just tender, about 4 minutes. Serves 4.
You can serve these carrots at room temperature as well as hot.

title: pears glazed with maple syrup
directions: In a chilled mixing bowl, combine cream and cardamon and whip until cream holds soft peaks.
Refrigerate, covered.
Quarter, core and peel pears.
Cut quarters in half and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Melt butter in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Arrange pears in skillet and cook on one side until pears just begin to brown, about 3 minutes.
Add maple syrup and cook for another minute.
Remove from heat and allow pears to cool slightly.
Transfer to serving bowls and serve warm topped with whipped cream.

title: frog eye salad
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together in large bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients and chill for at least 2 hours or overnight.

title: light fettuccine alfredo
directions: In medium saucepan over medium-high heat, whisk milk, garlic, flour and cream cheese.
Bring to boil, whisking constantly. Reduce heat and simmer for 2 minutes or until thick.
Add Parmesan, whisk until blended.
Remove from heat.
Stir in melted butter.
Add 1 pound cooked shrimp or chicken, if desired.
Pour over hot fettuccine.
Sprinkle with parsley and pepper, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Mix Crisco, sugar, salt and 1 cup boiling water.
Mix yeast dissolved in 1 cup lukewarm water.
Add to mixture.
Add eggs and 2 cups of flour; mix.
Add the other 4 cups of flour. Let rise 1 hour.
Punch.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Roll out.
Cut, rub top with melted butter and let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 425° until golden brown.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Mix all ingredients.
Shape into small balls and bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.
Serve warm.

title: veggie squares
directions: Finely chop all veggies; unroll crescent rolls.
Spread on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool. Mix cream cheese, cottage cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing; mix well.
Spread mix on top of dough.
Top with veggies. Refrigerate at least 4 to 5 hours.
Cut into squares.

title: christmas cheese ball
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together well. Form into a ball and chill in freezer 20 to 30 minutes. Remove and roll in crushed nuts. Put in freezer until 1 1/2 hours before serving.

title: chocolate chiffon cake
directions: Dissolve cocoa in boiling water.
Cool.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add oil, egg yolks, cocoa mixture and vanilla.
Mix well.
Combine egg whites and cream of tartar; beat until stiff peaks form.
Fold egg yolk mixture into egg whites.
Pour into 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Put Fudge Topping on cake (see recipe).

title: chocolate pudding shake
directions: Pour milk, pudding and ice cream into shaker cup or put in blender; shake for one minute or until creamy.
Pour into glass and enjoy.

title: lillie's creole chicken casserole
directions: Mix rice, liquid and seasoning in 2-quart casserole dish.
Put layer of chicken strips on top of rice.
Cover each strip with Creole tomatoes.
Add another layer of chicken, then tomatoes. Use all of chicken and tomatoes.
Arrangement depends on casserole shape.
Be sure chicken has liquid on each piece.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
You may need to add a little more water or V-8 juice, if rice is too dry.
Serve with slaw and hot rolls.

title: chile rellenos casserole
directions: Trim crusts from bread.
Place buttered side down in 11 x 7 x 2-inch dish.
Top with chiles and cheese.
Beat eggs until frothy. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour over casserole.
Cover and chill overnight (for at least 4 hours).
Uncover and bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes until lightly browned.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Makes six servings.

title: smothered pheasant
directions: Clean pheasant, use little water as possible.
Cut up as for frying.
Combine 2 1/2 teaspoons flour, salt and pepper.
Place in paper bag with pieces of pheasant; shake bag until meat is well coated.
Melt butter in Dutch oven or covered skillet.
Brown pheasant in this.
Pour sour cream mixed with remaining salt over meat.
Cover and bake for 2 hours until tender.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with crackers.

title: sea shells salad
directions: Pile salad ingredients in a mixing bowl as you prepare them. Combine salad ingredients, taste and adjust seasonings. Serve salad on bed of lettuce leaves. Yield: 4 servings.

title: crab dip
directions: Spread cheese on meat platter; cover with thin coat of sauce. Sprinkle crab meat on top.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: veal-chicken marsala
directions: Flour chicken or veal.
Pan-fry in oil to brown on both sides. Place in roasting pan and sprinkle with paprika.

title: chicken tostadas
directions: Toss chicken in salsa.
Let set in refrigerator for 1 hour, then spread shells with cream cheese.
Spread chicken over cheese. Top with lettuce, tomato and cheese.
Serve with hot sauce and jalapenos.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt butter and cocoa together.
Remove from heat; stir in sugar and beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Add flour, salt, chopped nuts and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: In a large Dutch oven, over medium heat, cook sausages until well browned.
Remove and cool slightly.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices. Or use ground flavored sausage and break apart while cooking. Remove fat and add ground beef and garlic.
Cook until browned. Return sausage to skillet and add tomatoes, paste, parsley, basil, sugar, oregano leaves and pepper.
Simmer until mixture thickens. (I sometimes use a quart and a half of home canned tomatoes, cooking takes a little longer to thicken.)
Cook lasagna noodles with olive oil as label directs and drain.
In a medium bowl, beat eggs.
Add Ricotta cheese.
(I have used cottage cheese pureed in food blender.)
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease two 13 x 9-inch baking pans.
Thinly slice Mozzarella.

title: yummy potatoes
directions: Mix and put into a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Top with crushed cornflakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: vegibars
directions: Spread crescent rolls in pan.
Bake according to directions and cool.

title: pear preserves
directions: Mix altogether and cook to desired thickness of syrup.

title: fried dill pickles
directions: Mix beaten egg with milk, Worcestershire, Tabasco and 1 tablespoon flour.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix 2 cups flour with salt and pepper to taste in a separate bowl.
Dip pickles in egg wash, then in flour and in egg wash again and flour.
Fry in 350° deep fat.
Fry to golden brown.

title: broccoli topped tuna bake
directions: Boil elbow macaroni and drain.
Reserve 1/2 cup of processed cheese spread.

title: triple treat bars
directions: Cream margarine and sugars.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Combine flour, soda and salt; gradually add and mix well.
Stir in chips and nuts.

title: crispy chicken supreme
directions: Crush cereal.
Place in shallow dish. Stir in paprika.
Set aside.
In a second dish, beat egg and milk slightly.
Add flour, salt, pepper and seasoning.
Mix until smooth.

Dip chicken in batter. Coat with crushed cereal. Place in single layer, skin side up, in well-greased or foil lined shallow baking pan. Drizzle with melted margarine. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender. Do not cover pan or turn chicken.

title: bacon quiche biscuit cups
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease muffin tins.
Mix first five ingredients.
Place biscuits in tins.
Put half of bacon in. Spoon 2 tablespoons of cheese mixture and rest of bacon.
Bake at 375° for 21 to 26 minutes.

title: english pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Chill before serving.

title: spoon bread ham casserole
directions: Cook the first 2 ingredients until thick like grits.
Add the eggs and salt.
(At this point, the mixture may be left to cool for several hours, or you may continue.)
Add the baking powder and butter.
(Use a shallow baking dish to melt the butter so that it greases the dish, then pour the butter into the mixture.) Cover the bottom of dish with ham and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 8.

title: microwave lasagna
directions: In 2-quart casserole, combine ground beef, sausage and onion. Microwave at High for 5 to 6 minutes or until meat is no longer pink, stirring twice.
Drain.
Add tomato puree, water, Italian seasoning and pepper.
Stir to blend and set aside.

title: heath bar torte
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and press in bottom of a 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Beat the egg whites with the cream of tartar, then add the sugar and beat.
Pour over the crust mixture; bake for an hour at 250°.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pineapple and juice, pistachio and coconut together.
Stir in Cool Whip and add nuts.
Mix well.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: sheath cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar together in a large bowl.
Put margarine, Crisco, cocoa and water in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil and pour over flour; add buttermilk, eggs, soda, cinnamon and vanilla.
Mix well; pour batter in a large greased pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: delicious ribs
directions: Cook ribs side down for 1 hour at 325°.
Cover loosely with foil and bake an additional 30 minutes.
Drain pan.
Pour sauce over ribs.
Cover loosely and bake 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter chews
directions: Put corn flakes in a very large bowl.
Cook sugar and syrup until it boils.
Remove form heat and add peanut butter and margarine.
Pour over corn flakes and mix.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper and cool.

title: homemade caramel corn
directions: Remove any unpopped kernels of corn from popcorn.
Add peanuts. Set aside.
Bring brown sugar, butter, corn syrup and salt to a boil in a super pot cooker at 250° (or you may use a heavy deep skillet or saucepan).
Continue boiling for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Turn off heat; quickly stir in baking soda.
Add popcorn and peanuts.
Gently combine with caramel.
Divide caramel corn mixture equally between two buttered 9 x 9 x 2-inch or 23 x 23 x 5-inch square cake pans.
Place in preheated 250° oven and bake for one hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and immediately spread out on wax paper to cool.
Yields 4 quarts.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Trim all fat from roast.
Brown in Dutch oven with a little oil.
Combine all ingredients.
Put meat in a heavy roasting pan, pour sauce over it and cover.
Bake at 350° for 3 to 4 hours. Remove meat and shred with fork and return to sauce.
For a little spicier version, add the sliced green bell pepper when you bake the roast.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix jello, sugar and cornstarch first.
Then add water; cook until mixture thickens.
Add margarine.
Cool before pouring over berries in pie crust.
Refrigerate until jello sets.

title: vegetable soup
directions: In
medium
size
saucepan
over medium heat, heat oil. Add onions
and
garlic;
cook,
stirring
frequently, 2 to 3 minutes or until soft.
Add tomatoes with their juice, chicken broth, carrots, celery, parsley, basil and pepper.
Bring to a boil. Reduce
heat;
cover
and
simmer 20 minutes.
Add lima beans
and water.
Bring
to	a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 20 minutes or until beans are tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: no-fuss chicken
directions: In a bowl, combine dressing, preserves and soup mix. Place chicken in ungreased baking pan. Top with dressing mixture. Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes; baste. Bake uncovered 20 minutes longer or until chicken juices run clear. Makes 8 servings.

title: seafood soup(makes 10 to 12 servings)
directions: In large soup pot, combine beef broth, water, onion and Old Bay seasoning.
Bring to a boil.
Add tomatoes, mixed vegetables and potatoes.
Simmer 1 1/2 more hours.

title: cranberry crunch
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix oats, flour and brown sugar.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Place half of this mixture in an 8 x 8-inch greased cake pan.
Cover with cranberry sauce.
Top with balance of mixture.
Bake 45 minutes.
Cut in squares.
Serve warm or cold with ice cream or whipped cream.
Delicious.

title: mistry drops
directions: Boil sugar and milk for 3 minutes.
Add other ingredients. Stir and drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°.
When 5 minutes are left, sprinkle with cheese.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, nuts and melted margarine and spread in rectangular pan with fingers.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Blend powdered sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Spread over baked crust.
Mix instant puddings and milk.
Spoon over cream cheese layer.
Spread remaining large Cool Whip on top of pudding layer.
Sprinkle with grated Hershey bar.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut
cabbage as you would to smother and boil in salted water until
tender,
but still green.
Drain and reserve the liquid. Melt
the
margarine in a deep skillet and fry ground meat	with onions,
garlic
and
seasonings until brown.
Mix cabbage	with the meat, adding mushroom soup, green onion tops and
boiled rice.
Pour
onto
greased baking dish.
Top with bread crumbs and
bake
for 20 to 30 minutes at 300°.
Before baking, if
you think it is too dry, you can then add some of the
water
from the boiled cabbage or another can of mushroom soup.

title: corned beef barbecue
directions: Brown corned beef, green pepper and onion in melted shortening.
Stir in all remaining ingredients.
Cover.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Spoon mixture into hamburger buns.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: beef and cabbage casserole
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Add onion and cook until tender. Stir in rice, tomato soup, water, salt and paprika. Cook for 5 minutes.
Place cabbage on bottom of greased 2-quart baking dish. Pour meat mixture over cabbage and cover.
Bake in oven for 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sausage - rice casserole
directions: Cook the sausage, green peppers and onions until sausage is browned, drain.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl, pour into 9 x 13 baking dish.
Bake 350 for 30 minutes.

title: mary's zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla until thick.
Combine flour, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and baking powder; add with remaining ingredients.
Makes 2 loaves or you can use a pound cake pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes to an hour.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine hamburger, apricot preserves, eggs and bread crumbs together.
Roll into balls.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan; bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Drain juice.
Pour barbecue sauce over meatballs.
Cook until bubbly.
Great to put in crock-pot after the first 20 minutes on low for several hours.

title: blueberry cinnamon cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together until light.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt. Add to the creamed mixture alternately with milk, beating until smooth.
Fold in the blueberries.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish; sprinkle with a mixture of the 4 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve warm.

title: chicken divan
directions: *May use enough fresh broccoli to cover bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: chocolate mint dip for strawberries
directions: Rinse strawberries and pat dry with paper towels.
Set aside. Whisk other ingredients to blend thoroughly.
Each recipe makes 3/4 cup of dip, enough for 6 servings.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix crab, onion, eggs, green pepper, mustard, cream, cayenne and bread crumbs.
Form into 8 cakes; roll in bread crumbs.
Fry until brown.
These freeze well.

title: double chocolate crinkles
directions: In a double boiler, melt chocolate and shortening. When melted, stir in sugar. Place mixture in a medium bowl. Cool. Beat until well blended. Add vanilla. Beat in eggs one at a time, mixing well after each addition. In another medium bowl, sift flour, baking powder and salt together. Stir flour mixture into chocolate mixture. Stir in chocolate chips. Refrigerate dough several hours or overnight. Break off small pieces of chilled dough and form into 1 inch
balls. Roll balls in powdered sugar, covering completely. Place balls 2 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet. Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 10 minutes.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: In large bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla. Pour into prepared crust.
Chill 3 hours or until set.
Top with desired amount of pie filling before serving.

title: texas hash
directions: Cook ground beef until slightly brown.
Cut onion and cook with beef for three minutes.
Drain grease drippings off.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add chili powder, tomatoes, rice, ketchup and mustard.
Put in casserole dish and cover.
Bake for 45 minutes. Uncover and put grated cheese on top.
Put back in oven until cheese is melted.

title: miriam's fish in cream
directions: Lay parsley in baking dish; add lemon slices.
Place fish on top.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake at 400° until tender. Mix sour cream and onion soup mix; spread over fish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Broil until cream is slightly brown and bubbly (usually less than 5 minutes).
Serve hot.

title: chocolate bonbons
directions: Pour butter over coconut.
Add next 2 ingredients and mix well.
Add powdered sugar.
Mix well and form into small balls. Chill balls.
Remove from refrigerator and dip individually into chocolate coating.
Place on wax paper to cool.

title: biscuit rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup of lukewarm water.
Combine dry ingredients and cut into Crisco.
Stir in yeast and buttermilk. Roll out and cut.
Let rise or you can cook when first made. Dough may be covered and kept in refrigerator a week or longer. Use as needed.
Bake at 450°.
This is an old recipe.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies fine in food processor.
Blend margarine, cream cheese and sugar together.
Mix milk with pudding mix.
Mix pudding with cream cheese mixture until smooth.
Add Cool Whip and gently fold together.
Put a layer of crushed cookies in bottom of pot, then a layer of filling.
Alternate layers, ending with cookies to resemble potting soil.
Place artificial flower in center after refrigerating for at least 4 hours.
Can be frozen.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Blend
sugar,
flour,
milk,
vanilla
and baking powder together well (use blender).
Melt margarine in casserole dish. Pour
flour
mixture over melted margarine.
Pour fruit on top. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix together and set overnight.

title: apple pie filling
directions: Peel apples and chop.
Add sugar and vinegar; cook until thick on low heat, stirring to keep from sticking.
Put in jars and seal.

title: old-fashioned tea cakes
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and milk.
Mix all ingredients well. Turn out on floured surface and roll to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake about 15 minutes at 375° or until lightly browned.

title: spanish omelette
directions: Heat oil in a nonstick frying pan and saute onion, carrot and green pepper, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Add zucchini and cook for another 5 minutes.
Add garlic and eggs to the vegetables and season with salt and pepper.
Stir gently until the omelette starts to set.
When the omelette is set underneath, put it under the broiler to set the top.
Do not let it get too firm or it will be rubbery.
Cut the omelette in 1/2 and serve immediately.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar, beaten egg yolks and salt together in pan.
Stir in water, mixing until smooth.
Cook until smooth and until it thickens.
Add butter, lemon rind and juice; pour into pie shell.

title: cheese puffs with olives
directions: Blend cheese with margarine.
Stir in flour, salt and paprika. Wrap 1 teaspoon mixture around olive.
Freeze.
Take out when frozen.
Bake frozen on ungreased cookie sheet 15 minutes at 400°.

title: stripe it rich cake
directions: Prepare the cake mix as directed on package and bake in a 13 x 9 pan.
Remove the cake from the oven and poke holes at once down through the cake.
After poking holes, combine pudding mix with the sugar and gradually stir in the milk.
Beat at low speed for 1 minute.
Before the pudding thickens, pour about 1/2 the mixture over the cake and into the holes.
Allow the remaining pudding to thicken slightly.
Spoon rest of mixture over the top to frost the cake.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Store in fridge.

title: cheese and grits
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Add Tabasco, garlic salt and pepper to sausage.
Set aside.
Cook grits.
Mix all ingredients well.

title: cappuccino mix
directions: Combine and mix well.
Store in airtight container.
Use 1 tablespoon plus 1 teaspoon to 1 cup hot water.
Yields 33 servings.

title: peachy pie supreme
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, vanilla pudding, oleo, egg and milk in a large bowl.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Arrange peaches over batter in pie pan. Combine cream cheese, powdered sugar and peach juice in a small bowl; beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Spoon mixture over peaches. Combine sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: italian macaroni salad(great substitute for potato salad)
directions: Cook macaroni
according to package directions; mix well. While still hot, toss with Italian dressing; let stand 30 minutes. Add remaining ingredients and chill.
Makes 6 servings.

title: raisin sauce for ham
directions: Cover raisins with water.
Add cloves and simmer 10 minutes. Add sugar, cornstarch, salt and pepper mixed together.
Stir until slightly thickened and add the remaining ingredients.

title: kolaches
directions: Mix in	series	like pie dough.
Leave at room temperature about
hours.
Sprinkle milk lightly on mixture.
Roll dough into
a
ball.
Divide
into two.
Wrap dough in plastic wrap; flatten
like
a
patty and refrigerate.
Dough must be cold to roll out.
Take
out
only a half a patty at a time to roll.
Work dough in hands immediately before rolling to make soft.
Roll dough
on pastry cloth sprinkled with flour.
Cut dough into 2-inch
squares.
Put 1 teaspoon of prune, apricot or strawberry filling in the center of each square.

title: chicken-shrimp tetrazzini
directions: Simmer chicken in water until tender, seasoning with salt to taste. Cool. Remove meat from bones and cut into bite size pieces. Cook vermicelli according to package directions.
