Over low heat, saute onion, garlic, green pepper and celery in butter. Add parsley and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir in chicken, vermicelli, shrimp, soup and tomato sauce.
Turn into greased shallow 2 1/2-quart casserole; top with cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: hobo popcorn
directions: Place 1 teaspoon oil and 1 tablespoon of popcorn in center of square piece of heavy-duty foil.
Using French folds, crease edges of foil to create a pouch.
Seal tightly but allow room for expansion.
Tie pouch to a lengthy stick with sturdy string. Place pouch directly on coals.
Shake constantly until popping ceases.
Season as desired with salt, pepper and butter.

title: cherry torte
directions: Bring cream cheese to room temperature and beat until smooth; beat in sugar gradually.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating hard after each addition.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into crust and bake 25 minutes in preheated 300° oven.
Remove from oven; cool.
Spoon cherry pie filling over top.
Chill in refrigerator for 3 hours.

title: lillie's baked beans
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into 5-quart Dutch oven. Place 4 or 5 slices of bacon on top and bake at 450° until bacon is done.
Or you can place in crock-pot and heat on stove on low heat for approximately 30 minutes.
Do not overcook!

title: pound cake
directions: Bring butter and eggs to room temperature.
In a mixing bowl, sift together flour and baking powder.
In mixer, beat butter for 30 seconds.
Add sugar to butter, 2 tablespoons at a time, beating on medium to high until light and fluffy.
Beat in vanilla and almond extract.
Add eggs one at a time, beating one minute after each addition.
Gradually add flour mixture to butter mixture, beating on medium speed until combined.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 65 minutes or until cake is done.
Cool on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: easy casserole
directions: Crumble ground round in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Chop onion very fine.
Over this pour the celery
soup (undiluted).
Cover with Tater Tots.
Bake 1 hour at 350°

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle coconut and nuts evenly over bottom of pan (can also add chocolate chips).
Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Blend margarine, cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Pour or spread evenly over top of uncooked cake.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add milk, eggs, butter and potatoes. Beat until smooth.
Put in pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Cook until done.

title: candy strawberries
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill 24 hours.
Form in shape of strawberries.
Roll in red sugar.
Add artificial green stem, if desired.

title: breakfast sausage balls
directions: Mix and roll into balls (size of half dollars).
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° in the oven for 15 minutes, or until browned lightly.
Makes 2 1/2 to 3 dozen.

title: glorified oven baked chicken
directions: In skillet, heat shortening or oil.
Brown chicken pieces until golden.
Remove from pan and place in a greased baking dish. Add soup.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven until tender, 45 to 60 minutes.

title: shoe peg vegetable salad
directions: Cook sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper until sugar is dissolved.
Cool and pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Will keep for 2 to 3 weeks.

title: microwave seafoam
directions: Combine sugars, syrup, water and salt.
Microwave on High in glass casserole for 5 minutes.
Stir.
Place back in microwave on High for 9 minutes.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar in mixer bowl until stiff peaks form.
Pour hot syrup mixture over egg whites.
Add vanilla.
Beat until mixture holds its shape and loses its gloss.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Top with pecan half, if desired.

title: rocky road fudge brownies
directions: Prepare mix as directed on package.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes in a 13x9x2 inch pan.
Sprinkle marshmallows over hot brownies.
Mix chocolate, milk, and butter in pan; heat until butter melts.
In a bowl mix the chocolate mixture with powdered sugar and spread over marshmallows.
Cool in pan.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: pasta salad
directions: Whip Miracle Whip, milk, sugar and vinegar together.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour over macaroni shells and toss; let chill.

title: fettucini italiano
directions: Prepare fettucini according to package directions. Drain. Gradually add milk
to combine salad dressing and garlic in small saucepan.
Heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat; blend in egg. Toss with hot fettucini until well coated. Add remaining ingredients; toss lightly. Garnish with basil leaves, if desired.
Makes 5 servings.

title: french dressing
directions: Blend well all ingredients (in blender) and serve.

title: marcia davees' icebox angel food cake
directions: Mix the milk, sugar and room temperature cream cheese until smooth.
Mix in the strawberry pie filling and Cool Whip and blend well.
Pinch the angel food cake in bite size pieces and put into a large bowl.
Add the pie filling mixture and mix well.
Store in the refrigerator.

title: "hot" chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer 5 to 6 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Add a little water, if too thick.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Saute green pepper and mushrooms in butter until tender. Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Add veggies and stir until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add chicken broth and half and half.
Cook over medium heat; stir constantly, until thickened and heated thoroughly.
Divide filling evenly between patty shells.
Yields 2 servings.

title: chocolate nut pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, corn syrup, butter and vanilla. Spread chocolate chips and pecans over bottom of unbaked deep dish pie shell.
Pour egg mixture over chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
(Cover edge of crust with aluminum foil for part of the baking time if edges are getting too brown.)

title: love cake for mother
directions: Mix well, bake in a hearty warm oven and serve to mother everyday.
She ought to have it in big slices.
Yields: happiness. "We may be sure we are not pleasing God if we are not happy ourselves."

title: ambrosia mold
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add cold water to the juice to measure 1 cup.
Stir boiling water into gelatin in a large bowl until completely dissolved.
Stir in measured liquid.
Refrigerate about 1 1/4 hours or until slightly thickened.
Stir in whipped topping with wire whisk until smooth; refrigerate 10 minutes or until mixture will mound.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Spoon into a 6-cup mold.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until firm.
Makes 10 servings.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed on package in a 9 x 13-inch pan lined with wax paper that has been greased and floured.
Remove from pan when cool.
Slice cake into 2 layers.

title: chow chow
directions: After cutting the tomatoes, put in a cloth sack, squeeze all the juice you can get out before cooking.
Then cut cabbage, onions and peppers.
Mix with the uncooked tomatoes.
Add 1 teaspoon salt.
Mix well.
Pour vinegar just enough to cover tomatoes.
Cook only until tomatoes change color.
You should not have any juice in them.
Pack in jars and seal.
You can use more seasoning if it doesn't taste like you want it to.

title: butterscotch brownies sugar-free
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set oven at 350°.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Mix all ingredients together.
Spread into pan and bake.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef with chopped onion.
Drain grease.
Add spaghetti sauce.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer ingredients, beginning with meat sauce, then noodles, then cottage cheese and then Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers two or three times. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Add 1 tablespoon water to each corner.
Cover with foil and bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours. Take off the foil for the last 15 minutes.

title: french onion soup
directions: Melt butter in large pot.
Cook onions until tender; add wine and boil 3 to 4 minutes.
Add broth, water, Worcestershire sauce and Gravy Master.
Cover and cook 1 hour.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and blend thoroughly. Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle dry cake mix over batter. Pour melted oleo over cake mix. Top with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Better to overbake, than underbake. Serve with whipped cream.

title: sweet mountain baked ham
directions: Combine cocktail sauce, brown sugar and mustard in baking dish.
Fold in ham until well covered with mixture.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes (until mixture boils). Let cool 5 minutes and serve warm.
Serve cool the next day over white bread.
Makes a great cold sandwich.
Serves 4.
Delicious!

title: chiey (chi)
directions: Put the water in a pot until it boils.
Remove from heat and fill a cup 1/2 full.
Fill to top of cup with milk.
Put a tea bag in cup and keep in until it turns brown.
Put in one teaspoon sugar, then stir.
Eureka - You're done.

title: english pea salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, salt, pepper and onion.
Add peas, cheese and diced eggs.
Stir gently.
Refrigerate.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together for 5 minutes.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add 2 gallons water and place in freezer for 24 hours.
This will make a slush, therefore you need no ice to serve.
Serves 80.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix well and drop by teaspoons into deep fryer.
Makes about 50.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add eggs, beaten slightly, then add applesauce to which soda has been added. Stir in half of the flour and use the other to flour the nuts and raisins. Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: elsie's sausage casserole
directions: Cook diced potatoes in a small amount of water.
Brown sausage and drain off excess fat.
Add minced onion, mix well and pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish or pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle with paprika and serve.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Prepare jello as usual, adding fruit, applesauce and lemon juice.
Chill and set in refrigerator.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve with fresh vegetable strips.

title: pasta a la calligeros
directions: Make pasta curly noodles according to directions.
While warm, sprinkle with Parmesan.
Mix real good.
Add more Parmesan, so it's all the way through.
Add the dressing (not too much; just enough that it's not dry).
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well and refrigerate a couple hours or overnight.
Enjoy.

title: easy curry
directions: Put meat in a skillet, add water.
Chop and add vegetables according to cooking time needed.
Add spices.
Blend together tomato sauce, milk and cornstarch.
Add to skillet.
Simmer 45 minutes or until vegetables are tender and sauce is thick and glossy.
Stir frequently.
Serve over rice, noodles or biscuits. May top with chopped tomatoes, mixed nuts, coconut or raisins.

title: date nut bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine dates, sugar, honey and butter.
Add very hot water; let stand for 15 minutes.
Preheat oven to 325°. Stir egg and vanilla into date mixture.
In a separate bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Stir the flour mixture into the date mixture.
Pour batter into a greased loaf pan and bake for 1 hour or until a wooden toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool in the pan for 10 minutes, then remove the bread and place it on a wire rack.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: In a bowl sift or mix together well the first 6 ingredients. Set aside.
In a separate large bowl beat together the remaining ingredients.
Gradually add the flour mixture to the pumpkin mixture and beat well.
Spray a 9 x 13 inch baking dish with a non-stick cooking spray.
Pour batter into the dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool pan on a wire rack.
Cool completely before frosting with whipped topping or your favorite frosting.

title: cornbread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together, mixing in liquid ingredients. Pour into 8-inch square pan which has been oiled or sprayed with cooking spray.
Bake at 425° until golden brown.
Yields 8-inch square or round pan.

title: rice balls
directions: Combine hamburger meat, seasonings, rice and 1 cup of tomato sauce with the slightly beaten egg. Mix together well. Roll into 1 1/2 to 2-inch balls and place into large skillet.

title: banana split cake
directions: Put pineapple into strainer to drain while preparing other ingredients.
Melt one stick of butter; mix with graham cracker crumbs.
Press into bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix 2 sticks softened (not melted) butter with eggs and confectioners sugar. Mix for at least 15 minutes.
Spread mixture on top of graham cracker crust.
Slice bananas; place on top of mixture.
Spread pineapple on top of bananas.
Top with Cool Whip and cherries (cut in halves).

title: cornell punch
directions: Ice ring can be made in jello mold with cherries and lemon/lime slices.
Makes 50 to 60 servings.

title: spring brunch punch
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; mix well and chill.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Yields 2 1/2 quarts.

title: rhode island johnnycakes
directions: Stir corn meal and salt into 1 cup boiling water.
Simmer for 10 minutes or until the mixture starts to thicken, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat and add milk gradually, stirring until thickened.
Drop by tablespoonfuls on hot, greased griddle. Serves 7.

title: no egg cake (chocolate)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in greased and floured pans and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Cool and serve plain or put on icing or ice cream.

title: biscuits
directions: Combine flour and soda, mixing well.
Cut in the shortening. Mix until mealy.
Add buttermilk, a little at a time, mixing well in between.
Turn out onto a floured surface.
Roll out and fold up at least twice.
Cut dough to make biscuits of desired size (a cleaned soup can works very well).
Place on a greased baking pan and bake in a 375° oven.
Bake for approximately 15 minutes (until crust is at desired doneness).
This could be more or less than 15 minutes, depending on your oven.

title: peppernuts
directions: You can use all white sugar in this recipe.
Mix the ingredients and roll into ropes.
Cut into 1/2-inch pieces and bake 7 minutes in 400° oven.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix until crumbly the first 5 ingredients.
Press half of the crumbs into a greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with 4 cups diced rhubarb.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Cook until thick and clear.
Pour over rhubarb.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: seafood cocktail dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add horseradish and lemon juice to taste.
Chill well.
Serve with crackers.
Can be made ahead and frozen.

title: lemon cake bars
directions: Mix together.
Beat for 4 minutes.
Bake in jelly roll pan or a 9 x 13-inch cake pan at 350°.

title: mom's toffee squares
directions: Cream butter, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Stir in flour and salt until well blended.
Pat into 13 x 10-inch rectangle on greased pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until browned (will be soft).
Melt chocolate in microwave on 50% power for 1 to 2 minutes. Immediately place melted chocolate on top.
Sprinkle with nuts. Yields 6 to 7 dozen.

title: favorite meat loaf(diabetic recipe)
directions: Dissolve beef bouillon cube in boiling water in a large bowl. Add all other ingredients except tomato sauce and blend well. Bake on a rack in a baking pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook the spaghetti and drain.
Mix all ingredients together. Mix the day before.
This makes a large salad.

title: walnut cheddar ball
directions: Beat Cheddar cheese and cream cheese together until well blended.
Mix in next 4 ingredients.
Chill until firm enough to shape into a ball.
Roll in nuts to coat.
Chill until 1/2 hour before serving.
Serve with Sociables crackers.
Makes 1 (4-inch thick) ball.

title: champagne punch #2
directions: Chill ingredients prior to mixing.
Just before serving, pour ingredients over block of ice and stir well.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer in order given in deep casserole dish; cover.
Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.
To brown topping, remove cover for the last 5 to 10 minutes.
Freezes well.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: brenda's chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until real tender.
Tear off into small pieces. Line a large, buttered casserole dish with chicken pieces.
Pour cream of chicken soup over top, then add milk.
Dampen dressing mix with water or broth.
Sprinkle over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: yummy lettuce salad
directions: Shred lettuce. Finely chop cauliflower. Add chopped onion and crumbled bacon. Mix mayo, sugar and cheese together and add to salad just before serving.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, except cornmeal.
Add cornmeal; combine egg, milk and shortening.
Stir.
Bake 25 minutes at 450°.

title: pear cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately to creamed mixture with pears.
Add raisins and walnuts.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake at 350°.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Mix cocoa and hot water.
Let dissolve.
Add other ingredients. Cook 15 minutes at 350°.
If you don't have sour milk, mix milk with 1 capful of vinegar.

title: lynda's corn casserole
directions: Melt butter on top of stove and add cream cheese.
Drain corn and add to mixture, along with the rest of ingredients (except red pepper).
Put mixture in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with red pepper.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chuck roast in sauce
directions: Marinade meat with first 3 ingredients in shallow dish for 8 hours.
Remove meat and mix marinade with all other ingredients. Pour over roast.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until tender.

title: lemons as "anti-fat agents"
directions: This recipe is taken from a 1911 cookbook:
Use the juice of half a lemon in a glass of hot water, taken just before breakfast, as a successful substitute for Calomel and all other alternative drugs.

When one rises in the morning, headachy and dull, with what "Wang" describes as a "dark brown, fuzzy taste in the mouth and dumb nausea weighing upon the stomach like a forty horse-power nightmare," let one try this prescription, repeating it for two days thereafter.

title: pea casserole
directions: Cook frozen vegetables individually as directed.
Drain.
Add other ingredients.
Place in buttered casserole.
Top with Ritz crackers, crumbled and tossed with 2 to 3 teaspoons of melted butter (1/4 cup butter to 1 1/2 cups Ritz crackers).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: swiss chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Place cheese slices on chicken. Combine cream of chicken soup and milk; pour over chicken. Sprinkle stuffing mix over everything.
Drizzle melted butter over stuffing mix.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: four layer marshmallow bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix cake mix, margarine and water until well blended.
Pat into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Mixture should be fairly stiff, not soupy.
Bake for 20 to 22 minutes. Layer marshmallows, candies and peanuts over crust.
Bake 2 to 3 minutes longer, or until marshmallows begin to melt.
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes 24.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Beat first four ingredients well, then add oil, flour and baking powder. Beat again.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Cook pineapple, sugar and flour until thick.
Set aside and cool.
Line cooled pie crusts with sliced bananas, coconut and nuts.
Pour pineapple mixture over bananas and let stand in refrigerator.
Top with Cool Whip.
Makes 2 pies.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
In chicken broth, cook spaghetti until tender and then drain.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together except half of the nuts.
Shape into 2 balls and roll in the rest of the nuts.
Chill overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: taco layer dip
directions: Mix refried beans and 3 Tbsp. of taco sauce.
In a separate bowl, combine sour cream and 3/4 cup of taco sauce.
Layer the ingredients on a flat dish: bottom layer-refried beans, next layer-combined taco sauce/sour cream mixture.
Then add layers of tomatoes, cheese and onions.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: sugar cake
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm milk.
Add to sugar, salt and mashed potatoes.
Add eggs, 1/4 cup margarine and Crisco.
Mix well.
Add flour to make soft dough.
Knead for a few minutes.
Let rise in greased covered bowl in warm place until doubled.
Spread dough with hand onto large greased pans 1/2 inch thick.
Let it double in size.
Pinch dough with thumb and forefinger at 1 1/2 inch intervals.
Brush on the following which has been mixed:
brown sugar, cinnamon, melted margarine and regular milk.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: frosted party log
directions: Blend in food processor the ham and onions.
Add mayonnaise, raisins and curry powder. Mix well.
Form into 9-inch log on waxed paper.
Cool 1 hour.

title: western casserole
directions: Brown meat in shortening.
Mix meat, onion, bell pepper, tomato sauce, tomato paste and water.
Make a layer of noodles and a layer of meat mixture in casserole dish.
Add layer of corn if desired.
Repeat until ingredients are used.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake about 20 minutes at 325°.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Freeze overnight.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 100 balls.

title: beth's quick enchiladas
directions: Cut burritos lengthwise.
Place open side down in casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Pour 1 can enchilada sauce and 1 can of water over these.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at
400° until hot all through.

title: marge's shrimp ball
directions: Heat first 3 ingredients together; do not boil.
Set aside, then mix remaining ingredients together.
Add everything together and refrigerate overnight.

title: graham cracker toffee cookies
directions: Fit the graham crackers into a jellyroll pan in a single layer.
Mix butter, margarine and sugar together and boil 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour evenly over crackers and sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Remove from pan when cool and break into pieces.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Put chicken breasts in bottom of dish.
Add onion.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over chicken.

title: creamy broccoli bake
directions: Heat 1 inch salted water (1/2 teaspoon to 1 cup water).
Add broccoli.
Cover; heat to boiling.
Cook 10 to 12 minutes.
Place in ungreased 1 1/2-quart round casserole.
Heat oven to 400°.
Beat soup and milk until smooth; pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix Bisquick with margarine until crumbly.
Sprinkle over cheese.
Bake until crumbs are light brown, about 20 minutes.

title: perfect white bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine yeast and 2 1/2 cups flour.
Heat milk, sugar, salt and shortening until warm.
Stir occasionally for 1/2 minute, then beat 3 minutes at high speed.

title: creamy strawberry dessert
directions: In bowl, combine wafer crumbs, sugars and butter. Press into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish. Refrigerate for 30 minutes. Meanwhile, dissolve jello in boiling water. Stir in strawberries and milk. Refrigerate for 30 minutes or until partially set. Fold whipped topping into strawberry mixture. Spread over crust. Refrigerate until set.

title: pizza roll
directions: Let frozen dough rise.
Roll out dough thin.
Top with pepperoni, Mozzarella cheese, oregano and garlic powder.
Drizzle with olive oil.
Roll up carefully and secure ends.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Slice in 1/2-inch pieces.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Bring to boil sugar and Karo syrup.
Allow to boil several minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter and cornflakes.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.
Allow to cool.

title: cheesy spam bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook sliced potatoes in boiling water (salted) 15 minutes.
Drain, saving 1 cup of cooking liquid. Place potatoes in casserole dish.
Melt butter in large skillet. Add chopped onion and brown slightly; add paprika, thyme, flour, dried mustard, salt and pepper.
Stir in reserved liquid; add light cream and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add cubed Spam and 1/2 cup shredded sharp cheese.
Pour sauce over potatoes; toss lightly.
Top with 1/2 cup shredded sharp cheese; bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with green salad.

title: rocky road
directions: Line 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan with foil, extending foil over edges of pan.
Butter the foil.
In a medium bowl, cook chocolate, in microwave, on 100% power 1 minute, uncovered.
Stir, cook another minute.
Stir in marshmallows and nuts.
Spread in pan. Chill about 30 minutes or until firm.
Lift foil out.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Store tightly covered.
Yields about 80 pieces.

title: easy appetizers
directions: Mix chili sauce and jam together in a saucepan.
Roll chopped beef into small balls.
Add meat balls to saucepan mixture and simmer 45 to 60 minutes.
Cool and remove grease from top.
To serve, heat until warm.

title: passover matzo brei
directions: Break matzo into pieces. Soak in cold water until soft. Drain.
Beat eggs with remaining ingredients.
Pour over the drained matzo.
Heat shortening and pour into frying pan the matzo mixture and cook until brown.
Turn over and brown the other side. Serve with sugar, syrup or salt.

title: charlie's super supper(microwave)
directions: Microwave the broccoli on High power for 8 to 10 minutes or until hot.
Drain and spread in a 10 x 6-inch glass baking dish or 2 quart casserole dish.
Combine soup, 1 cup cheese, sour cream and Worcestershire sauce.
Break tuna into pieces and arrange on broccoli.
Spoon soup mixture evenly over tuna; spread to cover. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup cheese.
Microwave on Medium-high, uncovered, 12 to 14 minutes or until done or microwave by temperature, setting meal sensor temperature probe at 150°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Bake corn muffins according to directions and set aside to cool. Fry bacon and crumble into bowl. Chop finely the tomato, bell pepper, onion and celery stalks and add to bacon. Mix in salad dressing, salt and pepper. Crumble in corn muffins and continue to stir until all ingredients are mixed thoroughly. Serve immediately.

title: chuck wagon stew
directions: Dust beef with flour.
Brown in oil in heavy pot.
Add remaining ingredients except tomato sauce.
Cover with water. Simmer over low heat 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add tomato sauce.
Cook an additional 15 minutes.

title: quick "baked" apples
directions: Microwave:
Remove peel from top and halfway down side of each apple, starting at stem end.
With apple corer or sharp knife, remove core to within 1/4 inch of bottom of apple, leaving bottom stem end intact.
Place apples in 9-inch microwavable pie plate or shallow baking dish.

title: mini "peachy" cheesecakes
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Place paper liners into muffin tins. Place 1 whole vanilla wafer in each section and set aside.

title: tart dough
directions: Mix all dry ingredients. Add crisco. Combine eggs and milk. Mix well. Place in greased bowl. Let stand in refrigerator 2 or 4 hours or overnight.

title: preacher's casserole
directions: Brown ground meat; cook onions and celery in a little oil until transparent.
Mix all ingredients together; saving 1/4 of noodles to sprinkle on top.
Place in a buttered casserole dish (now can be refrigerated or frozen for use later).
To cook, bake in 350° oven for approximately 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all and cover with cornflakes.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.

title: strawberry slush
directions: Combine all ingredients and freeze in large containers.
When frozen, scoop into glass and pour in Squirt.

title: cottage cheese casserole
directions: Take the cottage cheese, add your 2 tablespoons of Miracle Whip, then add meat, then your taco sauce and mix them all together.
Then it's ready to eat.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Peel cucumbers and slice.
Slice onion and put cucumbers and onion in a large bowl and put salt on them.
Let them set for 10 minutes.
Then add Miracle Whip and mix well.
Chill until dinner.

title: creamy scalloped potatoes
directions: Layer potatoes and onion in 1 1/2-quart microwave casserole. Combine soup and milk in 2-cup glass measure.
Cook in microwave 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes or until it starts boiling. Add salt and pepper and dots of butter to potatoes.
Spread soup over top. Cover and cook 4 to 6 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate icing for pound cake
directions: Place sugar, milk, and margarine in small sauce pan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Boil one minute, stirring occasionally.
Remove and add chips and vanilla.
Cool while beating until desired consistency.
Spread on cake.

title: dream whip jello dessert
directions: Combine jello and 1 cup of boiling water only.
Let cool. Pour in marshmallows, mayonnaise and softened cream cheese. Drain pineapple and stir in.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, water and corn syrup (at 375°) or until golden brown; stir occasionally.
Stir in peanuts and salt until brown. Remove from heat.
Quickly stir in margarine and soda (brittle will foam).
Spread evenly into pan.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: lebkuchens
directions: Roll 1/2-inch thick and cut into rectangular shapes.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chunky barbecue sauce
directions: Heat butter; add onion and garlic and cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool.
Great on chicken, ribs and hamburgers.

title: gazpacho
directions: In covered blender container at high speed, blend first 10 ingredients 1/3 at a time until fairly smooth.
Pour into large bowl; cover and chill.
Serve in soup bowls and pass chopped vegetables and croutons for garnish.

title: barbecued venison
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain, crumble and set aside.
Cook meat and onion in drippings until meat is browned; drain and set aside.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut in cubes.
Cook potatoes until almost done.
Put in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour White Sauce over potatoes.
Arrange slices of cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Cream all of the ingredients together.
Let chill.
Roll into a ball, then in chopped nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: choco chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix with mixer the brown sugar, white sugar, shortening and margarine.
When mixed, add melted chocolate chips.
Then add eggs, flour, salt and soda.
Mix well.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Spray pan or dish with Pam.
Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 350° until lightly brown.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Grease pan.
Mix and bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chinese shrimp salad
directions: Cook shrimp.
Add lemon juice and Accent to drain shrimp. Marinate for 20 minutes.
Drain lemon juice from shrimp.
Add other ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Mix all ingredients except paprika together and chill. Sprinkle with paprika.
Can be shaped, if desired, after chilling.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix the sugar, oil, vanilla and eggs together by hand. Add the remaining ingredients. After mixing all ingredients together by hand, pour into 3 waxed paper-lined pans. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool before icing.

title: italian baked chicken
directions: Salt and pepper the
chicken
pieces
on both sides and line them on a pan covered with foil.
Put Italian dressing on top of chicken and bake for
hours at 350°.
Broil the last few minutes to make it crusty.

title: light batter
directions: In bowl, stir together first 5 ingredients; add water and egg. Stir until smooth.

title: peanut butter cup cookies
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter and sugars.
Add egg and vanilla. Mix flour, soda and salt.
Blend into batter.
Put rounded teaspoonful into each cup of mini-muffin pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Put 1 unwrapped Reese's cup into center of each. Allow to cool.
Remove from pan and enjoy!

title: tiramisu
directions: Place half the slices of cake in 7 x 9-inch cake dish.
Mix together the Espresso, Marsala and Amaretto.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Mix with hands only.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: crab cakes
directions: Saute onion and garlic until translucent.
Add flour to butter and make a roux.
Mix all ingredients together, form patties and fry in oil.
Drain on paper towels.

title: skinny soup
directions: Let simmer 3 hours, eat & get skinny!

title: squash casserole
directions: Butter 13 x 9-inch casserole.
Pour 1/2 package Pepperidge Farm bread crumbs in casserole.
Pour in squash mix.
Cover with rest of crumbs.
Pour on 3/4 stick of oleo.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: unfried french fries
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Slice potatoes into French fry strips. Mix egg whites and Cajun seasoning in small bowl.
Dip potato slices into egg white mixture and arrange on baking sheet (coat well with Pam spray).
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until crispy.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Mix butter, cracker crumbs, peanut butter, and sugar.
Put into a 11 inch x 15 inch pan.
Melt chocolate in top of double boiler.
Spread over crumb mixture.
Cut into squares when chocolate hardens.	Wonderful!

title: simple chicken bake
directions: Brown chicken and mushrooms in butter.
Place chicken in large greased casserole.
Mix undiluted soups and wine and pour over chicken.
Place mushrooms on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours. Serves 12.

title: potato-leek chowder
directions: Separate and wash leeks; slice them into 1/2-inch pieces.
In a nonstick, large saucepan, saute the potatoes and leeks in the butter for several minutes, stirring the vegetables to prevent browning.
Add the broth, pepper and salt.
Bring the chowder to a boil; reduce the heat.
Cover and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes or until tender.
Add the milk gradually and heat gently, but do not boil.
Stir in parsley; serve with grated cheese on top.

title: three cheese manicotti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook manicotti shells according to package directions.
Drain and set aside.
Heat oil in large saucepan and saute the onion, garlic and pepper.
Stir in the tomato sauce and seasonings.
Cover and let simmer, stirring occasionally. Combine 1 3/4
c. of the mozzarella with the cottage cheese, parmesan and beaten eggs.
Stir gently. Stuff the cheese mixture into the cooked drained shells, using about 1/4 cup per shell. Pour 1/2 c. sauce into a shallow 2 quart casserole dish.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Store in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: margaret's hungarian plum cake
directions: Let hot water run into a mixing bowl to heat, then dry.
Put in butter and cream.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and 1 egg.
Beat well, then add second egg.
Beat again.
Add flour, baking powder and salt. Stir and add flavoring.
Spread in buttered deep pie plate.
Cut plums in half and remove pits, do not peel.
Arrange in rows on batter, skin side down and press slightly.
Sprinkle with second 1/2 cup sugar mixed with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: praline bread pudding
directions: In a large bowl, add first 6 ingredients and blend well.
Saute the pecans in melted butter for 5 minutes.
When cooled down, add to bread mixture.
Place bread mixture in a lightly buttered (or spray oil) pan in a 9 x 12-inch oblong cake pan (metal or Corning Ware).
Fill 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° in preheated oven for one hour (individual souffle dishes optional).
Serves 16.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients for 3 full minutes.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
No icing needed.

title: mother's spaghetti and cheese
directions: Cook spaghetti in liberal amount of water until partially done.
Drain and place in baking dish.
Add cheese; cut into chunks.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with enough milk to about 2/3 cover spaghetti.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Cook in a 350° oven until browned on top.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Sift flour once; measure. Add baking soda, ginger and salt and sift again. Work butter with spoon until creamy. Add sugar gradually, beating after each addition until light and fluffy. Add egg. Add molasses. Add flour alternately with milk, beating after each addition until smooth. Chill for 1 hour or more. Turn onto floured board. Roll 1/4-inch thick. Cut with scalloped cookie cutter. Bake at 400° for 12 minutes. Makes 3 dozen 3-inch cookies.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix together; shape into balls (I find it helpful to let it sit for a while before trying to roll into balls), and freeze. Bake frozen at 350° for 15 minutes.
(Does not do well in the microwave.)

title: lemon-lime salad
directions: Dissolve lemon and lime Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Stir in 2 cups cold water.
Chill until partially set.
Add pie filling; beat until blended.
Add pineapple to 1 cup Jell-O mixture.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Fold Cool Whip into remaining Jell-O mixture.
Pour over pineapple mixture.
Chill until firm.

title: peanutty giant cookie
directions: Beat together the margarine, peanut butter and sugars until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs. Add combined flour, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in oats, raisins and 1/4 cup of the chocolate chips.

title: broccoli casserole (chicken)
directions: Mix together the chicken soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice.

title: crab bisque
directions: Saute mushrooms, onion, celery and carrot in butter in a large saucepan over low heat for 2 minutes, or until tender.
Add chicken broth, salt and red pepper.
Bring mixture to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Pour vegetable mixture into container of an electric blender; process until smooth. Combine vegetable puree, half and half, wine and crabmeat in a saucepan.
Cook until thoroughly heated.
Yields 6 cups.

title: lime jello mold
directions: Make jello according to package directions.
Let stand for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until nearly firm; beat.
Beat whipped cream and cheese together.
Fold in celery, pecans, pineapple and whipped jello.
Put into a large mold.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Boil broccoli, onion and water for 10 to 12 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients except instant potatoes.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Add instant potatoes.
Thicken with flour and water.

title: angel's hash
directions: Combine butter, sugar and eggs in large mixer and beat until light and fluffy (8 to 10 minutes).
Cover bottom of 10 x 15 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish with wafer crumbs; layer with custard mixture, then pineapple, then whipped cream.
Refrigerate 4 hours.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place apple slices in a long, glass casserole dish, in a single layer.
Set aside.
